**PATHS**

Step III of Character Creation

Primal Jarl  ·  Resonance Seeker  ·  Zodiac Priest  ·  Fade-Guardian

Solar Guard  ·  Rāśi-Siddha  ·  Oathed Vanguard  ·  Void-Hunter

Fate-Breaker  ·  Star-Born  ·  Scion-Pledged  ·  Comet-Magus

Stellar Cartographer  ·  Ashé-Medium  ·  Coil-Stalker  ·  Geode-Pilot

Primal Accord  ·  Accord-Maker

Calling chosen at Depth 3. See PART II for full depth progression.

**Note: **Your Path determines Vitality Die, primary resource system, and Calling options.

### **Choose Your Path**

**★ Stellar Cartographer · Fate-Mapper**

d8 · Fate-Knots · Omega

Store natural 20s and 1s as Fate-Knots; redistribute them to any creature within 60 ft. Read Fate Numbers as an Instinct. Map Fated Bonds. Eventually identify Quint Bond cluster members on sight. Callings: Loom's Hand (fate-agent), The Unwritten (fate-eraser, includes Number Masking), Star-Reader (celestial-scholar). Best for: players who want to engage with the Fated Bond system as a core mechanic and enjoy probabilistic manipulation.

**★ Ashé-Medium · The Vessel**

d8 · Ashé Vessel 0–10 · Omega

Invite Orisha presence rather than weaving Workings. Fill the Ashé Vessel through communal acts; spend it on Invocations and Full Possession (Game Master-controlled for 3 rounds). Power cannot be suppressed by Aether-Dampening Ore. Callings: Community Healer, War-Medium, Ancestor-Speaker. Best for: players who want to engage with the Ashélands storyline and enjoy a Path where the power source is relational.

**★ Coil-Stalker · The Controlled Corruption**

d10 · Lead-Scale Gauge 0–20 · Beta

Carry Void-energy as a weapon — the gauge fills with power and approaches dissolution simultaneously. Five corruption stages (Cold/Tempered/Burning/Searing/Void-Husk threshold) each granting escalating combat bonuses and escalating risks. Siderium Quartz reduces the gauge. Callings: Infiltrator, Purgator, Scion-Hunter. Best for: players who enjoy high-risk resource management and want the most morally complex Path in the game.

**★ Geode-Pilot · The Frame-Bonded**

d8 + Frame Pool · Frame Modes · Beta

Bond with a Resonant Geode-powered mechanical Frame — a second body with its own Vitality pool. Three modes (Sentinel/Scout/Resonance), Frame Modifications at every even Depth, Overclock (once per rest), and Resonant Cascade (devastating area discharge). Callings: Sentinel, Engineer, Scout. Best for: players who want a mech-pilot fantasy and enjoy managing a complex secondary system.

**Primal Jarl · The Threshold-Walker**

d12 · Wrath State · Alpha

Highest Vitality Die. Wrath State — release the filter between will and full Aetheric force. Resonant Fortune on Forcefulness, damage resistance, no Weaving abilities while Wrathing. Callings: Berserker (Norse), Steppe Sovereign (Centaur), Beast-Soul (Arcadian). Best for: players who want to be the front-line physical force and enjoy a Path with a clear power fantasy.

**Resonance Seeker · The Harmony-Finder**

d8 · Resonant Chord · Omega

Resonant Chord (bonus die given to any ally per rest — scales from d6 to d12). Frequency Mastery, Countersong. The Path most naturally aligned with the Fated Bond system — Bond Chord gives enlarged dice to Bonded allies. Callings: Lore-Keeper, Valor-Singer, Bond-Harmonist (can facilitate Bond formation). Best for: players who want to support the party and engage with the world's lore and Bond systems.

**Zodiac Priest · The Domain-Tender**

d8 · Aetheric Benediction · Omega · Epic Tier

Tends the memory of what the fallen gods were. Twelve Callings (one per zodiac sign domain). Aetheric Benediction (not suppressible by Ore). Legendary Beast Communion at Depth 7. Domain Embodiment at Depth 17. Epic Tier extends to Depth 30. Best for: players who want the most cosmically connected Path and don't mind that their power grows slowly but reaches extraordinary heights.

**Fade-Guardian · The Veil-Watcher**

d10 · Veil Walk · Omega

Veil Walk (step halfway into the Otherworld), Veil Smite, Seasonal Power (enhanced abilities during birth-tree season). Guards the threshold between worlds. Best for: players who want an Otherworld guardian with deep Tuathan Veil-walking connections.

**Solar Guard · The Prepared**

d10 · Surge of Will · Alpha/Beta

Most versatile warrior. Surge of Will (Vitality restore as Instinct; extra Act 2x/rest). Extra Strikes at Depths 5/11/20. Indomitable (reroll failed Warding Resonances). No cosmic inheritance — pure trained will. Callings: Solar Chivalry, Psi-Warrior (Jade), Runic Knight (Norse). Best for: players who want the highest damage output and fewest mechanical complications.

**Rāśi-Siddha · The Ascetic**

d8 · Tapas Points · Omega · Most Complete

Internal fire as a resource. Three expenditure tiers (Satvic/Rajasic/Tamasic). Kanya Temple can cure Ashen Coil blight-rot. Unarmored Guard Rating from Attunement. Twelve Temple Callings (one per sign). Best for: players who want a discipline-based martial artist with deep connection to the Scattered Temples and zodiac traditions.

**Oathed Vanguard · The Sworn**

d10 · Vitality of the Oath · Alpha

Power contingent on an Oath sworn before the Loom of Fate. Vitality of the Oath (healing pool), Aura of Oath (Warding Resonance bonus to nearby allies). Callings: Solar Compact (devotion), Loom's Justice (vengeance), Ancient Sideros (nature/protection). Best for: players who want an Oath-bound warrior with Sideros-specific cosmic stakes.

**Void-Hunter · The Coil-Tracker**

d10 · Void Quarry · Beta

Void Quarry (bonus damage and tracking against Coil operatives and Void-Husks). Terrain Attunement. Always knows the Quarry's direction within 1 mile. Callings: Void-Slayer, Stalker's Eye, Fang of the Resistance (intelligence network). Best for: players who want to engage directly with the Ashen Coil as their primary antagonist.

**Fate-Breaker · The Probability Thief**

d8 · Probability Strike · Beta

Number Masking (suppress a Fate Number from being read). Probability Strike (bonus damage scaling to 10d6). Cunning Act, Uncanny Dodge, Reliable Discipline. Callings: Probability Thief, Loom Operative (assassin), Street Philosopher (scout). Best for: players who want the rogue fantasy with Fate Number system integration.

**Star-Born · The Uncontrolled**

d6 · Zodiac Surge Points · Omega

Born already weaving — Surge Points convert to/from Aetheric Channels. Wild Surges on natural 1s (or deliberate pushing). Quickened/Empowered/Extended Workings. Callings: Zodiac Bloodline, Wild Surge Master, The Veil-Touched (shadow). Best for: players who want raw weaving power with an element of productive unpredictability.

**Scion-Pledged · The Contract**

d8 · Patron Channels · Omega

Patron Channels (refresh on Brief Attunement — the Patron owns the power). Patron's Mark (free ranged Working). Scion Boons (permanent abilities from deepening the contract). Patrons: Legendary Beast, one of the 13 Scions, or Aethar himself. Best for: players who want the warlock fantasy with high political stakes and a patron relationship that drives campaign plot. Callings: Legendary Beast Pact, Scion Pact, Aethar Pact.

**Comet-Magus · The Formulation Scholar**

d6 · Weave Recovery · Beta

The Kallos-Sworn's scholarly tradition. Formulation Ledger (prepared Workings from research). Weave Recovery (partial Channel restore on Brief Attunement). Three Conclaves as Callings — Shifting Horizons (Aethar's former Conclave), Earthly Core, Veil-Walkers. Best for: players who want the wizard fantasy, Argent Spire storyline access, and depth of Working variety.

**★ Primal Accord · The Accord-Walker**

d8 · Aspect Manifestation · Alpha/Beta split

The Accord-Walker does not worship the Legendary Beasts — they walk in accord with what the Beasts already are. Arcadian theology reads the Pantheonic Fall as a choice: the twelve gods redistributed their divinity into distributed biological presence. Dual resource: Aspect Manifestation (nature Working-equivalents) and Beast Resonance Pool (builds near Legendary Beast sacred sites, through sustained interaction with Resonant Emanations, and through proximity to Apex Emanations). Callings: Grove-Tender, Storm-Caller, Moon-Walker, Earth-Shaper, Spore-Accord, Kore-kore Walker, Waka-tōhora. Best for: players who want the Druid fantasy with deep Legendary Beast connections and Arcadia Major storyline access.

**★ Accord-Maker · The Living Machine Tradition**

d8 · Infusions + Blueprints · Beta/Alpha

Approaches the Aether the way a Dunmarim master-smith approaches a difficult alloy — with precise knowledge of its properties and no illusions about who is in charge. Dual resource: Infusion List (temporary Aetheric properties on weapons, armor, items) and Blueprint List (permanent constructs built between sessions, Tier I through V). Operates in Aether-Dampening Ore zones at reduced tier rather than failing. Callings: Alchemist, Architect, Armorer (Dunmarim), Siege Engineer. Best for: players who want the Artificer/Inventor fantasy — rewards between-session preparation.

### **Resonance Attribute Generation Methods**

Choose one of three methods below. All methods produce the same six attributes: Forcefulness, Swiftness, Endurance, Acuity, Attunement, Resonance. After generating base scores, apply your Kindred's bonuses (listed in your Kindred entry). The modifier formula is the same for all scores: modifier = (score - 10) / 2, rounded down.

### **Attribute Score to Modifier Reference**

| **Score** | **Modifier** | **Score** | **Modifier** | **Score** | **Modifier** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1** | -5 | **2-3** | -4 | **4-5** | -3 |
| **6-7** | -2 | **8-9** | -1 | **10-11** | +0 |
| **12-13** | +1 | **14-15** | +2 | **16-17** | +3 |
| **18-19** | +4 | **20-21** | +5 | **22-23** | +6 |
| **24-25** | +7 | **26-27** | +8 | **28-29** | +9 |
| **30** | +10 |  |  |  |  |

### **Method A: The Fated Scores (Recommended)**

| **The Loom****'****s Gift** The dice set the Loom's pattern. The swap is you. The Kindred bonus is blood. The final number is the soul. |
| --- |

| **Step** | **Instructions** |
| --- | --- |
| **1** | Roll 4d6 and drop the lowest die. Repeat six times. Record the six results. |
| **2** | Assign each result to one of the six Resonance Attributes in the order you rolled them: Forcefulness, Swiftness, Endurance, Acuity, Attunement, Resonance. |
| **3** | You may swap exactly two scores with each other -- moving one score to a different Attribute. Only one swap is permitted. This represents the soul asserting one truth about itself. |
| **4** | Apply your Kindred's Attribute bonuses to the final scores. Calculate modifiers from the table above. Record all six scores and modifiers on your character sheet. |

### **Method B: The Loom****'****s Array (Standard Array)**

Use the following six scores and assign them to attributes in any order: **15, 14, 13, 12, 10, 8**. No swaps needed -- assign freely. This produces a balanced character with one strong focus area and one notable weakness. Good for players who want predictable build math or are creating their first character.

### **Method C: Point Buy (Customised Array)**

You have **27 points** to spend. Scores below 8 are not permitted. Scores above 15 (before Kindred bonuses) are not permitted. Spend points from the table below. This produces highly tailored characters at the cost of potential extremes.

| **Score** | **Point Cost** | **Score** | **Point Cost** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **8** | 0 | **9** | 1 |
| **10** | 2 | **11** | 3 |
| **12** | 4 | **13** | 5 |
| **14** | 7 | **15** | 9 |

### **Which Attribute to Prioritise**

| **Attribute** | **Primary Paths** | **Governs** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Forcefulness** | Primal Jarl, Solar Guard, Oathed Vanguard | Athletics, Intimidation. Melee Strike Resonances and damage for most martial Paths. Primal Jarl adds FOR to damage in Wrath State. |
| **Swiftness** | Fate-Breaker, Coil-Stalker | Acrobatics, Stealth, Sleight of Hand. Guard Rating for light armour. Pulse Order (initiative). Ranged attacks for most Paths. |
| **Endurance** | All Paths equally | No Disciplines -- expresses through Vitality maximum and Warding Resonances against physical harm, poison, and disease. |
| **Acuity** | Comet-Magus, Geode-Pilot | Aetheric Lore, History, Investigation, Nature. Weaving Attribute for intelligence-based Paths. |
| **Attunement** | Rāśi-Siddha, Zodiac Priest, Stellar Cartographer, Ashé-Medium | Perception, Insight, Medicine, Animal Handling, Survival. Tapas Points for Siddha. Most healing Paths. |
| **Resonance** | Resonance Seeker, Star-Born, Scion-Pledged, Ashé-Medium | Deception, Performance, Persuasion. Fated Bond Active Resonances. Chord Die size for Resonance Seeker. |

### **Generate Resonance Attributes**

### **Forcefulness-primary Paths**

Physical Force

Primal Jarl, Solar Guard, Oathed Vanguard (for strikes). Put your highest score here if you want to hit hard and often. Forcefulness also governs Athletics and most physical feats of strength. Primal Jarl in Wrath State adds Forcefulness to melee damage — every point matters.

### **Attunement-primary Paths**

Cosmic Sensitivity

Rāśi-Siddha, Zodiac Priest, Ashé-Medium, Stellar Cartographer, most Omega Paths. Attunement governs Tapas Points, Perception, Insight, healing, and most Warding Resonances against mental forces. If your Path is about perceiving and responding to the world rather than imposing force on it, Attunement is your primary Attribute.

### **Resonance-primary Paths**

Magnetic Presence

Ashé-Medium, Stellar Cartographer, Resonance Seeker, Star-Born, Scion-Pledged. Resonance governs all social Disciplines, the Fated Bond Active Resonances, and Weaving for Paths that use it as their Weaving Attribute. A high Resonance is the difference between a Resonance Seeker who gives their allies d6 Chords and one who gives d12s.

### **Acuity-primary Paths**

Pattern Recognition

Comet-Magus, Geode-Pilot. Acuity governs Aetheric Lore, Investigation, History, Nature, and the Weaving Attribute for Paths that draw on analytical intelligence. A high Acuity Comet-Magus prepares more Formulations per Deep Attunement and has a higher Working Threshold for everything they weave.

**Roll once per Attribute · Then swap two scores**

### **Roll Your Fate**

Roll 1d100. Record this number — it is yours permanently. It never changes except through extraordinary cosmic intervention.

Your zodiac sign is the cosmic force the Loom has designated you to express. It determines your Zodiac Attunement (Feat) at Depth 4, your Kindred-Zodiac Resonance ability, and which Legendary Beast will eventually recognize you as a peer.

### **Determining Sign from Fate Number (optional)**

Loom Method

If you want fate to determine your sign: divide your Fate Number by 100, multiply by 12, round up. Or use this table: 1–8: ♈ Aries · 9–17: ♉ Taurus · 18–25: ♊ Gemini · 26–33: ♋ Cancer 34–41: ♌ Leo · 42–50: ♍ Virgo · 51–58: ♎ Libra · 59–67: ♏ Scorpio 68–75: ♐ Sagittarius · 76–83: ♑ Capricorn · 84–92: ♒ Aquarius · 93–100: ♓ Pisces The Loom method produces a character whose sign and number share a domain — they are doubly designated by the same force.

**ORIGINS**

Step VI of Character Creation

Scholarly  ·  5 Origins  ·  Comet-Magi Initiate, Siddha Acolyte,       Loom Analyst, Order of Pure Reason Researcher, Stellar Observer

Merchant  ·  4 Origins  ·  Silk Road Guild Operative, Dunmarim Master-Smith,       Port Damaris Shadow-Council Agent, Far-Trade Factor

Shadow  ·  4 Origins  ·  Coil-Adjacent Operative, Trench Keeper Deserter,       Outlander, Noble House Exile

Wanderer  ·  5 Origins  ·  Moana-kin Navigator-Initiate, Steppe Rider,       Kallos-Sworn Field Agent, Ceque-Walker, Waka Navigator

Marked  ·  6 Origins  ·  Legendary Beast Witness, Quint Bond Adjacent,       Orisha-Touched Lineage, Ceque Line Born, Void-Touched Survivor, Kallos Dreamer

**Note: **Each Origin includes disciplines, feature, equipment, personality traits, ideals, bond, flaw, and 3 hooks.

### **Choose Your Origin**

Your Origin is not your Path. It is what came before — the experiences and relationships and choices that made you the kind of person the Path would eventually call. A Comet-Magus with a Merchant Origin brings a particular kind of pragmatism to their formulations. A Primal Jarl with a Scholarly Origin fights differently than one with a Wanderer Origin. The Origin shapes the person; the Path shapes the power.

Your Calling — the specific direction within your Path — is chosen at Depth 3, not Depth 1. This is intentional. The first two Depths of play are the character discovering which aspect of their Path resonates most deeply. You should know your options now (they're listed in the Path document), but the choice itself happens through play.

Choose one of your Path's starting packages, then take the equipment listed for your Origin category. You may also take the starting Gold Marks option instead of your Path's package if you prefer to purchase equipment directly.

Package A (grove-tender / ocean-walker): Leather armor or hide armor, a druidic focus (zodiac-aspected carved wooden staff or beast-talisman), an explorer's pack, a healer's kit (10 uses), a herbalism kit, a Beast-Resonance Journal (blank — for recording Legendary Beast observations during play).

Package B (storm-caller / void-walker): Leather armor, a quarterstaff, a druidic focus, a diplomat's pack, a collection of natural materials from three different ecosystems (Game Master determines significance of each).

Package A (Alchemist / Architect): Leather armor, a dagger, an alchemist's kit, a set of artisan's tools (smith's or tinker's by Calling direction), an explorer's pack, an Infusion Ledger (blank), and one starting Tier I Blueprint (mechanical trap or alchemical device — determined with Game Master at Session Zero).

Package B (Armorer / Siege Engineer): Scale mail (self-modified — includes one built-in Infusion agreed with Game Master at Session Zero), a hand crossbow with 20 bolts, a medium shield, armorer's tools, an explorer's pack, an Infusion Ledger.

### **Warrior Path Package**

Primal Jarl · Solar Guard · Oathed Vanguard · Void-Hunter

Package A (front-line): Chain mail or scale mail, a martial weapon of choice, a shield, 5 javelins, an adventurer's pack (bedroll, mess kit, tinderbox, 10 torches, 10 days' rations, waterskin, 50 ft hempen rope). Package B (mobile): Leather armor, two martial weapons, a light crossbow with 20 bolts, an adventurer's pack. Void-Hunter specific addition: A Hunter's Journal (contains notes on one Coil operative's known location — outdated but a starting lead).

### **Weaving Path Package**

Comet-Magus · Star-Born · Zodiac Priest · Stellar Cartographer · Ashé-Medium

Package A (scholar): A quarterstaff, a component pouch, an explorer's pack, a Formulation Ledger (Comet-Magus) or ritual journal (other Paths), a set of robes in your house colors (Kallos-Sworn) or plain traveling clothes (others). Package B (traveler): A dagger, an arcane focus (zodiac-aspected crystal or carved wooden focus), a diplomat's pack, a letter of introduction from a relevant institution (Argent Spire, a Scattered Temple, the Ifá tradition). Ashé-Medium specific addition: A ritual bundle (materials for Orisha Invocation — specific to your patron Orisha, assembled with a priest's guidance).

### **Skilled Path Package**

Fate-Breaker · Resonance Seeker · Rāśi-Siddha

Package A (performer/operative): A rapier or shortsword, a light crossbow with 20 bolts, leather armor, a musical instrument or thieves' tools (based on Path and Calling direction), an entertainer's pack or burglar's pack. Package B (wandering): Two daggers, leather armor, a lute or deck of fortune-telling cards (narrative item), a diplomat's pack. Rāśi-Siddha specific: No weapon required — unarmed strikes are your weapon. Replace weapon with: a meditation mat, a set of prayer beads (Tapas Point tracking aid), and your Temple's traveler's robe.

### **Unique Path Packages**

Coil-Stalker · Geode-Pilot · Scion-Pledged · Fade-Guardian

Coil-Stalker: Dark leather armor, two shortswords, a vial of Siderium Quartz (2 charges — the only thing keeping your gauge in check), a burglar's pack, and a dossier on your current target. Geode-Pilot: Your Resonant Frame (already bonded — it is you), artisan's tools (for Frame maintenance), a navigator's pack, and a letter of introduction from the Jade Empire or the Grand Prime Forgeman (your choice). Scion-Pledged: Any light armor, a weapon of choice, a scholar's pack, and a contract document (sealed — the actual terms are between you and your Patron; the Game Master has seen them). Fade-Guardian: Any armor permitted by your Oath tradition (light, medium, or heavy — your Veil-Walking nature imposes no restriction), a martial weapon, a holy symbol (Otherworld-aspected — a silver branch, a knot-worked disk), a priest's pack.

### **The Starting Package**

### **Scholarly Origins**

**Comet-Magi Initiate**   Scholarly · Argent Spire

You trained at Argent Spire — not long enough to reach a significant Circle, but long enough to absorb the Conclaves' framework and leave with something they didn't intend you to keep.

| **Disciplines:  **Aetheric Lore, History | **Tool / Language:  **Calligrapher's supplies · One of: Old Kallosian, Eldren script, or Conclave notation |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Formulation Fragment** You retain a suppressed Comet-Magi Formulation — a Working the Conclaves consider too dangerous to teach formally. Once per Deep Attunement, attempt to express it: Working Threshold check DC 15. On success: produce a 2nd-tier Working effect (agreed at character creation). On failure: the fragment destabilizes, dealing 1d6 psychic damage. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Scholar's pack, Comet-Magi initiate's robe, personal Formulation Ledger with notes, 15 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I quote from texts most people have never heard of — and I know this is irritating. I collect small facts the way other people collect wounds. | Knowledge is the only thing that outlasts catastrophe. The truth is worth knowing even when it costs you peace. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| A mentor at Argent Spire taught me something I'm still working out. | I underestimate things I can't quantify. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Why did you leave before completing your training?

▸  Which Conclave did you align with — and do you still agree with their position?

▸  What is in the suppressed Formulation fragment you retained?

**Siddha Acolyte**   Scholarly · Temple Tradition

You were raised in or drawn to one of the Twelve Scattered Temples — not as a full Siddha, but as a student who absorbed the tradition's rhythms, mantras, and cosmological framework.

| **Disciplines:  **Religion (Siddha tradition), Medicine | **Tool / Language:  **Herbalist's supplies · Classical language of your temple's sign-culture |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Temple Blessing** Your sign's Temple has acknowledged your training. Once per Deep Attunement, spend 10 minutes in meditation to invoke your sign's temple blessing — a minor Working effect tied to your sign's domain requiring no Aetheric Channel. Game Master determines the specific effect (Mesha = weapon enhancement; Kanya = remove Corrupted; Vrishchika = read emotional history of touched object; etc.). |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Prayer beads, healer's kit (10 uses), traveler's clothes, your sign's temple's foundational mantra text, 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I find stillness in crisis — which unnerves people who are not still. I treat silence as a complete answer to difficult questions. | Discipline is the only freedom that cannot be taken. The mantra is more honest than the practitioner. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| My teacher's final lesson was unfinished when they died. | I dismiss practical problems that could be solved with less dignity. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Which temple did you train at — and why did you leave?

▸  Do you still practice the mantras? What do they mean to you now?

▸  What does the temple want from you that you haven't delivered?

**Loom Analyst**   Scholarly · Loom of Fate Intelligence

You worked for the Loom of Fate as an analyst — not field operations, but Fate Numbers, bond patterns, probability clusters. You processed intelligence that would disturb most people. You eventually found something that disturbed you.

| **Disciplines:  **Investigation, Insight | **Tool / Language:  **Forgery kit · One language of your choice |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Pattern Recognition** When you succeed on an Insight Active Resonance, you may ask the Game Master one yes/no question about whether the situation contains a concealed element — a hidden agenda, a false identity, a missing piece of information. The Game Master must answer honestly. Cannot use this twice in the same scene. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Forgery kit, coded journal (DC 18 to decipher), Loom of Fate contact cipher (reaches a specific handler — if still active), 20 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I know more than I should about most people I've just met. I maintain cover habits even when I don't need them. | Information is neutral. What you do with it isn't. The Loom sees all threads — I only needed to see the relevant ones. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| I was assigned to protect someone. I failed. Or I didn't — I'm still not sure. | I compartmentalize too effectively. People feel this. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What did you find in the Loom's records that you weren't supposed to see?

▸  Are you still employed — or did you burn that bridge?

▸  Who is attached to your contact cipher, and do you trust them?

**Order of Pure Reason Researcher**   Scholarly · Dunmarim · Anti-Working

You were part of the Order of Pure Reason's research division — studying the world scientifically, attempting to explain Aetheric effects through natural philosophy. You have since left, been expelled, or simply stopped believing the Order's conclusions are sufficient.

| **Disciplines:  **Nature, Investigation | **Tool / Language:  **Alchemist's supplies · Dunmarim technical notation |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Scientific Method** Resonant Fortune on all Warding Resonances against being surprised, Soul-Swayed, or Dread-Struck by Aetheric phenomena — you recognize the mechanism. Additionally: identify any Aetheric Artifact's school and approximate tier by examining it for 1 minute (no Working required). |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Alchemist's supplies, research journal (valuable to multiple factions), Order of Pure Reason credentials (opens or closes doors), 15 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I ask questions before I act, which sometimes costs me the moment. I am more comfortable with systems than with people. | The truth exists independent of who finds it. A flawed model is better than no model — but only if you know it's flawed. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| A colleague remained inside the Order when I left. I owe them an accounting of what I found. | I require evidence past the point where most people have already decided. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What did you observe that the Order's framework couldn't explain?

▸  The Order considers former members a security concern — are they right to?

▸  Your research journal would interest multiple factions. Who knows you have it?

**Stellar Observer**   Scholarly · Celestial Study

You spent years watching the sky from a tower, a hillside, or the back of a cart moving between observation points. You think in patterns that span centuries. Most conversations feel short.

| **Disciplines:  **Aetheric Lore, Perception | **Tool / Language:  **Navigator's tools (star charts, astrolabe) · One additional language |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Celestial Memory** You have memorized the current position of every major celestial body. Under open sky: always know the exact time, date, season, and geographic position — no tools required. Underground or indoors: know precisely how long you've been away from the sky. The Centaur-Kin recognize this as a lesser form of their Stellar Cartography — they are not wrong. Additionally: Resonant Fortune on Aetheric Lore Active Resonances related to astronomical or zodiac timing. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Navigator's tools, a personal star log spanning several years of observations, traveler's clothes, 12 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I think in longer patterns than most conversations allow. I note celestial events even when no one asked me to. | The stars don't lie. People do. Pattern is the most honest form of truth. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone funded my observations for years. I don't know why. | I notice the wrong things at the wrong moments — cosmically significant, immediately useless. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What did you observe in the sky that prompted you to stop watching and start moving?

▸  The Great Orrery in Aetheria is the most sophisticated astronomical instrument ever built. Have you seen it?

▸  Your star log contains an anomaly from six months ago that you haven't been able to explain.

### **Merchant Origins**

**Silk Road Guild Operative**   Merchant · Trans-Continental Trade

The Silk Road Guild officially connects every major trading hub in the world. Unofficially, it also moves information, people who need to disappear, and goods that don't appear on manifests. You know which version of the Guild you worked for.

| **Disciplines:  **Persuasion, Deception | **Tool / Language:  **Navigator's tools · Trader's Common (trade pidgin, understood at all major ports) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Guild Contacts** In any city or major trading post, find a Guild contact within 1d4 hours. The contact can provide: current commodity prices; local political summary; one night's safe house; hiring intelligence. The contact operates on mutual benefit — not loyalty. Asking for something that risks them costs a favor. The Game Master tracks what favors you owe. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Guild signet ring, merchant's scale, letter of credit worth 50 Gold Marks (redeemable at any Guild office), fine clothes, 25 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I price everything, including things that aren't for sale. I form alliances before I form friendships — both can become the other. | A fair deal is one both parties walk away from having gained something. Movement is safety — anything stationary can be surrounded. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone on the route still owes me a debt I intend to collect. | I trust negotiation over direct action past the point of usefulness. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Are you still a Guild operative — or did you leave? If you left, did they let you?

▸  Drava Nullsong used Silk Road Guild infrastructure to build the Fang of the Whisper. Do you know something about that?

▸  What was the last shipment you moved that you've been trying to forget?

**Dunmarim Master-Smith**   Merchant · Stone Kingdom Craft

You trained under a Dunmarim master-smith — the most rigorous craft tradition in the world. You may not be Dunmarim yourself, but you spent enough years in the Stone Kingdom to absorb their approach to material and work. Your hands know things your mind hasn't caught up with yet.

| **Disciplines:  **Athletics, History (material culture) | **Tool / Language:  **Smith's tools, Mason's tools · Dunmarim (spoken and written) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Master****'****s Hand** When you craft using your Mastered tools, the result is always one quality tier higher than the materials would normally allow. Additionally: identify the origin, approximate age, and quality of any worked metal or stone object in 1 minute. This includes Aetheric Artifacts made of metal or stone — you know they've been worked even if you don't know how. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Smith's tools, a masterwork personal weapon or tool (worth twice standard price), Dunmarim letter of reference, 15 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I respect work and have strong opinions about work done badly. I see the construction of everything I encounter. | Good work is its own argument. Bad work is too. The craft outlasts the craftsperson — make it worth outlasting you. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| I made something for someone important. They died before receiving it. | I take longer than the situation allows when quality matters to me. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Who was your master-smith, and why did you leave their workshop?

▸  The Dunmarim are suspicious of anyone who takes their craft knowledge out of the Stone Kingdom. Are they right to be?

▸  Your masterwork piece — what is it, and what does it mean to you?

**Port Damaris Shadow-Council Agent**   Merchant · Underground Economy

Port Damaris runs on a dual economy — the legitimate merchant layer the Duchy Compact recognizes, and the Shadow-Council layer that actually controls the city. You worked for the latter. You know how the city really works, which is not the same as how it appears to work.

| **Disciplines:  **Deception, Intimidation | **Tool / Language:  **Thieves' tools · Port Damaris cant (coded trading language, recognized in any underground economy) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — City Infrastructure** In any city you've spent at least a week in, you know its hidden infrastructure. Upon arriving in a new city, after 24 hours of observation, identify: one safe house, one official susceptible to bribery (and their price), one black market contact. The Game Master provides these as specific NPCs — not abstractions. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Thieves' tools, dark common clothes, Port Damaris Shadow-Council token, 30 Gold Marks (mixed denominations, nothing traceable)

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I notice exits before I notice decor. I don't confirm or deny things unless I have to. | The law protects people who can afford it. Understanding someone is not the same as trusting them. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone got me out of a situation I couldn't have escaped alone. I owe them. | I assume the worst about institutions before they've had a chance to disappoint me. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Why did you leave Port Damaris — or are you still technically employed?

▸  The Shadow-Council doesn't like former agents who know too much. What do you know that makes you a liability?

▸  The Lunar Queen may be operating in Port Damaris's economy. Do you know something?

**Far-Trade Factor**   Merchant · Cross-Cultural Intermediary

You managed trade relationships across cultural lines — you know how different peoples value different things and why. You've sat at tables where every assumption about what matters was wrong, learned to read the room, and survived on the difference between what people say they want and what they actually need.

| **Disciplines:  **Deception, Insight | **Tool / Language:  **Navigator's tools · Two additional languages (cross-cultural trade requires range) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Cultural Fluency** You have spent enough time with at least three Kindred cultures that you understand their social assumptions intuitively. You are never accidentally offensive when you know you're in unfamiliar cultural territory — you ask the right questions first. NPCs from Kindreds you've traded with start at Friendly disposition rather than Neutral. Additionally: Resonant Fortune on Insight Active Resonances when trying to understand a cultural or social motive rather than a personal one. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Fine clothes (culturally appropriate for two different regions), a trading ledger with coded notes on contacts across three territories, 20 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I adjust my manner to whoever I'm speaking with — this is respect, not deception. I notice what people want before they say it. | Mutual benefit is not naivety — it's the only sustainable arrangement. Understanding someone is not the same as agreeing with them. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| A trading partner became something else. I haven't resolved what. | I read manipulation into generosity more often than is warranted. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Which cultural crossing taught you the most — and cost you the most?

▸  You've moved goods across lines that politics says are closed. Who knows about those routes?

▸  One of your long-term contacts has recently gone silent. What does that mean?

### **Shadow Origins**

**Coil-Adjacent Operative**   Shadow · Ashen Coil (Former)

You worked for an organization that was — you now realize — either directly part of the Ashen Coil or one of its front operations. You didn't know at the time. Or you knew and chose not to look too closely. Either version of this story has consequences.

| **Disciplines:  **Stealth, Deception | **Tool / Language:  **Thieves' tools or Poisoner's kit (your choice) · Coil operational cipher |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Coil Pattern Recognition** Resonant Fortune on Insight and Investigation Active Resonances when investigating Coil activity, agents, or operations. Additionally: once per session, ask the Game Master whether a specific person, organization, or location has any Coil connection — answered based on what your operational knowledge would realistically reveal. Your knowledge has gaps and dates — this is not omniscience. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Dark travel clothes, forged identity document (one alias), a Coil dead-letter drop location (Game Master decides if it's still monitored), 20 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I understand the appeal of the Coil better than most people who fight it — this is useful and uncomfortable. I am careful about what I say I believe in, having believed in something that turned out to be wrong. | I am not what I did. I am what I do next. The Coil's logic was coherent. Its conclusion was wrong. That distinction matters. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone I recruited is still inside. I owe them an attempt at extraction. | I am waiting for the people I travel with to discover what I was and leave. Some part of me thinks they should. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What was the operation that made you realize what you were actually working for?

▸  The Coil doesn't retire operatives. What is the current status of your relationship with them?

▸  Does anyone in your current party know this about you?

**Trench Keeper Deserter**   Shadow · Military · The Maw

You served in the Trench Keepers — the garrison holding the line between the world and whatever the Maw contains. You left before your tour ended. What you saw down there is the reason. Whether desertion was the right call is something you're still working out.

| **Disciplines:  **Athletics, Survival | **Tool / Language:  **One artisan's tool (your garrison role) · Trench Keeper operational shorthand |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Void-Hardened** Resonant Fortune on Warding Resonances against Void-Touched Exposure and against Dread-Struck effects from undead and Void-energy manifestations. Additionally: you automatically succeed on Attunement Warding Resonances to detect Void-energy presence within 30 ft. You've spent enough time near it to recognize the specific quality of its absence. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Medium armor (garrison issue — functional, technically still military property), personal weapon, Trench Keeper's compass (always points toward the Maw's center), 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I don't flinch from necessary things — I have done necessary things. I watch exits and assume I'm being watched. | The thing that marks you doesn't own you. It just lives with you. I survived. That has to mean something. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| A fellow Keeper covered for my desertion. I don't know if they survived what came next. | I sometimes freeze when I should move. The body remembers. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What did you see in the Maw that made you leave?

▸  The Trench Keepers will arrest a deserter on sight. How do you manage this?

▸  Regent Ophiomorph may be someone you served under. What is your relationship?

**Outlander**   Shadow · Beyond Institutional Reach

You grew up outside every institution — in the Kurgan Bog's margins, in the deep Boreal wilderness, in a nomadic community that avoided settlements, or simply alone in a landscape the Duchy Compact's maps mark as empty. You know things about the world that people who grew up in cities don't know. They know things you don't. The exchange is ongoing.

| **Disciplines:  **Survival, Nature | **Tool / Language:  **Herbalist's supplies · One regional language (Steppe-tongue, Boreal dialects, Bog-cant, etc.) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Wanderer****'****s Memory** You can always find food and fresh water in natural environments — not abundantly, but sufficiently. You can navigate by stars, landmarks, and environmental reading without tools and cannot be lost in natural terrain. In urban environments, you find the natural infrastructure instinctively — Resonant Fortune on Investigation Active Resonances to find exits, weak points, or natural resources in built environments. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **A staff, a hunting trap, a bedroll, traveler's clothes, a trophy from your home environment (tooth, feather, stone — with personal significance), 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I say less than I think in most situations. I am patient in a way that people who grew up in cities find unsettling. | The land will provide if you know how to ask. Clean kills are mercy — everything else is cruelty. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| I saw something in the margins that I've never told anyone. I'm not sure it wanted to be seen. | I undervalue shelter, warmth, and company in ways that concern people who care about me. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What brought you out of the wilderness and into contact with the world's institutions?

▸  Is there something in the wilderness you're trying to return to — or something you're running from?

▸  What do you not understand about how cities work that creates friction with your companions?

**Noble House Exile**   Shadow · Political Fall

You had position, wealth, or both — until you didn't. The reasons vary. The fall was real. What you did with it afterward is what actually defines you, though the people from your former world haven't figured that out yet.

| **Disciplines:  **Persuasion, History | **Tool / Language:  **One gaming set (politics is played at game tables) · One additional language |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Position of Privilege** Your bearing and manner communicate authority even after your title is gone. NPCs give you the benefit of the doubt in formal situations — you are assumed to belong until specifically challenged. Additionally: once per session, invoke a former contact from your house days — someone who remembers owing you something, or who prefers you think well of them. The Game Master determines their current disposition and what they can offer. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Fine clothes (slightly worn — quality visible despite age), a signet ring from your former house (controversial to display), a letter of introduction to one surviving ally, 15 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I speak to servants with the same directness I use with lords — both find this disorienting. I understand the rules well enough to know when they're being bent. | Position is earned, not inherited. I know this now. The house failed its people. I didn't — or I'm trying not to. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone in my former house was innocent of what I was accused of. I owe them a clearing of their name. | I still think in terms of houses and factions when individuals are what actually matter. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What caused the fall — and who benefited from it?

▸  Is there anyone from your former house who would help you — and anyone who would actively work against you?

▸  What would restoration of your position actually require, and do you still want it?

### **Wanderer Origins**

**Moana-kin Navigator-Initiate**   Wanderer · Ara Moana Tradition

You trained in the Ara Moana navigation tradition — not as a full Waka-tōhora practitioner, but someone who absorbed the foundational framework. The ocean is a different kind of landscape when you understand how to read it. So is any landscape that moves.

| **Disciplines:  **Survival (navigation), Perception | **Tool / Language:  **Navigator's tools, Water vehicles · Moana-kin (spoken); Pre-Fall Star Charts notation |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Ara Moana Attunement** You have learned the foundational Shelter Sense ability from the Ara Moana system — you always know the direction and approximate distance to genuine safety (cannot be fooled by illusions). Additionally: you cannot be lost in any environment with an open sky; you always know cardinal directions and approximate time without tools. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Navigator's tools, a Pre-Fall Star Chart (partial — illegible in places, genuine navigational data throughout), sailor's clothes, 15 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I am more comfortable moving than staying. I navigate by feel as much as calculation, which makes me hard to teach and hard to argue with. | The route is the answer — everything else is just deciding whether to take it. Home is whoever you're navigating toward. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| I lost someone in the Mirror Sea. I'm not certain they're dead. | I undervalue staying. Some things require you to stop moving. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What route did you navigate that you haven't been able to stop thinking about?

▸  The Mirror Sea is expanding. Does your navigational sense register it differently than ordinary water?

▸  Your Star Chart has markings you don't understand. Who made them?

**Steppe Rider**   Wanderer · Sagittarian Steppes

You grew up on the Sagittarian Steppes — a landscape of impossible distances and constant movement. You learned to ride before you learned to read. The Steppes produced you and have opinions about where you're going, none of which have stopped you.

| **Disciplines:  **Animal Handling, Athletics | **Tool / Language:  **Land vehicles; Land mounts · Steppe-tongue (understood by Centaur-Kin communities) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Born to the Saddle** Resonant Fortune on Animal Handling Active Resonances involving mounts, including unusual mounts (Centaur-Kin, oversized creatures). When mounted: movement speed +10 ft; cannot be dismounted without consent unless you fail Swiftness Warding Resonance DC 15. Additionally: make Strike Resonances with ranged weapons while mounted without Resonant Discord from mount movement. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **A riding horse (Steppe-bred, worth 100 Gold Marks), shortbow with 40 arrows, Steppe riding clothes, a clan-mark brand or tattoo (identifies you to Steppe communities), 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I give directions in terms of landmark and horizon rather than left and right. I find enclosed spaces oppressive in a way I can't fully explain. | Distance is not an obstacle — it's the point. Loyalty to the clan is real, but the clan has to earn it again each season. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| My horse was a gift from someone who knew they were sending me away. I haven't figured out how to repay that. | I make decisions based on where I can go, not just whether I should go there. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What drove you off the Steppes?

▸  The Steppe clans and the Centaur-Kin have complicated politics. Where do you stand?

▸  Lord Sagittarius controls the region. Do you have a relationship with his administration?

**Kallos-Sworn Field Agent**   Wanderer · Kallos-Sworn

You trained with the Kallos-Sworn and served as a field agent — not at a high Circle, but long enough to carry their methods and their responsibilities. You know what the Kallos-Sworn are for, which means you know why they sometimes fail.

| **Disciplines:  **Aetheric Lore, Persuasion or Stealth (your field role) | **Tool / Language:  **Calligrapher's supplies · Old Kallosian (Kallos-Sworn internal notation) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Kallos-Sworn Access** You retain credentials at your departure Circle (Circles 1–4 for this Origin — higher Circles are Path-level). In any city with a Kallos-Sworn House: access to the House's common room, non-restricted library, and communication relay; recognized by Kallos-Sworn members at your Circle and below; Resonant Fortune on Aetheric Lore Active Resonances when consulting Kallos-Sworn records. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Kallos-Sworn credential seal (your Circle insignia), Kallos-Sworn working clothes, a copy of the founding vow (**"**Never Again**"**), 15 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I know the Kallos-Sworn's methods well enough to see when they're being applied to me. I find unmonitored situations more uncomfortable than dangerous ones. | Never Again means something — the question is whether the institution still does. Institutions fail. The vow doesn't. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| My Starbound Bond partner from field service is still active. We haven't spoken since I left. It's complicated. | I still think in terms of operational security when I should just be honest. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What House were you assigned to — and what was their specific mission?

▸  Did you leave the Kallos-Sworn, or are you still technically active?

▸  What do you know about the Starbound Bond system that bothers you?

**Ceque-Walker**   Wanderer · Elethorn Grid

You've walked the sacred lines of Elethorn — as pilgrimage, duty, or simply because the grid felt like the only honest geography in a dishonest world. Distinct from being Ceque Line Born (which is about biology), the Ceque-Walker origin is about practice: years of deliberate walking, attunement, and the specific wisdom that comes from following a path older than any living civilization.

| **Disciplines:  **Aetheric Lore, Survival | **Tool / Language:  **Cartographer's tools · Ceque notation (partial — functional for recording walks) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Grid Sense (Practiced)** You can feel the presence of Ceque Line nodes within 300 ft — a faint warmth that intensifies near active nodes. You know whether a node is dormant, active, or reactivating with the wrong energy. You have walked at least one partial Ceque Line and carry its temporary attunement — choose one zodiac sign's domain at character creation. Resonant Fortune on Active Resonances in that domain until you complete the full line or the attunement fades (3 months from last walking). You can renew it by walking again. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Cartographer's tools, a personal walking map of Ceque Lines walked so far (added to during play), sturdy traveling boots, 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I trust geography more than people — it doesn't change its mind. I measure distances in walking time and have difficulty converting to any other unit. | The grid was built to hold the world together — walking it is the least I can do. Movement is the most honest form of commitment. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| A Ceque-Keeper showed me a node that was wrong in a way I can't explain. I need to understand what I saw. | I interpret every significant event as cosmically meaningful — which is sometimes correct and often paralyzing. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Which line have you walked most completely — and what did you find at the end?

▸  Grid-Point Seven is reactivating. You felt something change in the lines weeks ago. What was it like?

▸  A Ceque-Keeper has been following your walking route. They haven't made contact yet.

**Waka Navigator**   Wanderer · Deep Ocean

You learned to read the ocean before you learned to read text. The stars were your first language and the current was your first home. Unlike the Navigator-Initiate (who trained in a formal tradition), the Waka Navigator grew up on the water — the tradition is in your body, not your training.

| **Disciplines:  **Perception, Survival | **Tool / Language:  **Navigator's tools · One additional maritime language |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Ocean Reading** Predict weather accurately up to 48 hours in advance through wave pattern, cloud behaviour, and wind quality — no Working required, no roll. Always know geographic position under open sky. On any vessel you crew, travel time is reduced by 20% — your navigation is simply more efficient. The Mirror Sea blocks this ability entirely. The first time you enter the Mirror Sea: Attunement Warding Resonance DC 14 or gain one level of Aetheric Depletion from the disorientation. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Navigator's tools, a lashing kit, sailor's clothes, a small carved wayfinding compass (personal significance, non-Aetheric), 12 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I find deep water calming in a way that confuses people who fear it. I give directions in terms of current and star-line rather than left and right. | The ocean doesn't care about your plans — it cares about your preparation. Every voyage is a promise you make to the water. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| My crew didn't make it back from the last voyage. I was the only one who could navigate us home. That's not something I've made peace with. | I undervalue staying. Some things require you to stop moving — and I haven't learned to tell which things those are. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What voyage fundamentally changed how you understand the world?

▸  The Moana-kin Navigator tradition and your ocean-born instinct — are they the same thing or different things pointing at the same truth?

▸  Something came up from below on your last voyage. You haven't told anyone what you saw.

### **Marked Origins**

**Legendary Beast Witness**   Marked · Zodiac · Rare

You were present at a Legendary Beast encounter — not as a practitioner seeking it, but as a bystander, a child, a traveler in the wrong landscape at the right moment. The Beast looked at you. You survived. You have been different since.

| **Disciplines:  **Nature, Survival | **Tool / Language:  **Herbalist's supplies · Nature Tongue (recognized intent with your Beast's zodiac sign creatures) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Beast Mark** You already qualify for the Zodiac Attunement Feat prerequisite — the witness counts. Additionally: the Beast of your sign does not aggress toward you by default. It will look again before deciding to act — one Pulse of non-aggressive status before any encounter with your sign's Beast begins. The Beast's Emanations recognise your lineage-frequency: Peripheral Emanations treat you as neutral, Resonant Emanations as kin. At the Game Master's discretion, surviving a genuine crisis encounter with your sign's Apex Emanation also qualifies as the prerequisite. Accord-Walkers who take this Origin begin with one Beast Resonance pool at 5 points immediately. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **A physical token of the encounter (Game Master determines based on which Beast), traveler's clothes, a journal entry describing the encounter written at character creation, 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I know what's worth fearing and what isn't — the lists don't always match other people's. I notice large animals before I notice people in the same space. | The Beasts are not monsters. They are the gods we couldn't keep. I survived. That has to mean something. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone else witnessed what I witnessed. We haven't spoken about it. We both know we should. | I hold the cosmic in higher regard than the immediate — which can make the immediate very costly. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Which Beast did you witness, and what were the circumstances?

▸  How did the encounter change you — and does anyone know it happened?

▸  The Accord-Walker tradition will be very interested in you. Are you ready for that attention?

**Quint Bond Adjacent**   Marked · Fate Number · Game Master Assigned

Your Fate Number falls in the 55–58 range. This Origin is assigned by the Game Master, not selected by the player — it reflects a cosmic fact that has always been true. At character creation, player and Game Master agree that this character may be one of the Five Who Remember.

| **Disciplines:  **Insight, one other of the player's choice | **Tool / Language:  **Any one tool of the player's choice · Any one language of the player's choice |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Loom****'****s Weight** Your Fate Number reads differently to Stellar Cartographers — an additional resonance, as if the thread carries more weight. Stellar Cartographers who read your Number are compelled to read it twice. Resonant Fortune on all Warding Resonances against having your Fate Number masked or suppressed. Once per session: a moment of prophetic clarity — a brief, accurate vision of what is about to happen. The Game Master delivers this at a dramatically appropriate moment. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Normal starting equipment for the character's Path. This Origin adds no physical equipment — what it adds has been present since birth.

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I have always felt that the people around me needed something from me specifically — before I understood why. I trust patterns more than explanations. | If the Loom has a design for me, I'd rather know what it is and choose whether to follow it than follow it blind. The Five Who Remember have to choose to remember. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| I have met one of the others — I just don't know it yet. The Game Master knows who. | I carry a sense of cosmic significance that I have done nothing to earn — and I'm never entirely sure whether that's humility or evasion. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Do you know your Fate Number? Most people don't — have you had it read?

▸  Serath of the Closed Circle has identified three of the five. Are you one he knows?

▸  The Ifá prophecy is known to scholars and priests. Have you heard it?

**Orisha-Touched Lineage**   Marked · Ashélands · Spiritual

Your lineage carries a specific Orisha's favour — not the full Ashé-Touched biological expression, but enough that the Orisha occasionally communicates with you in dreams and crisis moments. You may not be from the Ashélands. The Orisha's favour isn't geographically limited.

| **Disciplines:  **Religion (Orisha tradition), Insight | **Tool / Language:  **Musical instrument · Yoruba-derived Ashé liturgical language |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Orisha****'****s Eye** Once per Deep Attunement, your patron Orisha may communicate during a dream or crisis moment — the Game Master delivers one piece of accurate, relevant information from the Orisha's divine perspective. The communication is non-verbal (symbolic, sensory, emotional) and requires interpretation. Additionally: Resonant Fortune on Insight Active Resonances when attempting to understand someone's emotional truth. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **A portable shrine to your patron Orisha, an Orisha-themed personal item (specific color garment, bead string, carved item — varies by Orisha), 15 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I can sense when an Orisha's presence is near — a particular quality of attention in the room. I hold the sacred and the practical at the same level, which unnerves people who keep them separate. | The Orishas are real. Behave accordingly. Devotion that costs nothing is not devotion. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| What has my patron Orisha asked of me that I haven't delivered — and why haven't I? | I sometimes wait for divine guidance when I should simply act. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Which Orisha is your patron, and how did you learn of the connection?

▸  The Ashé-Touched community may have complicated feelings about a non-Ashélands practitioner. How do you navigate this?

▸  What has your patron Orisha asked of you that you haven't delivered?

**Ceque Line Born**   Marked · Precursor Grid

You were born within a Ceque Line node's active range during a period of unusual activity. The Precursor grid's Aetheric frequency expressed itself in your biology at a formative moment. Distinct from the Ceque-Walker (who chose to walk the lines), you carry the grid's calibration in your body — it was never a choice.

| **Disciplines:  **History (Precursor civilization), Aetheric Lore | **Tool / Language:  **Cartographer's tools · Ceque notation (partially deciphered by modern scholars) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Grid Resonance (Innate)** You always know when within 1 mile of an active or reactivating Ceque Line node — a physical pressure in the chest that intensifies closer to the node. You cannot be fooled by false nodes or illusions. Additionally: when walking a Ceque Line (see Mechanics Codex), all effects accumulate twice as fast — 1 Node gives the 3-Node effect; 3 Nodes give the Half-Line effect. The grid recognizes you as a calibrated instrument. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Cartographer's tools, a partially completed Ceque Line map started at character creation and added to during play, 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I occasionally know where I am on an emotional map I can't explain the source of. I am comfortable with ruins in a way that feels like recognition. | The Precursors built something worth understanding. The fact that it destroyed them doesn't change that. What we inherit shapes us — but we decide what to do with the inheritance. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| I can feel Grid-Point Seven differently from how I feel other nodes. Something changed about it recently. I don't know what that means for me. | I privilege the ancient over the immediate in ways that cost me the immediate. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  Grid-Point Seven's reactivation — when did you first feel something wrong?

▸  The Stellar Cartographers of Aetheria have a theory about Ceque Line Born individuals. Are you aware of it?

▸  Your Ceque notation knowledge is partial — who taught you what you know?

**Void-Touched Survivor**   Marked · Exposure · Recovery

You were exposed to something that left a mark on your Fate Number — not enough to make you Void-Touched, but enough that you've felt the Hollow Serpent's attention. You are not corrupted. You are changed. The difference is the most important thing you know.

| **Disciplines:  **Insight, Perception | **Tool / Language:  **Healer's kit (you've needed it) · One language of your choice |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Hollow Resonance** Your exposure left a faint Void-frequency in your Aetheric field. You can sense Lead-Scale Corruption at Tempered stage or higher within 30 ft without a roll — it feels like static at the edge of your awareness. Void-Husks do not automatically attack you — they process your frequency as adjacent to the Coil's before deciding you're not, giving approximately one Pulse of non-hostile time. Additionally: Resonant Fortune on Warding Resonances against Void-Touched Exposure accumulation — you've been there before. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **Healer's kit, dark travelling clothes, a Weep-Stone (1 charge, kept close — old habit), 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I am quieter than I was before — I don't fully know what I left in that place. I trust people who have also been marked more readily than those who haven't. | The thing that marks you doesn't own you. It just lives with you. I survived — that has to mean something, even when I can't say what. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone pulled me out of that place. I would not be here without them. | I sometimes freeze when I should move. The body remembers. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  What was the exposure — and do you know its source?

▸  The Kanya Siddha can purify Void-Touched Exposure residue. Have you sought that treatment?

▸  Your Hollow Resonance makes you slightly recognizable to Coil operatives. Has anyone acted on that recognition?

**Kallos Dreamer**   Marked · Precursor Memory

You dream the Precursor civilization — not histories, not facts, but the texture of a world that died four thousand years ago. You don't know why. The Eldren find it deeply unsettling when they learn of it, which tells you something about what you're accessing.

| **Disciplines:  **Aetheric Lore, Insight | **Tool / Language:  **Calligrapher's supplies · Partial literacy in Precursor script (simple inscriptions, not complex documents) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Dream Archive** Once per week during sleep, you receive a dream from the Precursor era — not a chosen memory, but what the collective unconscious of a dead civilization considers important for you to know right now. The Game Master delivers one accurate historical fact about the Kallos era, the global grid, or the Four Architects. The fact is always relevant to your current situation, though the relevance may not be immediately obvious. This cannot be triggered deliberately — it comes when it comes. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  **A dream journal (extensive, partially in your own notation and partially in partial Precursor script you don't fully understand), calligrapher's supplies, 10 Gold Marks

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I sometimes know things I shouldn't — things from before anyone living was alive. I hold the dead with the same regard I hold the living. Both are real to me. | The dead built this world — we owe them at least the courtesy of understanding what we inherited. Memory is the only form of immortality that matters. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| One of the Four Architects appears in my dreams. I know their name. I don't know what they want from me. | I privilege the past over the present in ways that cost me the present. |

### **Narrative Hooks**

▸  The Eldren treat Kallos Dreamers with a combination of reverence and suspicion. Have you encountered this?

▸  Your dream journal contains a record of the Night of Kallos from a perspective that should be impossible to access. Who knows about this?

▸  One of the Four Architects has started giving you specific instructions rather than memories. When did that change?

### **Resonance Depth 1**

Your Calling — the specific direction within your Path — is chosen at Depth 3, not Depth 1. This is intentional. The first two Depths of play are the character discovering which aspect of their Path resonates most deeply. You should know your options now (they're listed in the Path document), but the choice itself happens through play.

### **The Starting Package**

### **Starting Equipment**

Choose one of your Path's starting packages, then take the equipment listed for your Origin category. You may also take the starting Gold Marks option instead of your Path's package if you prefer to purchase equipment directly.

Package A (grove-tender / ocean-walker): Leather armor or hide armor, a druidic focus (zodiac-aspected carved wooden staff or beast-talisman), an explorer's pack, a healer's kit (10 uses), a herbalism kit, a Beast-Resonance Journal (blank — for recording Legendary Beast observations during play).

Package B (storm-caller / void-walker): Leather armor, a quarterstaff, a druidic focus, a diplomat's pack, a collection of natural materials from three different ecosystems (Game Master determines significance of each).

Package A (Alchemist / Architect): Leather armor, a dagger, an alchemist's kit, a set of artisan's tools (smith's or tinker's by Calling direction), an explorer's pack, an Infusion Ledger (blank), and one starting Tier I Blueprint (mechanical trap or alchemical device — determined with Game Master at Session Zero).

Package B (Armorer / Siege Engineer): Scale mail (self-modified — includes one built-in Infusion agreed with Game Master at Session Zero), a hand crossbow with 20 bolts, a medium shield, armorer's tools, an explorer's pack, an Infusion Ledger.

### **Warrior Path Package**

Primal Jarl · Solar Guard · Oathed Vanguard · Void-Hunter

Package A (front-line): Chain mail or scale mail, a martial weapon of choice, a shield, 5 javelins, an adventurer's pack (bedroll, mess kit, tinderbox, 10 torches, 10 days' rations, waterskin, 50 ft hempen rope). Package B (mobile): Leather armor, two martial weapons, a light crossbow with 20 bolts, an adventurer's pack. Void-Hunter specific addition: A Hunter's Journal (contains notes on one Coil operative's known location — outdated but a starting lead).

### **Weaving Path Package**

Comet-Magus · Star-Born · Zodiac Priest · Stellar Cartographer · Ashé-Medium

Package A (scholar): A quarterstaff, a component pouch, an explorer's pack, a Formulation Ledger (Comet-Magus) or ritual journal (other Paths), a set of robes in your house colors (Kallos-Sworn) or plain traveling clothes (others). Package B (traveler): A dagger, an arcane focus (zodiac-aspected crystal or carved wooden focus), a diplomat's pack, a letter of introduction from a relevant institution (Argent Spire, a Scattered Temple, the Ifá tradition). Ashé-Medium specific addition: A ritual bundle (materials for Orisha Invocation — specific to your patron Orisha, assembled with a priest's guidance).

### **Skilled Path Package**

Fate-Breaker · Resonance Seeker · Rāśi-Siddha

Package A (performer/operative): A rapier or shortsword, a light crossbow with 20 bolts, leather armor, a musical instrument or thieves' tools (based on Path and Calling direction), an entertainer's pack or burglar's pack. Package B (wandering): Two daggers, leather armor, a lute or deck of fortune-telling cards (narrative item), a diplomat's pack. Rāśi-Siddha specific: No weapon required — unarmed strikes are your weapon. Replace weapon with: a meditation mat, a set of prayer beads (Tapas Point tracking aid), and your Temple's traveler's robe.

### **Unique Path Packages**

Coil-Stalker · Geode-Pilot · Scion-Pledged · Fade-Guardian

Coil-Stalker: Dark leather armor, two shortswords, a vial of Siderium Quartz (2 charges — the only thing keeping your gauge in check), a burglar's pack, and a dossier on your current target. Geode-Pilot: Your Resonant Frame (already bonded — it is you), artisan's tools (for Frame maintenance), a navigator's pack, and a letter of introduction from the Jade Empire or the Grand Prime Forgeman (your choice). Scion-Pledged: Any light armor, a weapon of choice, a scholar's pack, and a contract document (sealed — the actual terms are between you and your Patron; the Game Master has seen them). Fade-Guardian: Any armor permitted by your Oath tradition (light, medium, or heavy — your Veil-Walking nature imposes no restriction), a martial weapon, a holy symbol (Otherworld-aspected — a silver branch, a knot-worked disk), a priest's pack.

### **Your Thread in the Loom**

The Loom has woven your cosmic position — your Kindred, your sign, your Fate Number, your Essence. Your Path has named the road. Your Origin has given you a past. What remains is the person at the intersection of all of these.

After all players have rolled their Fate Numbers, compare them as a group. Numbers within 5 points of each other form a natural Paired Bond between those characters. The Game Master tracks whether characters acknowledge this or not — an unacknowledged bond still exists; both characters simply haven't named what they've been feeling.

### **What brings you to this place, at this moment?**

Session Zero

Every character in Sideros begins somewhere specific. A city. A crossroads. A ruin. The Game Master needs to know not just who you are but how you arrived where the story begins. This is not backstory — it is the last step before the first step. Be specific. Be present. Arrive.

### **What do you know about the Ashen Coil?**

World Awareness

Every character knows something — even if it's just rumor, even if it's wrong. The Ashen Coil's existence is an open secret in most regions. What your character has heard, believed, dismissed, or personally experienced will shape how they respond when the Coil becomes directly relevant. Most characters underestimate. Some have been touched by it. One or two may have worked for it. All of these are valid starting positions.

### **Who would notice if you disappeared?**

Connections

Name one person, organization, or creature — real, in the world, with an opinion about your existence. This is not your backstory. This is your thread in the Loom. The Game Master will use this. It will become relevant. The Loom noticed you before you noticed the Loom — and whoever would notice your disappearance is part of the pattern that holds you in the world's weave.

☐  Concept: Three questions answered — want, loss, and Loom's design on you

☐  Kindred: Chosen, traits recorded, Vitality Die noted

☐  Path: Chosen, Depth 1 features recorded, Calling options reviewed

☐  Attributes: Six scores generated (4d6 drop lowest × 6), swap applied, Kindred bonuses added, modifiers calculated

☐  Derived stats: Vitality maximum, Guard Rating, Mastery Bonus (+2), Ambient Attunement calculated

☐  Fate Number: 1d100 rolled and recorded

☐  Primal Essence: 1d6 rolled — Alpha (1), Beta (2–5), or Omega (6)

☐  Zodiac Sign: Chosen or determined by Fate Number

☐  Kindred-Zodiac Resonance: Bonus ability established with Game Master at Session Zero — 240 combinations across twenty Kindreds and twelve signs; the Game Master improvises based on the thematic intersection of your Kindred's Aetheric nature and your sign's domain. No master table exists; this is a Session Zero conversation.

☐  Origin: Chosen, two Disciplines Mastered, tool or language recorded, Origin Ability recorded

☐  Flavor: One personality trait, one ideal, one bond, one flaw selected or written

☐  Equipment: Starting package selected, Origin equipment bonus added

☐  Languages: All languages recorded (Common + Kindred language + Origin language if applicable)

☐  Name and appearance: Something worth saying aloud at the table

### **Character Advancement**

Characters grow through Resonance Depths -- the Sideros equivalent of character levels. Depth 1 is where every character begins. Depth 20 is the standard capstone. Some Paths (notably Zodiac Priest) extend into an Epic Tier beyond Depth 20.

### **Advancement Methods**

| **Method** | **How It Works** |
| --- | --- |
| **Milestone (Recommended)** | The Game Master decides when the party advances based on story events, session accomplishments, and narrative momentum. Typically 2-4 sessions per Depth in the early game, lengthening as Depths increase. Milestone advancement is the default in Sideros -- it keeps advancement tied to narrative significance rather than encounter count. |
| **Experience Points (Variant)** | The Game Master awards XP for encounters, exploration, and story events. XP thresholds: 300 (Depth 2) · 900 (D3) · 2,700 (D4) · 6,500 (D5) · 14,000 (D6) · 23,000 (D7) · 34,000 (D8) · 48,000 (D9) · 64,000 (D10) · 85,000 (D11) · 100,000 (D12) · 120,000 (D13) · 140,000 (D14) · 165,000 (D15) · 195,000 (D16) · 225,000 (D17) · 265,000 (D18) · 305,000 (D19) · 355,000 (D20). |
| **Bond-Milestone (Variant)** | Depth advances when significant Fated Bond thresholds are crossed and acknowledged. One character's bond acknowledgement can trigger advancement for the whole party. Best for campaigns centred on the Quint Bond narrative. |

### **What Happens When You Advance**

| **At Every New Depth** | **At Specific Depths** |
| --- | --- |
| Roll your Vitality Die and add your Endurance modifier (minimum 1). Add this to your Vitality maximum. Always use the HIGHER of your Kindred's or Path's Vitality Die. | Depth 3: Choose your Calling -- the specific direction within your Path that defines long-term development. |
| Apply any new Path features listed in your depth progression table. | Depth 4: Attribute Score Improvement (increase two attributes by 1, or one by 2, max 20). Also: Zodiac Attunement becomes available after your Legendary Beast encounter. |
| Your Mastery Bonus increases at Depths 5, 9, 13, and 17 (from +2 up to +6 by Depth 17). This automatically increases every Mastered Discipline, attack roll, and Warding Resonance that uses it. | Depths 8, 12, 16, 19: Additional Attribute Score Improvements. At these Depths you may take a General Feat instead of the ASI. |

### **Four Tiers of Play**

| **Depths** | **Tier** | **Character in the World** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **1-4** | **The Awakening** | The Loom has noticed you. Your Path is new -- you are learning what you are capable of. Threats are local: Coil operations in a single city, a Void-Husk outbreak in a region, the first signs of political manipulation in a zodiac institution. You are one of the interesting people in a district. |
| **5-10** | **The Rising** | The Coil begins to take an active interest. You have survived long enough to know things you were not supposed to know. You can affect the outcome of city-level conflicts and Conclave-level politics. Your Fated Bond may be approaching Triad tier. You are one of the significant people in a province. |
| **11-16** | **The Sovereign** | You operate at a level that shapes political reality. The Coil tracks you directly -- Drava Nullsong has your file personally. You can challenge institutions. Your Fated Bond may be approaching Quad tier. You are one of the important people in a nation. |
| **17-20** | **The Legendary** | You are a force comparable to Legendary Beasts. Aethar knows you exist. If the Quint Bond is forming, it is near completion. You can affect world-level events. You may be one of five people who can stop what is coming -- or the reason it cannot be stopped. |

### **Cross-Path Training (Multiclassing Equivalent)**

| **Optional Rule** Cross-Path Training is the Sideros equivalent of multiclassing. It is more narratively costly than in D**&**D -- the lore positions each Path as a distinct relationship with the Aether that changes the soul. Consult your Game Master before undertaking this. |
| --- |

After Depth 5 in your primary Path, you may begin studying a secondary Path under a qualified teacher. Requirements: the primary Attribute for the secondary Path must be 13 or higher. Cost: 250 gm + 250 days of dedicated study with a practitioner of the secondary Path at Depth 8 or higher. Benefit: access to that Path's Depth 1 features only. You do not advance in Depth in the secondary Path separately -- your single Depth represents the depth of your combined practice.

**SESSION ZERO**

The First Meeting — Before Your Campaign Begins

## **Session Zero**

Session Zero is a pre-campaign meeting — not the first session of the story, but the session that makes the story possible. No combat. No dice. Characters meet each other, the table agrees on how the campaign will run, and the Game Master establishes everything that makes Session One land properly. It runs roughly 2.5 to 3 hours.

Your safety survey responses have been collected and compiled. The Game Master has run your Fate Numbers. The session works through a structured agenda. You do not need to have your character completely figured out — Session Zero often changes things. That is the point.

**A note before you arrive.** Your character's zodiac is not their belief. It is the cosmic fact they were born inside. The Solar Throne's mandate, the Loom's weaving, the Orishas' Ashé, the ancestor-spirits' guidance — these are not theologies competing for adherents. They are true, each within their territorial reach, and they are incompatible. Other cultures will treat your character's truth as wrong. They are not lying. They are inside a different truth. Holding this clearly is half of what makes Sideros play feel like Sideros.

### **Before You Arrive — Player Checklist**

| **□** | **Character creation complete:** Steps I through IX finished, character sheet filled out |
| --- | --- |
| **□** | **Safety survey submitted:** Game Master's Google Form completed and submitted before the session |
| **□** | **Fate Number, Primal Essence, and Zodiac Sign recorded:** these will be shared with the table at Session Zero |
| **□** | **Three Narrative Hooks written:** the hooks from your Origin's narrative questions — bring them to share |
| **□** | **Step I questions answered:** what your character wants, what they have lost, and what the Loom wants with them |
| **□** | **Arrival scenario considered:** what brings your character to the campaign's starting location at this exact moment |
| **□** | **Coil knowledge position decided:** what does your character know, believe, or have heard about the Ashen Coil? |
| **□** | **Party connection preference considered:** do you want to start knowing the other characters, or arrive as strangers? |
| **□** | **Calling direction thought through:** which Calling direction feels most like who this person is becoming? |
| **□** | **One person who would notice your disappearance:** a specific name, organisation, or creature the Game Master can use |
| **□** | **Platform setup confirmed:** voice/video channel tested, VTT access confirmed if applicable |
| **□** | **One question for the Game Master:** something about the world, the system, or the campaign you want answered before Session One |

## **Session Zero Agenda**

| **1** | **Safety Survey Review****   15-20 min** The Game Master shares aggregate results. Confirmed Lines read aloud — no discussion, just acknowledgment. Active safety tools introduced and explained.   • Every Line is confirmed understood by everyone at the table    • Safety tools selected — X-Card, Script Change, Open Door, Post-Session Check-In |
| --- | --- |
| **2** | **Character Introductions****   20-30 min** Each player introduces their character briefly: name, Kindred, Path, and one sentence on who this person is right now. One Narrative Hook shared with the table.   • Brief Primal Essence acknowledgment — each player names their Essence and how they expect to play it    • Multiple Alpha players discuss momentum; Omega players confirm comfort with NPC deference |
| **3** | **Fate Number Reveal****   10-15 min** All players reveal their Fate Numbers simultaneously. The Game Master announces Bond clusters. Void-Touched Numbers (13, 66, 99) handled sensitively.   • Numbers within 5 points: natural Paired Bond between those characters    • Bond cluster protocol: acknowledged, unacknowledged, or held for a story moment    • Quint Bond potential (all 5 within 1 point): extraordinary — the Game Master will address this privately |
| **4** | **Kindred-Zodiac Resonance****   15-20 min** The Game Master works with each player to establish their unique Kindred-Zodiac Resonance ability. No master table — this is a conversation about the intersection of your Kindred's nature and your sign's domain. 240 possible combinations; each is original. Record it on your sheet. |
| **5** | **Party Connections****   15-20 min** The table decides how the PCs know each other — or whether they start as strangers. Bond relationships between PCs are discussed and the recognition style agreed. |
| **6** | **World Context Calibration****   10-15 min** The Game Master shares what each character would know about the current world state. Coil knowledge calibrated per character. No spoilers — just what is realistic. |
| **7** | **Campaign Agreements****   10-15 min** Scheduling, absence policy, pacing preference, and between-session engagement confirmed for the whole table. |
| **8** | **Opening Scene of Session One****   5-10 min** The Game Master delivers the opening image of Session One: where the characters are, what they can see, and what is already happening when the story begins. This is not Session One — it is Session One's last piece of preparation. |

### **Things to Know**

**Session Zero is not Session One.** No combat, probably no dice. It is a conversation, not gameplay. Working correctly means the agenda runs cleanly.

**Your character may change after this session.** The Fate Number reveal and the Resonance conversation often reframe things. Revision after Session Zero is expected and normal. The Game Master sets the cutoff: typically 48 hours before Session One.

**Lines established here are permanent.** If something was marked as a Line in the safety survey, it does not return for renegotiation. Not mid-campaign, not in a specific scene. A Line is a Line.

**The Game Master holds world canon.** Questions about the world are answered by the Game Master. Your character's story is yours. The world's lore, history, and mechanics are the Game Master's domain.

**After Session Zero:** Update your character sheet with your Kindred-Zodiac Resonance ability. Note any Bond relationships established. Confirm your arrival scenario with the Game Master if it was modified. The next time you meet is Session One.

