### **Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Frequency Mastery** | Depth 2 | The Resonance Seeker becomes Mastered in any Discipline after observing an expert use it once in their presence — they don't learn the skill, they harmonize with the frequency of someone who already has it. This Mastery lasts until the next Deep Attunement, at which point it either deepens into permanent Half-Mastery or fades entirely (player's choice whether to maintain through continued contact with that expert). |
| **Countersong** | Depth 6 | When a creature within 60 ft is targeted by a Working that relies on sound or spoken language, the Resonance Seeker may use their Reflex to produce a countering frequency. The targeted creature has Resonant Fortune on their Warding Resonance against that Working. This covers Soul-Swayed (Charm) effects, Dread-Struck triggered by spoken compulsion, and any Working with a verbal component. Against Auroran communication being disrupted: Countersong doubles in effectiveness — the Seeker can temporarily stabilize an Auroran's frequency in an Aether-Dampening field. |
| **Harmonic Resonance Field** | Depth 14 | The Resonance Seeker's mastery reaches a point where their presence itself harmonizes the Aetheric field around them. All allies within 30 ft may add the Seeker's Resonance modifier to their Warding Resonances against Dread-Struck, Soul-Swayed, and Resonance-Shattered conditions. This is passive, permanent, and does not require Sustained Resonance. Additionally: all Bonded allies within 30 ft have Resonant Fortune on rolls to use their Bond abilities — the Seeker's harmonic field amplifies the Bond's existing resonance. |

### **Callings**

**The Lore-Keeper**  —  Scholar-Performer

**Cutting Frequency (Depth 3):  **Once per Pulse, when a creature within 60 ft makes an Active Resonance or Strike Resonance, you may use your Reflex to impose Resonant Discord on that roll — you've identified and broadcast the dissonant frequency in their technique.

**Frequency Archive (Depth 6):  **You retain the harmonic impression of every Working you have witnessed — you know the frequency and can reproduce it as a Working of equivalent tier, once, before the impression fades. This is not learning the Working; it is mimicking the frequency one time.

**Lore Mastery (Depth 14):  **Mastered in all knowledge Disciplines (Aetheric Lore, History, Nature). You are the walking record of the world's frequencies. When you recite knowledge relevant to the current situation, all allies who hear you have Resonant Fortune on their next relevant Active Resonance.

**The Valor-Singer**  —  Combat-Performer

**Battle Chord (Depth 3):  **You may use Resonant Chords in combat without sacrificing your Act. Chords granted as Instinct during combat persist through the entire encounter rather than expiring in 10 minutes.

**Armor of Frequencies (Depth 6):  **While you can hear and speak, your Resonance Seeker Workings that require Sustained Resonance do not break when you take damage — the frequency holds because your body reinforces it in real time.

**Combat Inspiration (Depth 14):  **Creatures who use your Resonant Chord on a Strike Resonance may add the die result to the damage roll as well as the attack roll — the Chord amplifies the entire strike, not just the aim.

**The Bond-Harmonist**  —  Fated Bond Specialist

**Bond Sight (Depth 3):  **You perceive Fated Bonds as visible threads of light between Bonded individuals — always active, no Instinct required. You see tier, health, and whether the bond is acknowledged, same as the Stellar Cartographer's Bond Cartography but without reading Fate Numbers.

**Bond Amplification (Depth 6):  **Once per Deep Attunement, by performing 10 minutes of focused harmonic work directed at a Bonded pair or group, you amplify their Bond for 24 hours: all Bond abilities operate at one tier higher than their current tier. The harmony you create supplements the existing resonance.

**Resonant Weaving (Depth 14):  **You may attempt to introduce two unBonded individuals whose Fate Numbers are within range to each other — facilitating a Paired Bond formation as a 1-hour ritual. Both individuals must be present and willing. The Loom decides whether the bond takes; your work creates the conditions but cannot force the recognition. Both individuals make an Attunement Warding Resonance (Threshold 14) with Resonant Fortune; success on both completes the bond.

