| **Seasonal Power** | Depth 3 | The Fade-Guardian's connection to the Tuathan Otherworld tradition aligns them with the Celtic Tree Zodiac. Their Oath powers are enhanced during their birth-tree's season: both Aetheric Benediction uses recharge at sunrise during the season; Veil Walk duration doubles; Veil Smite deals +1d8 additional damage. Outside their season, one Aetheric Benediction use per Deep Attunement instead of two. At solstices and equinoxes: both effects (seasonal and off-season) become available simultaneously for 24 hours. |
| **Otherworld Sight** | Depth 7 | The Fade-Guardian no longer needs to Veil Walk to perceive Otherworld entities — they always see the full spectrum of both worlds simultaneously. This grants: automatic detection of Fae-Blooded Kindred using their Twilight Step; awareness of active Otherworld incursions (something crossing the Veil) within 300 ft; the ability to communicate with Otherworld entities without entering the Otherworld. The cost: the Guardian occasionally experiences intrusive Otherworld sensory overlaps — the Game Master describes these as narrative flavor during moments of stress or significance. |
| **Veil Seal** | Depth 15 | Once per week, the Fade-Guardian may permanently seal a specific Otherworld threshold — a Faerie Mound, a Fade-Bleed zone boundary, or a known crossing point. The seal lasts for one year and one day (a traditional Tuathan binding period), after which it must be renewed. While sealed: no entity may cross the threshold in either direction without the Guardian's explicit permission. A sealed threshold registers on Fae-Blooded perception as an unnatural absence — they feel the doorway and cannot open it. |
| **Oath Working List** | Depths 3–17 | Depths 3–9 Depth 3: Speak with Animals, Faerie FireDepth 5: Moonbeam, Pass without TraceDepth 9: Conjure Animals, Plant Growth Depths 13–17 Depth 13: Guardian of Faith, Hallucinatory TerrainDepth 17: Tree Stride, Commune with Nature |

The Fade-Guardian is an Oathed Vanguard Calling (Oath of the Fading Veil) with no sub-Callings. Its complete powers are defined by its Oath Features listed above and the Oathed Vanguard depth progression.

### **Solar Guard**

Base: Fighter · Alpha/Beta-aspected · Vitality Die: d10

**Core Mechanic:  **Surge of Will (replaces Second Wind + Action Surge)  Vitality Surge (Instinct, 1/Short or Deep Attunement): Restore Vitality equal to 1d10 + Resonance Depth. This is not magical healing — it is trained stress response. Works in anti-magic fields. Works in The Stillness. Will does not require the Aether. Combat Surge (Act, 2/Short or Deep Attunement — increases at higher Depths): On your Moment, you may take one additional Act. Not an Instinct — a full additional Act. Replaces Action Surge. A Solar Guard in Combat Surge can: attack twice and use an Instinct and still have an Act remaining. This represents trained efficiency reaching a point of genuine superhuman performance without cosmic aid. Fighting Discipline (chosen at Depth 1): Select one fighting tradition — Archery, Defense, Dueling

