### **Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Tactical Reading** | Depth 3 | The Solar Guard has studied combat long enough to read it. At the start of each encounter, they may use their first Instinct to assess all hostile creatures within 60 ft — learning each creature's approximate Vitality (full/bloodied/near death), primary attack method (melee/ranged/magical), and one tactical vulnerability (a specific positioning weakness or a condition they have not yet resisted this encounter). This is observation, not magic. It cannot be suppressed. |
| **Extra Strikes** | Depth 5, 11, 20 | When the Solar Guard uses the Strike Act, they may make two Strike Resonances instead of one (Depth 5). This increases to three at Depth 11 and four at Depth 20. The Solar Guard is the Path with the highest raw strike volume — not because of cosmic power, but because they have trained every day since they could hold a weapon and they have simply gotten very, very good at this. |
| **Indomitable** | Depth 9 | Once per Deep Attunement, when the Solar Guard fails a Warding Resonance, they may reroll it with Resonant Fortune. The reroll must be used. At Depth 13: twice per Deep Attunement. At Depth 17: three times. This is not cosmic resilience — it is the refusal of a trained warrior to accept what just happened to them. A Solar Guard who has failed a save looks at the result and decides it is unacceptable. |

### **Callings**

**Solar Chivalry**  —  Leonine Tradition

**Chivalric Precision (Depth 3):  **Once per Pulse, add your Mastery Bonus to one damage roll after seeing the Strike Resonance result.

**Know Your Enemy (Depth 7):  **After observing a creature for 1 minute, or after one combat encounter with it, you know its exact current Vitality, all resistances and immunities, and its Primal Essence.

**Relentless (Depth 10):  **When you are reduced to 0 Vitality but not killed outright, you may make one Strike Resonance before falling. The Solar Chivalry's code requires one last act of defiance.

**Psi-Warrior**  —  Jade Tradition

**Psionic Strike (Depth 3):  **Once per Pulse, when you hit with a Strike Resonance, add 1d6 psychic damage. The Jade Empire's warrior tradition trains the mind as a weapon.

**Telekinetic Movement (Depth 7):  **Move one object or creature within 30 ft up to 30 ft as an Instinct. Creatures make a Forcefulness Warding Resonance (Threshold = 8 + Mastery + Attunement) to resist.

**Bulwark of Force (Depth 10):  **Once per Deep Attunement, create an invisible barrier of psychic force within 30 ft — a 10-ft cube that blocks all movement through it for 1 minute.

**Runic Knight**  —  Norse Tradition

**Rune Carving (Depth 3):  **Learn two runes from the Elder Futhark tradition. Each rune may be inscribed on one weapon or piece of armor per Deep Attunement, granting a specific passive benefit (Cloud: Resonant Fortune on Swiftness; Stone: +2 Guard Rating; Fire: +1d6 fire on strikes; Frost: Warding Resonance immunity to cold).

**Giant****'****s Might (Depth 7):  **As an Instinct, grow to Large size for 1 minute. Gain Resonant Fortune on Forcefulness Active Resonances, +1d6 damage, and can grapple creatures up to Huge size.

**Runic Shield (Depth 10):  **When an ally within 60 ft is hit by a Strike Resonance, use your Reflex to impose Resonant Discord on that roll — the runes extend their protection through the warrior's will.

### **Rāśi-Siddha**

Base: Monk · Omega-aspected · Vitality Die: d8 · Most complete Path

**Core Mechanic:  **Tapas Points (fully defined in Mechanics Codex)  Pool = Mastery Bonus × Attunement modifier (minimum 2). Three expenditure tiers: Satvic (purification, lower cost), Rajasic (active, standard cost), Tamasic (corrupting, higher cost, Tapas Depletion risk). Regeneration: full on Deep Attunement; partial on meditative Brief Attunement. Unarmored Guard Rating: 10 + Attunement modifier + Mastery Bonus while at full Tapas pool (Ascetic Stillness ability). Without a full pool: 10 + Attunement modifier + Swiftness modifier. Siddha Strike: Unarmed strikes count as Aetheric Artifacts for the purpose of overcoming damage resistance — the mantra in the body makes the fist a Working. Unarmed damage: 1d6 at Depths 1–4; 1d8 at 5–10; 1d10 at 11–16; 1d12 at 17+.  The Rāśi-Siddha is the most complete Path in

