### **Callings**

**Mesha Temple (♈ Aries)**  —  Initiative

**First Breath (Depth 3):  **You always act first in the first Pulse of any encounter, regardless of Pulse Order — no roll required.

**Blazing Mantra (Depth 6):  **Your Mantra Strike deals fire damage and sets the target ablaze (1d4 fire at start of their Moment) for 1 minute unless they spend their Act extinguishing it. Fire cost: 1 additional Tapas (Rajasic).

**Surge Form (Depth 11):  **Once per encounter, as a free action after reducing a creature to 0 Vitality, immediately move up to your full speed and make one additional Mantra Strike. No Tapas cost — the momentum is free.

**Kanya Temple (♍ Virgo)**  —  Purification

**Blight-Rot Cure (Depth 3):  **Spend 3 Tapas (Satvic — never Tamasic) to cure Ashen Coil blight-rot on a touched creature. The only non-Lotus cure in the world.

**Purifying Strike (Depth 6):  **Your Mantra Strike removes one condition (Corrupted, Soul-Swayed, or Dread-Struck) from the target on a hit in addition to dealing damage. The Purification touch is weapon and medicine simultaneously.

**Community Shield (Depth 11):  **Passive. All allies within 30 ft have Resonant Fortune on Warding Resonances against Corrupted and disease conditions while you have 4+ Tapas remaining.

**Vrishchika Temple (♏ Scorpio)**  —  Shadow

**Shadow Step (Depth 3):  **Spend 1 Tapas (Rajasic) to teleport from one area of dim light or darkness to another within 60 ft as an Instinct.

**Shroud of Night (Depth 6):  **Spend 2 Tapas to wrap yourself in shadow for 1 minute — Stealth Active Resonances have Resonant Fortune; dim-light conditions count as darkness for you.

**Death Touch (Depth 11):  **Spend 4 Tapas (Tamasic — risk of Depletion). On a successful unarmed strike: target makes an Endurance Warding Resonance (Threshold = 8 + Mastery + Attunement) or drops to 0 Vitality immediately. On success: takes 4d10 necrotic damage instead. One use per encounter.

**Tula Temple (♎ Libra)**  —  Balance

**Deflecting Palm (Depth 3):  **When you are hit by a Strike Resonance, spend 2 Tapas (Satvic) as a Reflex to deflect — reduce damage by 1d10 + Attunement modifier.

**Balanced Form (Depth 6):  **While your Tapas pool is exactly at half its maximum (not above, not below), all your Active Resonances and Warding Resonances have Resonant Fortune. The balance point is power.

**Redirect (Depth 11):  **When you successfully deflect a missile attack to 0 damage (using Deflecting Palm), spend 1 additional Tapas to redirect it at any creature within range — using your own Strike Resonance modifier.

### **Oathed Vanguard**

Oathed Vanguard · Alpha-aspected · Vitality Die: d10

**Core Mechanic:  **Vitality of the Oath + Aether Smite  Vitality of the Oath: A pool of healing equal to 5 × Resonance Depth, refreshed each Deep Attunement. As an Act, touch a creature and restore any amount of Vitality from this pool. Also use pool to cure disease or poison (5 points per condition). The pool represents the Oath's living power — the cosmic force backing the Vanguard's commitment, expressing as healing through their hands. Aether Smite: When a Strike Resonance hits, expend one Aetheric Channel to add radiant damage: 2d8 per Channel tier, +1d8 against Void-Husks and creatures with dissolved Fate Numbers, +1d8 against creatures the Vanguard's Oath designates as enemies. The smite cannot be used retroactively — it must be declared before the roll

