### **Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Zodiac Surge Points** | All Depths | Surge Point pool = Resonance Depth. Refresh on Deep Attunement. Spend 1 point: Quicken a Working (cast as Instinct). Spend 2: Empower (roll damage twice, keep higher). Spend 3: Extend duration. Channels also restore 2/tier on Brief Attunement for tiers 1–5. |
| **Wild Surge** | Natural 1 or deliberate push | When the Star-Born rolls a natural 1 on a Working Strike Resonance, or pushes Channel capacity beyond safe limit, roll on the Wild Surge table. Effects range from minor (wrong target) to dramatic (doubled area/power) to dangerous (adjacent creatures take damage). Cannot fully suppress. At Depth 14, may attempt to shape Surges. |
| **Innate Working Progression** | D1/3/5/7/9/11 | D1: Light, Dancing Lights (Ambient), Cure Wounds, Faerie Fire · D3: Calm Emotions, Moonbeam · D5: Aura of Purity, Daylight · D7: Greater Invisibility, Guardian of Faith · D9: Commune, Mass Cure Wounds · D11: Sunbeam (6th tier) |

### **Callings**

**Zodiac Bloodline**  —  Inherited Power

**Sign Surge (Depth 1):  **All Workings you cast deal their primary damage type as your sign's domain type instead (if it changes the damage type — a Scorpio Star-Born's fire Working becomes necrotic/poison). The sign's energy overwrites the Working's base expression.

**Elemental Affinity (Depth 6):  **Add your Weaving Attribute modifier to damage rolls for any Working dealing your sign's domain damage type. Additionally, spend 1 Surge Point after a Working is cast to gain resistance to that damage type for 1 hour.

**Dragon Wings variant (Depth 14):  **Spend 3 Surge Points to manifest your sign's domain energy as flight for 1 hour. Aries: fire-jet propulsion (50 ft fly, fire trail). Scorpio: shadow-wings (40 ft fly, Aether-Veiled while flying). Each sign manifests differently.

**Wild Surge Master**  —  Chaos Channeler

**Surge Control (Depth 1):  **When a Wild Surge occurs, you may spend 2 Surge Points to select the result from the top 3 options on the Game Master's roll rather than taking the worst. You can't stop the surge but you can shape what it becomes.

**Bend Luck (Depth 6):  **Spend 2 Surge Points as a Reflex when any creature within 30 ft makes a roll — add or subtract 1d4 from the result. The Star-Born's inherent probability-warping nature can push fate in small ways constantly.

**Controlled Chaos (Depth 14):  **Once per Deep Attunement, deliberately trigger a Wild Surge — choosing the result rather than rolling. The Game Master offers three options appropriate to the current situation. The Star-Born selects one.

**The Veil-Touched**  —  Shadow Magic

**Eyes of the Dark (Depth 1):  **Darkvision 120 ft. Additionally, cast a specific darkness Working once per Deep Attunement without expending a Channel or Surge Points — the darkness that flows through your lineage always has a reserve.

**Strength of the Grave (Depth 6):  **When damage would reduce you to 0 Vitality, make an Endurance Warding Resonance (Threshold = 5 + damage dealt). On success: drop to 1 Vitality instead. Cannot use against radiant damage or Resonant Strikes. The Veil-Touched lineage resists death specifically because death is not quite foreign to them.

**Umbral Form (Depth 14):  **Spend 3 Surge Points to become shadow-substance for 1 minute: resistance to all non-radiant damage; move through creatures without impediment; become fully Aether-Veiled in dim light or darkness. The Star-Born's lineage briefly reasserts its Otherworld nature.

### **Scion-Pledged**

Scion-Pledged · Omega-aspected · Vitality Die: d8

**Core Mechanic:  **Patron Channels (replaces Warlock Aetheric Channels) + Scion Boons (replaces Eldritch Invocations)  Patron Channels: The Scion-Pledged has 1–4 Patron Channels (number increases with Resonance Depth), always of the maximum tier available to them. These refresh on Brief Attunement — the Patron replenishes what it has leant. The Patron owns the power. The Pledged borrows it. Missing a Brief Attunement refresh: the Patron notices. Three missed refreshes: the Patron sends a representative to inquire about their investment. Patron's Mark (replaces Eldritch Blast): A ranged Working (120 ft, no Channel cost) dealing 1d10 damage of the Patron's energy type. Scales with Resonance Depth. This is the Patron's direct expression through the Pledged — it works as long as the contract holds. Scion Boons:

