### **Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Patron Channels** | All Depths | 1–4 Patron Channels always of maximum available tier; refresh on Brief Attunement. The Patron owns the power — three missed refreshes prompts a Patron representative to investigate. |
| **Patron****'****s Mark** | Depth 1 | One free ranged Working from the Patron's list, usable at will (no Channel cost). The Mark is the Patron's investment — its scope is determined by which Patron was chosen. |
| **Scion Boons** | Depths 2,5,7,9,12,15,18 | Permanent abilities granted by deepening the contract. Boon list is specific to each Patron (Legendary Beast Pact / Scion Pact / Aethar Pact). Each Boon deepens the Patron's hold — the contract is legally binding at the cosmic level. |

### **Callings**

**The Legendary Beast Pact**  —  Fey/Celestial equivalent

The Patron: One of the twelve Legendary Beasts — the fallen gods themselves. This is the rarest and most dangerous Patron, because the Beast does not understand contracts. It responded to something in the Pledged's nature. The relationship is instinctual, not negotiated. The Beast may withdraw at any time.

**Beast Mark (Depth 1):  **The Patron's Mark deals radiant or force damage (Pledged's choice per use). The Patron's energy is divine, even degraded. Once per encounter, when you use the Patron's Mark, the Beast's Aetheric presence briefly manifests — creatures within 30 ft must make a Resonance Warding Resonance (Threshold 14) or be Dread-Struck for 1 Pulse.

Sample Boons: Legendary Beast Resistance (resistance to the Beast's domain damage type); Companion Spirit (a small manifestation of the Beast as a familiar); Vitality Transfer (spend 1d6 Vitality to restore equal Vitality to an ally).

The risk: If the Pledged ever acts directly against the Legendary Beast's nature — hunting it, harming creatures it protects, acting against its domain's values — the contract suspends. No power until the Pledged makes amends in a way the Beast recognizes.

**The Scion Pact**  —  Fiend equivalent

The Patron: One of the thirteen Scions of the Ashen Coil — a zodiac-sign-corrupted Coil commander. Each Scion offers power derived from Void-energy corrupted through their sign's domain. This is not necessarily a villainous choice — some Scion-Pledged are infiltrators, some are desperate, some genuinely believe the Coil's vision of controlled dissolution.

**Void Mark (Depth 1):  **The Patron's Mark deals necrotic damage. Once per encounter, on a hit, the target must make an Endurance Warding Resonance (Threshold = 8 + Mastery + Weaving Attribute) or gain one Void-Touched Exposure. The Scion is slowly corrupting everything the Pledged touches.

Sample Boons: Dark One's Blessing (when reducing a creature to 0 Vitality, gain temporary Vitality equal to Weaving Attribute modifier + Resonance Depth); Corruption Tolerance (Lead-Scale Corruption Gauge reduced by 2 per encounter, compatible with Coil-Stalker multiclassing); Voice of the Scion (advantage on Resonance Active Resonances when using the Scion's name as authority).

The risk: The Scion monitors the Pledged. Any significant action against the Ashen Coil is noticed. At three significant anti-Coil actions, the Scion withdraws the contract and sends the Fang of the Whisper.

**The Aethar Pact**  —  Great Old One equivalent

The Patron: Aethar the Serpent Bearer himself — the fractured tactical mind of Ophiuchus, former 12th Circle Comet-Magus, the primary villain. This Patron does not offer power out of mutual benefit. It offers power because a Pledged who carries Aethar's mark is a tool, a probe, and eventually a vulnerability in the heroes' party. The Game Master should discuss this Calling carefully with any player who chooses it.

**Void Core Mark (Depth 1):  **The Patron's Mark deals void damage (bypasses all resistances except divine immunity). Once per session, Aethar may communicate directly through the Pledged — a message, a vision, or a compulsion the Pledged may resist (Attunement Warding Resonance, Threshold 20).

Sample Boons: Awakened Mind (telepathy within 30 ft); Entropic Ward (resistance to one damage type that changes each Deep Attunement — Aethar chooses which); Far Scrying (Aethar can observe through the Pledged's senses at will — the Pledged always knows when this is happening, but cannot stop it).

The risk: Everything. Aethar knows everything the Pledged learns. He is patient and he has a plan. The Pledged is part of it.

