### **Callings**

**Conclave of Shifting Horizons**  —  Celestial Observation

**Zodiac Formulation (Depth 2):  **All Formulations dealing your zodiac sign's domain damage deal +1d6 additional damage and have +1 to their Working Threshold. The Conclave trains extensively in celestial alignment — a Mage who has studied their own sign deeply channels it more effectively.

**Portent (Depth 6):  **After a Deep Attunement, roll two d20s and record the results. Once per day each, replace any Active Resonance, Strike Resonance, or Warding Resonance made by any creature you can see with one of these recorded rolls. The Shifting Horizons tradition reads fate lines and applies them deliberately.

**12th Circle Aspirant (Depth 14):  **You have been identified by the Conclave as a candidate for 12th Circle advancement — the same designation Aethar held. Your Ledger is now accessible to the full Conclave library. Once per Deep Attunement, prepare one Working from the Conclave's restricted collection (Game Master selects three options; you choose one).

**Conclave of the Earthly Core**  —  Material Resonance

**Material Mastery (Depth 2):  **Transmutation and material-alteration Formulations cost 1 fewer Channel tier (minimum 1st). Additionally, you may cast one transmutation Formulation per Deep Attunement without expending a Channel — the Earthly Core's power is the domain you have most deeply internalized.

**Stone****'****s Endurance (Depth 6):  **As an Instinct, gain resistance to one damage type until the start of your next Moment — the Mage draws on material-resonance to briefly align with the struck element. Once per Brief Attunement.

**Master Transmuter (Depth 14):  **Once per Deep Attunement, perform one of the following without Channel cost: cure all diseases and neutralize all poisons; restore 2d10 × 10 Vitality; restore life to a creature that died within the last hour; temporarily convert one non-precious material to a precious one (duration: 1 hour).

**Conclave of the Veil-Walkers**  —  Threshold Magic

**Veil Research (Depth 2):  **You have Mastery in all knowledge Active Resonances related to Otherworld entities, Fae-Blooded phenomena, and the boundary between material and spiritual reality. Divination Formulations you cast have doubled duration and +2 Working Threshold.

**Third Eye (Depth 6):  **Once per Deep Attunement, spend 8 hours in meditation to gain one of the following lasting 24 hours: Darkvision 60 ft; see invisible creatures; see the Otherworld simultaneously with the material world; read thoughts of creatures within 30 ft (they make Attunement Warding Resonance Threshold 16 to resist).

**Veil Mastery (Depth 14):  **Illusion and conjuration Formulations cannot be disbelieved — creatures that succeed on Warding Resonances against them see through them visually but still experience their effects physically. Reality and perception are different things. You have made them more different.

### **Stellar Cartographer**

**Core Mechanic:  **A Stellar Cartographer does not predict the future. They read the Loom's current threading and act on what they find there — storing the moments when fate swings wildly (the natural 20, the catastrophic 1) and redirecting that stored probability where it is needed most. Where other Paths weave cosmic force outward, the Stellar Cartographer channels it through time — saving a moment of fate from one instant and spending it in another. The Loom of Fate named itself after what Stellar Cartographers do. The faction appropriated the metaphor. The Path predates them by centuries.  Stellar Cartographers are also, practically, the world's most reliable intelligence gatherers on Fated Bonds. Their ability to read Fate Numbers as a Instinct makes them the character who walks into a room and immediat

## **Depth Progression**

