### **Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Fate Number Reading** | — | As an Instinct, the Stellar Cartographer may read the Fate Number of any creature they can see within 30 feet. They learn: the exact Fate Number, the creature's Primal Essence (Alpha/Beta/Omega), and whether any active Fated Bond connection exists. They do not automatically learn who the bond connects to — that requires the creature to be within sight simultaneously. Void-Touched Numbers (13, 66, 99) are immediately apparent — they register differently from all other Numbers, like a note played in the wrong octave. A Void-Touched character's Number reads correctly, but the Cartographer feels the Hollow Serpent's frequency behind it. |
| **Fate-Knot Weaving** | — | The core Fate-Knot system becomes active. Maximum stored Knots = Resonance modifier (minimum 2). All Knots clear at the end of each Deep Attunement — stored probability cannot be held indefinitely, it begins to express itself in unpredictable ways after 8 hours. Knots stored during the current encounter only: any Knot not spent by the end of the encounter in which it was captured releases spontaneously — the Game Master secretly rolls on the Knot Release table (see below). |
| **Bond Cartography** | — | The Stellar Cartographer can now map Bond connections visible to them. When they read two creatures' Fate Numbers simultaneously, they know: whether the creatures are bonded, the tier of the bond (Paired/Triad/Quad/Quint), the bond's current health (stable, strained, severed, or inverted by Void-energy), and whether the bond is acknowledged or denied. Denied bonds register as two taut threads — both Numbers are present but pulling toward each other without meeting. An inverted (Void-Husk) bond registers as one Number present and one Number-shaped hole. |
| **Probability Threading** | — | The Cartographer may now spend two Fate-Knots of the same type simultaneously to produce an enhanced effect: Two Bright Knots — grant Resonant Fortune and a +5 bonus to one roll (the probability is genuinely weighted, not just amplified). Two Dark Knots — force a reroll with Resonant Discord and a −5 penalty. One Bright + One Dark — the Woven Thread: a roll that succeeds but produces a complication of equal weight to the success, or fails but produces an unexpected benefit. The Game Master designs the complication/benefit. This is the Loom in motion — nothing is ever simply good or simply bad. |
| **Loom Sight** | — | Once per Deep Attunement, the Stellar Cartographer may spend 10 minutes in focused reading of the Loom's current state in their area. They learn: which Fate Numbers in the current location are approaching a threshold (a significant event is imminent for a specific creature), whether any Quint Bond cluster is within 100 miles (they sense the numerical proximity, not the individuals), and one specific action any creature in the area is likely to take in the next 24 hours (the creature with the most taut thread). Serath of the Closed Circle has this feature — and uses it to monitor emerging Quint Bond formations for the Coil. |
| **Fate-Knot Expansion** | — | Maximum stored Knots increases to Resonance modifier + Mastery Bonus. The Cartographer may now store Knots from their own rolls as well as others'. Additionally: Knots no longer release spontaneously at encounter's end — they can be held until the end of the current Deep Attunement cycle. Extended storage carries cost: each Knot held more than 4 hours causes 1 point of psychic pressure (cosmetic — the Cartographer experiences intrusive probability visions) that clears when the Knot is spent. |
| **Thread Severance** | — | Once per Deep Attunement, by spending three Fate-Knots (any combination), the Stellar Cartographer may attempt to temporarily sever a Fated Bond connection they can perceive. Both bonded creatures make a Resonance Warding Resonance (Threshold 18). If both fail, all Bond benefits are suppressed for 24 hours — the connection exists but cannot function. If either succeeds, the attempt fails and the Cartographer loses the Knots. This is the most ethically contested ability in the Path — the Loom of Fate uses it to separate inconvenient bonds. The ability does not permanently sever bonds. Permanent severance requires death or Void-Husk corruption. This is a suppression, not a cutting. |
| **Quint Recognition** | — | The Stellar Cartographer can now identify Quint Bond cluster members on sight — any creature whose Fate Number falls within the 3-point margin of an active cluster glows faintly in the Cartographer's perception, visible at 300 ft range. They also know, always, whether the Quint Bond has been fully acknowledged (all five members in contact) or is still forming. If the Cartographer themselves is a Quint Bond member, their recognition extends to 1 mile and they always know the direction of each other member. The Ifá prophecy ("the Five Who Remember") refers specifically to a moment when all five simultaneously achieve Quint Recognition. |

### **Callings**

**The Loom****'****s Hand**  —  Fate-Agent

**Reinforcement (Depth 3):  **When you spend a Bright Knot on an ally, they also gain temporary Vitality equal to your Resonance modifier. The Loom strengthens what it endorses.

**Cascade (Depth 7):  **When you spend a Bright Knot and the recipient rolls a natural 20 on the boosted roll, you automatically store a new Bright Knot. Fortune compounds.

**Armor (Depth 11):  **Passive. Once per Pulse, when you would take damage that would reduce you to 0 Vitality, you may spend one Bright Knot to reduce that damage to 1 Vitality instead. The Loom has use for you yet.

**The Unwritten**  —  Fate-Eraser

**Void (Depth 3):  **When you spend a Dark Knot, the target's next roll after the forced reroll cannot benefit from Resonant Fortune, Bond abilities, or any probability-modifying effect. The bad luck doesn't just strike — it strips the cushion around the next moment.

**Masking (Depth 7):  **You can suppress a creature's Fate Number from being read — your own, or any creature you touch for 1 minute of work. The Number still exists but reads as static to any Fate Number Reading ability. Duration: 24 hours. This is the Fate-Breaker ability — the Unwritten Cartographer is the true specialist, while the Fate-Breaker Path borrows a lesser version.

**Cutting (Depth 11):  **Once per Deep Attunement, you may spend three Dark Knots to permanently remove a minor Fated Bond benefit (one specific ability, not the entire bond) from a bonded creature you touch. The bond remains. That particular resonance is simply no longer accessible. The Loom of Fate used this to create the "Denied Bond" condition in some historical cases.

**The Star-Reader**  —  Celestial-Scholar

**Reading (Depth 3):  **When you read a creature's Fate Number, you also learn their zodiac sign and whether they have taken their Zodiac Attunement. If they haven't, you know why — the Attunement's prerequisite (Legendary Beast encounter) either has or hasn't been met, and you sense which Beast would recognize them.

**Map (Depth 7):  **Once per Deep Attunement, you may create a probability map of the next 24 hours for one location. The Game Master places three markers on the map: one threat, one opportunity, one wildcard. All three will manifest somewhere in the location within the time frame. You know the category but not the specific event.

**Reading (Depth 11):  **You can determine whether a Legendary Beast has noticed a specific creature — whether it is aware of them, whether it considers them a peer, and whether it would receive them peacefully. This knowledge is useful for planning Zodiac Attunement encounters. You cannot force the Beast's recognition. You can tell the character whether they're ready.

### **Ashé-Medium**

**Core Mechanic:  **The Ashé-Medium does not cast Workings. They do not open Aetheric Channels. They invite. The distinction matters because an invited force is not under the Medium's control — it is under the Orisha's. The Medium's skill lies in cultivating a relationship of sufficient trust and resonance that the Orisha chooses to come when called, expresses through the Medium's body with care for the Medium's survival, and departs when the situation is resolved rather than lingering to serve its own agenda. Every Ashé-Medium is, at all times, in an ongoing relationship with a being of immense power. The Path is the cultivation of that relationship.  Ashé-Mediums are not exclusively Ashé-Touched Kindred, though the Path is most naturally walked by those whose biology already carries Orisha resonance. A Huma

