| **Orisha Patron ****&**** Ashé Vessel** | — | Choose your patron Orisha (Eshu-Elegbara, Ogun, Shango, Yemaya, Oshun, Oya, Obatala, or Orunmila). This is your primary divine relationship — the Orisha you have spent years cultivating contact with. The Ashé Vessel system becomes active. Patron Domain: Your patron's Domain ability (from Kindred traits if Ashé-Touched, or learned through initiation otherwise) activates at double potency when you have 5+ Ashé in the Vessel. Communal Instinct: Whenever you complete an Act that benefits another creature, you may immediately restore 1 Ashé as an Instinct — the act of giving fills the vessel automatically. |
| **Orisha Workings** | — | The Ashé-Medium gains access to Workings powered by Ashé rather than Aetheric Channels — these cannot be suppressed by Aether-Dampening Ore (Ashé predates the Aetheric system). Beginning Working list varies by patron: Eshu-Elegbara: Open/Close Threshold, Comprehend Languages, Misfortune Ogun: Sharpness, Iron Skin, Righteous Strike, Unbreakable Shango: Call Lightning, Thunder Clap, Storm Sight, Judgment Strike Yemaya: Healing Waters, Breathe Water, Ocean's Embrace, Wave Wall Oshun: Sweet Persuasion, Truth Waters, Fertility Blessing, Emotional Reading Oya: Wind Walk, Ancestor Speak, Storm Cloak, Death's Threshold Obatala: Peace Aura, Purify, Calm Emotions, White Light Ward Orunmila: Ifá Reading, Fate Sight, Destiny Nudge, Truth Compulsion Each Working costs 1–3 Ashé depending on power. The C |
| **Orisha Invocation** | — | Using 3 Ashé as an Act, call partial Orisha presence. For 1 minute (10 rounds): patron Domain ability activates at full potency; all patron Workings cost 1 fewer Ashé; the Medium's presence is perceptible to those with spiritual sensitivity (Attunement DC 12 Active Resonance to feel the divine nearness). Drain: 1 Ashé per round while Invocation is active. When Ashé drops to 0, the Invocation ends immediately. The Orisha is present but not in control — the Medium acts with divine support, not divine replacement. |
| **Second Orisha Contact** | — | Through years of expanded ritual practice, the Ashé-Medium establishes contact with a secondary Orisha (chosen from the list, different from the patron). They gain 3 Workings from the secondary Orisha's list, usable at standard Ashé cost. The secondary Orisha cannot be Invoked — that intimacy belongs to the patron only. However: once per Deep Attunement, the secondary Orisha may speak through the Medium briefly (1 Pulse) without Ashé cost — these moments are not chosen by the Medium. The Game Master decides when the secondary Orisha has something to say. |
| **Full Possession** | — | Once per Deep Attunement, spending 8 Ashé as an Act, the patron Orisha fully inhabits the Medium's body for 3 rounds. The Game Master runs the character as the Orisha — not maliciously, but with divine priority rather than the character's personal agenda. The Orisha will not act against the character's fundamental nature but pursues its own objectives for those 3 rounds. Orisha stats during Possession: Forcefulness and Resonance increase by 4; all Workings from the patron list cost 0 Ashé; the Orisha may use one ability the Medium does not normally have access to (Game Master designs this based on the Orisha's nature). After Possession: character drops to 0 Vitality and stabilizes immediately. Ashé resets to 0. The Orisha remembers. Actions taken during Possession are remembered by the pat |
| **Communal Anchor** | — | The Ashé-Medium becomes a node of communal spiritual protection. All allies within 30 feet of the Medium have Resonant Fortune on Warding Resonances against Dread-Struck, Soul-Swayed, and Void-Touched Exposure. This is not a Working — it is the ambient presence of accumulated Orisha relationship radiating outward. Against Ashen Coil Workings specifically: allies within 30 feet may add the Medium's Resonance modifier to their Warding Resonances. The Orishas and the Hollow Serpent are ancient opposites. The Medium's body has become a claim staked against entropy. |
| **Orisha Convergence** | — | The Ashé-Medium may now Invoke their secondary Orisha simultaneously with their patron. Both Orisha are present but neither is in full control — the Medium navigates between them. During Dual Invocation (costs 6 Ashé to initiate, drains 2 Ashé per round): access to both patron and secondary Working lists at half cost; the Medium's body shows traits of both Orishas simultaneously; creatures witnessing this must make an Attunement Warding Resonance (Threshold 16) or be Dread-Struck for 1 round — not from malice, but from proximity to two divine presences in one mortal frame. Dual Invocation cannot escalate to Full Possession — the Orishas will not share a body completely. Attempting to force Full Possession during Dual Invocation causes both to withdraw and costs 1 week of relationship repai |

### **Callings**

**The Community Healer**  —  Restoration

**Healing (Depth 3):  **Your healing Workings restore Vitality equal to double the normal amount when cast on a creature at or below half their maximum Vitality. The Orisha gives more to those who need more.

**Restoration (Depth 7):  **Once per Deep Attunement, by spending 4 Ashé in a 1-hour community ritual involving at least 5 willing participants, you remove one curse, magical disease, or long-term condition from each participant simultaneously. The ritual requires genuine communal participation — performed as a service, not a transaction.

**Gift (Depth 11):  **When you complete a Full Possession, choose one ally who witnessed it. They gain full Vitality restoration and all conditions removed — the Orisha's passing through heals its wake.

**The War-Medium**  —  Combat

**Body (Depth 3):  **During Orisha Invocation, your Guard Rating increases by 3 and all Strike Resonances deal +1d6 damage of your patron's domain type. The Orisha's combat nature flows through you during the Invocation.

**Fury (Depth 7):  **When you reduce a hostile creature to 0 Vitality while Invoking your patron, you gain 2 Ashé immediately — the Orisha approves. This can only trigger once per Pulse.

**Form (Depth 11):  **When you use Full Possession with a martial patron, the Orisha's stat bonuses increase to +6 Forcefulness and all attacks during Possession are Resonant Strikes (maximum damage) without rolling. The price: after Possession ends, you are at 0 Vitality AND gain one level of Aetheric Depletion. The Orisha burns brighter in the War-Medium's body.

**The Ancestor-Speaker**  —  Divination

**Threshold (Depth 3):  **You can speak with the dead for up to 1 hour after death (extended from 10 minutes). The dead remember everything up to the moment of dying and answer honestly — they have nothing left to protect.

**Consultation (Depth 7):  **Once per session, spend 2 Ashé and 1 hour in divination ritual. Ask the Game Master one complex question about any creature's past, nature, or motivation. The answer is always accurate and always filtered through the Orisha's perspective — Orunmila answers in patterns, Oya answers in endings.

**Ancestor (Depth 11):  **Once per Deep Attunement, spend 5 Ashé to invite a specific dead individual's presence as a spiritual advisor. They remain for 24 hours, invisible to non-spiritual-sensitive creatures, able to advise but not act. The Medium chooses who. The ancestor chooses whether to come.

### **Coil-Stalker**

**Core Mechanic:  **The Coil-Stalker is not a villain. They are someone who looked at the Ashen Coil's power, understood what it actually is, and decided that carrying it in a controlled form was better than leaving it exclusively in the Coil's hands. The original Coil-Stalkers were agents of the Loom of Fate who were tasked with infiltrating the Ashen Coil — and who discovered, over time, that infiltration required genuine corruption, and genuine corruption required management. The Lead-Scale Corruption gauge is the management system they developed to survive.  The Coil-Stalker is the most morally complex Path in Sideros because the power it uses is objectively entropic — it does not simply harm enemies, it harms the Coil-Stalker too. Every use of Void-energy pushes the gauge. A Coil-Stalker who loses discip

