### **Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Stage: Cold (0–5) — The Carrier** | — | The Coil-Stalker carries Void-energy but has not integrated it. No bonuses, no penalties. Passive benefits: detect Coil agents within 60 ft (they register as corruption on the gauge — a subtle pull in the right direction); Void-Husks do not immediately attack a Cold Coil-Stalker (they process them as potentially Coil-aligned); complete immunity to the Corrupted condition from mundane poison sources. |
| **Stage: Tempered (6–10) — The Weapon** | — | Corruption Strikes: Melee strikes deal +1d4 necrotic damage. The Void-energy bleeds through physical contact. Void-Sense: Passive awareness of all active Coil Workings within 300 ft — the Cartographer reads the Loom, the Coil-Stalker reads the rot. Necrotic Resistance: Resistance to necrotic and poison damage. The corruption has begun to immunize. Glow: Faint purple light from corruption sites on the skin — Stealth has Resonant Discord in darkness unless the light is covered. This is not optional. The gauge shows. |
| **Stage: Burning (11–15) — The Hazard** | — | Enhanced Corruption Strikes: +1d8 necrotic. Void-Husk Neutrality: Void-Husks ordered to attack the Coil-Stalker must make a Warding Resonance (Threshold 14) to do so — they instinctively classify the Stalker as Coil-adjacent. Psychic Pressure: Wisdom Warding Resonances against Coil compulsions have Resonant Discord — the burning gauge makes the Coil's whispers louder. Stealth failure: The purple glow is now bright enough to be visible at 30 ft in darkness even through cover. Social encounters with Coil-unaware parties become difficult — the corruption is visible to anyone with Attunement DC 10. |
| **Stage: Searing (16–19) — The Edge** | — | Maximum Corruption Strikes: +2d6 necrotic. Void-Frenzy available (see below). Identity Strain: All Attunement and Resonance Active Resonances have Resonant Discord — the Coil's frequency is competing with the Stalker's own. Coil Recognition: Aethar and the 13 Scions are aware of the Coil-Stalker's existence and approximate location — a Searing Coil-Stalker is large enough in the Void-energy field to be visible to those who read it. The Fang of the Whisper will make contact. Whether that contact is an attack or a recruitment attempt depends on the Stalker's recent actions. |
| **Void-Frenzy — Requires 16+ Gauge** | — | Activate as an Instinct. For 1 minute: one extra Strike Resonance per Pulse (Instinct); all Corruption Strikes deal maximum necrotic damage without rolling; cannot distinguish friend from foe — Attunement Warding Resonance (Threshold 14) at the start of each Moment to choose targets (fail = nearest creature, ally or enemy). Gauge increases by 2 immediately on activation, then +1 per round. Spend one Weep-Stone charge as an Instinct to end Frenzy early. On Frenzy end: Gauge is at current level. If Gauge hits 20 during Frenzy, Void-Husk threshold triggers immediately — no Warding Resonance during Frenzy. |
| **Corruption Tolerance** | — | The Coil-Stalker's body has learned to process Void-energy without immediate degradation. The Gauge system becomes active. Weep-Stone Mastery: Siderium Quartz reduces the Gauge by 2 per charge rather than 1 — the Stalker's practiced application is more efficient. Corruption Sense: The Stalker always knows their current Gauge level without checking — they feel the weight of the corruption in their bones. |
| **Controlled Bleed** | — | The Coil-Stalker may deliberately increase their Gauge by 1 as an Instinct to immediately deal their current Corruption Strike damage to one creature within 5 ft — a burst of Void-energy expelled through physical proximity rather than a strike. This does not require an attack roll — it is a direct corruption transfer. The creature takes the damage; the Stalker takes the Gauge increase. A controlled trade that requires knowing exactly how much room is left in the gauge. |
| **Void Reading** | — | The Stalker's corruption has reached sufficient depth to perceive the Coil's operational structure. Once per Brief Attunement, by concentrating for 1 minute, the Stalker may ask the Game Master: the current location of the nearest active Coil cell, one name among the Scions who is directing operations in this region, and whether any Void-Husks in the area are being actively directed or acting autonomously. This information is accurate but not real-time — it reflects the state of the Coil's network as of the last 24 hours. |
| **Corruption Armor** | — | The Void-energy integrated into the Coil-Stalker's body becomes defensive as well as offensive. Guard Rating increases by 1 for every 5 points of current Gauge (maximum +3 at Gauge 15+). Additionally: the Stalker may use their Reflex to impose Resonant Discord on one Strike Resonance targeting them per Pulse — the corruption deflects, absorbing and briefly destabilizing the incoming force. The armor is the poison — a higher Gauge provides more protection but brings the Void-Husk threshold closer. |
| **Gauge Ceiling** | — | The experienced Coil-Stalker has established an internal discipline that prevents accidental Gauge overflow. The Void-Husk threshold is now 22 rather than 20 — two additional points of buffer before the dissolution begins. Additionally: once per Deep Attunement, the Stalker may choose to cap a Gauge increase — when corruption would push the Gauge above 18, they may hold it at 18 by making an Endurance Warding Resonance (Threshold 14). The excess corruption discharges outward as a 10-ft burst of necrotic energy (2d10 damage, Endurance Warding Resonance for half). Control costs expression. |

### **Callings**

**The Infiltrator**  —  Coil-Agent

**Cover (Depth 3):  **At Tempered stage or higher, you may pass as a genuine Coil operative to any creature without Fate Number reading ability. Coil agents will not question your presence or credentials without a specific reason for suspicion.

**Contact (Depth 7):  **You may deliberately initiate contact with one of the 13 Scions. They will meet with you once, believing you are a high-gauge operative seeking guidance. The meeting is real. The Scion will eventually realize you are not what you claimed — but not during the first meeting.

**Agent (Depth 11):  **You maintain two simultaneous identities with Resonant Fortune on Active Resonances to sustain either. When one identity is compromised, the other is not automatically — the Game Master treats them as genuinely separate unless a specific connection is discovered.

**The Purgator**  —  Anti-Coil

**Counter (Depth 3):  **When you strike a Coil operative or Void-Husk, you may expend 2 points of your own Gauge to deal double your Corruption Strike damage to that target only. You carry the same energy. You know exactly where the vulnerabilities are.

**Disruption (Depth 7):  **By entering a Coil ritual site while at Tempered stage or higher, you can disrupt the ritual by spending 3 Gauge points and using your Act for 3 consecutive rounds. The disruption is guaranteed — but each round you remain in the ritual's field, your Gauge increases by 2.

**Severance (Depth 11):  **Once per Deep Attunement, you may touch a Void-Husk and attempt to sever the Coil's control — not restore the creature's Fate Number, but free it from active direction. Endurance Warding Resonance (Threshold 18) for the Void-Husk. On failure: the Coil's control breaks, the Void-Husk collapses (0 Vitality, stable). Your Gauge increases by 4. On success: the Void-Husk resists — your Gauge increases by 2 and the attempt fails.

**The Scion-Hunter**  —  Assassin

**Sight (Depth 3):  **You can identify a Scion of the Ashen Coil by their corruption signature — each Scion has a distinct zodiac-corrupted frequency that you recognize on sight. You always know a Scion's approximate Gauge level and which zodiac sign they represent.

**Exploit (Depth 7):  **When fighting a Scion, you may align your Corruption Strikes to exploit their sign's domain vulnerability. Your strikes deal +1d10 additional damage of the type their sign's domain would be opposed to (fire vs. water-sign Scion, etc.). This requires 1 round of observation to identify the sign's weakness.

**Problem (Depth 11):  **Having studied the Scions deeply, you understand that defeating one Scion creates a vacancy. You know, intuitively, whether Aethar has already selected a replacement — and roughly where that replacement is being cultivated. This knowledge doesn't prevent the replacement. But it gives you a head start on the next hunt.

### **Geode-Pilot**

**Core Mechanic:  **A Resonant Frame is not armor. It is not a vehicle. It is a second body — one powered by a Geode calibrated to the Pilot's zodiac frequency, one that responds to the Pilot's Aetheric state as naturally as their biological body responds to their nervous system. The Frame cannot be used by anyone else — it is tuned to one specific Pilot's resonance. Another person attempting to operate a Pilot's Frame finds it unresponsive, as if the machinery had simply stopped working. The machinery has simply stopped recognizing the operator.  The Grand Prime Forgeman of Argent Spire is the oldest Geode-Pilot in the world — having piloted, repaired, upgraded, and rebuilt his Frame for four centuries. His Frame is so extensively modified that it no longer resembles any standard Jade Empire design. He knows

