### **Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Aetheric Tools ****&**** Infusion System** | Depth 1 | The Accord-Maker's artisan tools become Aetherically attuned — functioning as a Weaving focus for all Path Features and Workings. The Infusion system becomes active. Begin with 2 known Infusion types (chosen from the Depth 1 list) and 2 active Infusion slots. Learn 2 additional Infusion types at each Resonance Depth. Weaving from tools: The Accord-Maker may weave Workings with a casting time of 1 Action by incorporating the Working into their tool use — the Weaving is part of the crafting motion. They must have their tools in hand. This does not require a separate Act for the focus — it is part of the same action. |
| **Blueprint System ****&**** First Construction** | Depth 1 | The Blueprint system becomes active. Begin with 2 known Blueprints (chosen from the Tier I list) and 1 active Blueprint slot. Additional Blueprint slots unlock at Depths 3, 6, 9, and 14. The First Construction: At Depth 1, the Accord-Maker constructs their first Aetheric Turret or Aetheric Lantern at no material cost — a practice model, produced during the session that establishes the character. This represents the training construction that completed their initiation into the tradition. The Game Master should make this moment a scene. |
| **Aetheric Knowledge** | Depth 1 | The Accord-Maker gains Mastery in two Disciplines from: Aetheric Lore, History, Investigation, Medicine, Nature, or Sleight of Hand. They also gain Mastery in artisan's tools of their choice (the tools that function as their focus). Additionally: the Accord-Maker always knows whether an object they examine has been Infused, Blueprinted, or otherwise Aetherically worked — and approximately when, by what tier of practitioner, and whether the agreement is still stable. This is professional recognition, not a Working. |
| **Right Tool for the Job** | Depth 2 | During a Brief Attunement, the Accord-Maker may produce any nonmagical artisan's tool from their portable kit without having specifically packed it — the agreement between their kit and their needs produces whatever is required. This covers any tool worth 25gp or less. It does not cover materials — only the instruments for working with them. Additionally: when the Accord-Maker succeeds on a crafting Active Resonance using their Mastered tools, they may immediately begin a second related crafting task as part of the same time period — two things built in the time one normally takes, if both use the same tool set. |
| **Aetheric Channels — Limited Access** | Depth 1 | Unlike most Weave-capable Paths, the Accord-Maker has a restricted Aetheric Channel pool — they are engineers, not weavers. They gain Channels as follows: Depths 1–4: Two 1st-tier Channels per Deep Attunement Depths 5–8: Two 1st-tier + two 2nd-tier Depths 9–12: Two each of 1st, 2nd, 3rd-tier Depths 13–16: Two each of 1st through 4th-tier Depths 17–20: Two each of 1st through 5th-tier The Accord-Maker does not gain higher tiers through natural progression. Infusions and Blueprints do not cost Aetheric Channels — they are pre-negotiated. Channels are used only for active Workings from the Accord-Maker's Working list, which is curated rather than comprehensive. |
| **Accord-Maker Working List** | Depth 1 — Always Prepared | Unlike the Comet-Magus who prepares from a broad ledger, the Accord-Maker always has the same Working list available — a curated set of technically-oriented Workings that have been incorporated into their practice. They do not need to prepare these; they are always available as long as Channels remain. Working List (always prepared): Ambient Workings: Guidance, Mending, Resistance (Endurance boost), Prestidigitation 1st-tier: Cure Wounds, Detect Workings, Disguise Self, Expeditious Retreat, False Life, Feather Fall, Grease, Identify, Jump, Longstrider, Sanctuary 2nd-tier: Aid, Arcane Lock, Blur, Continual Flame, Darkvision, Enhance Attribute, Heat Metal, Invisibility, Levitate, Magic Mouth, Rope Trick, See Invisibility, Spider Climb, Web 3rd-tier: Blink, Dispel Working, Elemental Weapon, Fly |
| **Aetheric Flash of Genius** | Depth 7 | When a creature within 30 ft of the Accord-Maker makes an Active Resonance or Warding Resonance, the Accord-Maker may use their Reflex to add their Acuity modifier to the roll — identifying the precise physical or Aetheric adjustment that would improve the outcome and communicating it instantly. This is not a Working. It is expertise. It cannot be suppressed by Aether-Dampening Ore. Usage: Once per Pulse maximum. The Accord-Maker must be able to perceive the situation — they cannot Flash of Genius for a roll they cannot observe. |
| **Aetheric Infusion Mastery** | Depth 11 | When the Accord-Maker applies an Infusion, the Aetheric agreement is now so efficient that the item effectively counts as an Aetheric Artifact of Attuned tier — without requiring the recipient to spend an Attunement/Resonance Binding slot. Up to three Infused items may benefit from this simultaneously. Items beyond three still require normal Resonance Binding. Additionally: Infusions no longer end on Deep Attunement automatically. The Accord-Maker may choose to refresh them during Deep Attunement — but an Infusion maintained without refreshing gradually improves: after 30 days of continuous maintenance, the Infusion's bonus increases by 1 (a +1 weapon becomes +2, etc.). Maximum improvement through this method: +3. |
| **Aetheric Soul** | Depth 14 | The Accord-Maker's constant work with Aetheric agreements has integrated a persistent Aetheric field into their body. They gain the following permanent properties: • Resistance to force and Aetheric damage — the body has learned to absorb rather than receive. • Immunity to disease — the Aetheric field maintains biological stability. • The Accord-Maker does not age — time continues, but biological degradation has been negotiated away. They can still be killed. They simply won't die of old age. • Their Infusion limit increases by 2 permanently — the Aetheric Soul provides additional bandwidth for active agreements. The Grand Prime Forgeman discovered this feature after two centuries of practice. He did not consider it remarkable — it was simply the logical conclusion of maintaining enough agreements. |
| **Aetheric Perfection** | Depth 20 | The Accord-Maker's mastery has reached a point where the agreements they negotiate are so efficient that they require minimal maintenance. Once per Deep Attunement, when the Accord-Maker rolls any die for an Active Resonance, Warding Resonance, damage roll, or Working effect and dislikes the result, they may use their Reaction to reroll — keeping the new result regardless. Additionally: all Infusions the Accord-Maker maintains now function at +1 above their stated values. A +2 Infusion becomes effectively +3. A resistance Infusion grants immunity instead of resistance. The agreements are simply that good. |

### **Callings**

**The Dunmarim Alchemist**  —  Beta-aspected · Dunmarim Tradition

**Alchemical Savant (Depth 3):  **The Alchemist gains Mastery in the Alchemist's Supplies tool and adds their Acuity modifier to the damage and healing of any Working they deliver through a potion, elixir, or alchemical preparation — including healing Workings administered as a liquid. Additionally: when the Alchemist uses a Healing Potion, it heals maximum Vitality rather than rolling. The agreement is pre-calibrated to be as efficient as possible.

**Experimental Elixir (Depth 3):  **At the end of each Deep Attunement, the Alchemist produces a number of Experimental Elixirs equal to their Acuity modifier (minimum 1). Roll d6 for each: 1 = Healing (2d4+2 Vitality restored), 2 = Swiftness (Resonant Fortune on Swiftness Active Resonances for 1 hour), 3 = Resilience (1d6+1 Aetheric Buffer), 4 = Boldness (immune to Dread-Struck for 1 hour), 5 = Flight (fly 10 ft per Pulse for 10 minutes), 6 = Transformation (choose one Minor Aspect from the Primal Accord's Aspect table — lasts 10 minutes). The Alchemist cannot choose the results — they can only control the quality of the reagen

**Restorative Reagents (Depth 5):  **When the Alchemist casts a healing Working by administering an elixir or potion, they may remove one of the following conditions simultaneously at no additional Channel cost: Corrupted, Dread-Struck, or one level of Aetheric Depletion. The chemistry addresses both the symptom and its Aetheric cause simultaneously.

**Chemical Mastery (Depth 9):  **The Alchemist gains immunity to poison and the Corrupted condition — years of working with volatile substances have produced comprehensive biological adaptation. Additionally: once per Deep Attunement, the Alchemist may produce one dose of Greater Restoration or Raise Dead as a 1-hour alchemical process requiring 300gp in reagents. These are not Workings — they are chemical solutions to biological problems. They function inside the Stillness of Dunmar.

**The Runic Armorer**  —  Alpha-aspected · Dunmarim Rune-Smith Tradition

**Arcane Armor (Depth 3):  **The Runic Armorer designates one suit of armor as their Arcane Armor — spending their Deep Attunement Infusion work on it specifically. The Arcane Armor: always fits perfectly (no disadvantage from mismatched size); can be donned or doffed as an Act rather than requiring the standard time; and functions as the Armorer's Weaving focus, meaning they do not need separate artisan's tools to apply Infusions while wearing it. The armor is always Infused — the agreement is built into the armor's fundamental structure rather than sitting on top of it.

**Armor Model (Depth 3):  **Choose one of two configurations for the Arcane Armor. This can be changed during a Deep Attunement: Guardian Model: Integrated weapon (the armor itself can deliver melee strikes — 1d8 + Forcefulness modifier thunder damage). Thunder Gauntlet ability: a struck creature has Resonant Discord on Strike Resonances against anyone except the Armorer until the start of their next Moment. Infiltrator Model: Integrated ranged weapon (lightning launcher built into the forearm — 1d6 + Acuity modifier lightning damage, 90-ft range). The armor enhances Stealth rather than impeding it — no Resonant Discord

Armor Modifications (Depth 3 + every 2 Depths): At Depth 3 and every even Depth thereafter, choose one Armor Modification to integrate permanently into the Arcane Armor: • Gemini System: Arcane Armor can split into two suits (duplicate armor for an ally, each with half the bonuses) • Aetheric Propulsion: Fly speed 30 ft • Reinforced Defense: +1 Guard Rating (may be taken twice) • Blazing Beacon: Emit bright light 30 ft radius; immune to radiant damage • Dampening Field: Resistance to one damage type (chosen when taken) • Perfected Armor: +1 Strike Resonance to all attacks made by the Armorer w

**Perfected Armor (Depth 15):  **The Arcane Armor's Infusion bonus increases to +2. Additionally: when the Armorer takes damage while wearing the Arcane Armor, they may use their Reflex to reduce that damage by 1d6 + Acuity modifier — the armor's agreements absorb and redistribute incoming force. Usable once per Pulse.

**The Siege Engineer**  —  Alpha-aspected · Jade Empire War-Machine Tradition

**Turret Mastery (Depth 3):  **The Siege Engineer's Aetheric Turrets are significantly enhanced. Turret damage increases to 2d8 + Acuity modifier. Turrets can now be activated from up to 120 ft rather than 60 ft. Additionally: the Siege Engineer may deploy two Turrets simultaneously (using the same Blueprint slot) — this represents a dual-turret configuration that the standard Blueprint cannot achieve without the Engineer's specialization. The Engineer may use their Instinct to command both simultaneously.

**Flash of Tactical Genius (Depth 3):  **Once per Pulse, when an ally within 30 ft makes a Strike Resonance roll and misses, the Siege Engineer may use their Reflex to grant that ally an immediate reroll using Resonant Fortune — identifying the precise adjustment needed in the weapon's angle, timing, or target approach. This is the Flash of Genius feature (normally Depth 7) applied specifically to combat rolls, available early to the Siege Engineer because battlefield optimization is their entire practice.

**Fortified Position (Depth 5):  **The Siege Engineer can establish a Fortified Position during a Brief Attunement — deploying up to their Acuity modifier in Aetheric devices (Turrets, defensive constructs, Aetheric Locks, alarm glyphs) within a 60-ft radius as a single coordinated deployment rather than individually. The coordinated deployment costs the same Blueprint slots as individual deployment but requires only 10 minutes rather than hours. The Position remains active indefinitely but can only be established once per Brief Attunement.

**Aetheric Cannon Expertise (Depth 9):  **The Siege Engineer can fire their Aetheric Cannon as an Instinct rather than an Act — the pre-aimed targeting system responds to thought-level commands rather than requiring physical manipulation. Additionally: the Cannon's recalibration time between shots drops from 1 minute to 1 Pulse — it fires every round if the Engineer wishes. The cooldown represents physical heat management, not Aetheric recovery. The Engineer has solved the heat problem.

**The Resonant Architect**  —  Beta-aspected · Grid-Integrated Construction

**Extended Blueprint Capacity (Depth 3):  **The Resonant Architect's Blueprint active slots increase by 2. Additionally: they gain access to Tier IV and V Blueprints one Depth earlier than the standard progression (Depth 9 rather than 10 for Tier IV; Depth 12 rather than 14 for Tier V). The Architect's specialization compresses the learning curve for complex constructions.

**Grid Integration (Depth 3):  **The Resonant Architect can integrate any Blueprint-constructed object with a nearby Ceque Line node — if constructed within 300 ft of an active node, the object draws ambient power from the node rather than requiring the Accord-Maker's ongoing maintenance. Integrated objects: never expire, function at +1 above stated values, and alert the Architect (regardless of distance) when tampered with or damaged. This feature is why the Accord-Maker tradition's most accomplished Architects are found in Elethorn — and why the Coil considers them priority targets.

**Permanent Construction (Depth 5):  **The Resonant Architect can construct permanent structures — buildings, bridges, fortifications — with Aetheric properties integrated into their architecture. Construction requires the standard Blueprint time × the structure's scale (a room: standard time; a building: 1 week; a fortification: 1 month). Completed structures gain one Infusion-equivalent property per 10 ft of height or 100 sq ft of floor area (chosen at construction). The Resonant Binding ritual's sixth component — the Ceque-Walker circuit — is essentially a Resonant Architect's work performed at continental scale. An Architect wh

**★ Resonant Node Stabilizer Access (Depth 9):  **The Resonant Architect automatically learns the Resonant Node Stabilizer Blueprint at Depth 9 without requiring the Grand Prime Forgeman's instruction or Precursor documents — their deep understanding of grid integration produces the same knowledge through applied practice. This is the earliest any Accord-Maker Calling can access this Blueprint. The Game Master should consider what it means when a player character Accord-Maker reaches Depth 9 while Grid-Point Seven is reactivating.

## **PART III: PLAY REFERENCE**

### **The Fated Bond System**

The Loom of Fate weaves every living creature's future. Among the millions of threads it sustains, a small number fall into proximity with each other -- not by accident, not by choice, but because the pattern the Loom is building requires those specific frequencies together. Most people will live their entire lives and never know their Fate Number. Those who do rarely find anyone within range. Those who do find someone rarely experience the specific shared moment that activates the thread. Those who do rarely complete the acknowledgment before the world separates them.

Finding a Fated Mate is not a feature of a good life. It is an event of such rarity that most cultures have myths about it rather than firsthand accounts. The Coil has been preventing it from happening for fifty years. The Loom has been trying to produce it for centuries. These facts are in direct tension.

### **The Veiling -- Why Most People Never Bond**

| **Most people die without ever knowing their Fate Number.** A Stellar Cartographer is required to reliably read it. Cartographers charge for the service. The Coil has spent fifty years bribing, threatening, and occasionally disappearing independent Cartographers. Those that remain often report to the Fang of the Whisper's Register. Finding a trustworthy Cartographer who will not report your Number to a Coil-adjacent database requires either wealth, connections, or luck. |
| --- |

Even people who KNOW their Numbers face the remaining barriers: finding someone with a compatible Number who also knows their own, experiencing a Kindle Moment together, surviving the Thread State without the Coil or circumstance severing it, and completing the Acknowledgment ceremony before the window closes.

### **Revised Fate Number Proximity Requirements**

| **Tier** | **Bond Type** | **Number Proximity** | **What ****"****Within X Points****"**** Actually Means in the World** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Tier I** | **Paired Bond** | **Within 5 points** | Roughly 10% of the population is numerically eligible to bond with any given person. After accounting for the Veiling (most never know their Number) and the Kindle Moment requirement, perhaps 1 in 200 people ever completes a Paired Bond. Most go their entire lives without it. |
| **Tier II** | **Triad Bond** | **All 3 within 4 points** | Three specific people, all within 4 points of each other. Requires genuine cosmic arrangement. No recorded Triad has ever formed by accident -- someone was always looking, or the Loom was weaving visibly. |
| **Tier III** | **Quad Bond** | **All 4 within 2 points** | Effectively impossible without the Loom actively working toward it. Four souls within 2 points have occurred twice in recorded history: the Four Architects of Kallos (four thousand years ago) and one other cluster that the Coil destroyed before acknowledgment. |
| **Tier IV** | **Quint Bond** | **All 5 within 1 point** | Five souls at the same number. Not within one -- at the same number, or one apart. This has never been recorded. The Coil's entire existence is organized around preventing it. |

### **The Three Stages of Bond Formation**

A Fated Bond does not form from proximity and compatible Numbers alone. Three distinct stages must occur in sequence. Each can be interrupted.

### **Stage 1 -- Resonant Proximity**

When two people with compatible Numbers spend time near each other, both notice something they cannot explain. Not attraction necessarily -- sharpened attention. Unusual clarity when the other person speaks. A sense that this person is somehow more real than others in the room.

This stage is entirely passive and unconscious. Neither party knows it is happening. Animals in the area may behave differently around the pair. A Stellar Cartographer within 60 ft can detect the proximity resonance as a faint mutual glow between the two Numbers.

## **Resonant Proximity does not produce any mechanical benefit. It produces narrative weight.**

### **Stage 2 -- The Kindle Moment**

The bond cannot form by intention. The Loom decides when. A Kindle Moment is a specific shared experience that simultaneously exposes both souls' Aetheric signatures -- stripping away the protective Aetheric "noise" that normally conceals a person's Number from casual observation.

| **What Qualifies as a Kindle Moment** One party reaching a Loom Test (0 Vitality) while the other is present and conscious -- not winning a fight, a genuine moment of potential death. │ Both witnessing the same Legendary Beast recognition event within 300 ft simultaneously. │ Surviving a Void-Husk attack together during which both come within one Pulse of incapacitation. │ The death of someone both knew, witnessed together in the immediate aftermath, when both are fully exposed emotionally. │ A shared revelation that irrevocably changes both of them -- the kind that makes everything before feel like a different life. |
| --- |

| **What Does NOT Qualify** Shared travel, meals, or conversation -- regardless of intimacy or duration. Combat that does not reach a Loom Test. Being in proximity to a disaster without meaningful shared exposure. Arranged meetings or ceremonies, however significant to the parties. Any experience manufactured with the intention of triggering a Kindle Moment -- the Loom cannot be tricked. |
| --- |

A Kindle Moment is visible to Stellar Cartographers within range as two Fate Number threads illuminating simultaneously -- like a struck match seen from across a dark room. The flash lasts one Pulse and leaves a detectable trace for approximately 24 hours. The Fang of the Whisper specifically trains operatives to recognize this signature.

### **Stage 3 -- The Thread State**

After a Kindle Moment, the bond thread exists but is fragile. This Thread State lasts 1d6+2 months. During this period:

| **What Both Experience** | **Details** |
| --- | --- |
| **Drawn attention** | Both feel inexplicably more aware of the other -- not love necessarily, not attraction necessarily. Just a quality of attention they cannot explain and cannot fully redirect. |
| **Emotional permeability** | Resonant Fortune on Insight Active Resonances directed AT each other. They read each other more clearly than they want to. This is not a gift -- it is a vulnerability. |
| **The Loom****'****s weight** | Both occasionally feel as though something important is unresolved. During sleep, both may experience the same location in their dreams (not communication -- the same setting, independently). This is the Loom trying to close the circuit. |
| **Invisible to most** | Neither party knows the Bond system exists unless someone tells them. Most people in Thread State attribute the feeling to ordinary human connection and either act on it or don't. |

| **How the Thread Can Be Severed** | **Details** |
| --- | --- |
| **Deliberate emotional rejection** | If one party says, explicitly and aloud, that they do not feel the connection and do not wish to pursue it -- spoken in the other's presence -- the thread severs. It cannot be re-formed by a second Kindle Moment with the same person. |
| **Extended planar separation** | More than 30 continuous days on different planes. The Thread cannot sustain across that distance. |
| **Coil interference ritual** | The Fang of the Whisper possesses a suppression ritual developed from corrupted Stellar Cartographer knowledge. It requires a Coil operative within 10 ft of either party for one uninterrupted hour. It does not kill -- it quiets the thread until it fades naturally. Most targets never know it happened. |
| **Death of either party** | The thread severs. Unlike an acknowledged Bond, a severed Thread produces no lasting Aetheric damage to the survivor -- but the grief is real. |

### **The Acknowledgment**

To advance from Thread State to a formal Paired Bond, both parties must acknowledge the bond. This is more than saying "I feel it." It requires:

Both present simultaneously. | Each speaks the acknowledgment in the other's hearing -- not scripted, not ceremonial, just true. | A witness (any person; the acknowledgment gains additional Aetheric weight if the witness is a Stellar Cartographer or another bonded individual). | The Aetheric discharge: at the moment of full acknowledgment, candles extinguish within 30 ft, animals within 60 ft go still, and any Weave-capable character within range feels the Loom register the change.

### **Bond Tiers and Their Abilities**

| Tier I **Paired Bond -- Shared Pulse** Two souls · Within 5 points · Perhaps 1 in 200 ever completes this · Both must have experienced a Kindle Moment together **Resonant Awareness:  **Always know the general emotional state of the bonded partner -- calm, distressed, focused, afraid. Not thoughts. The feeling. Range: unlimited, same plane. **Shared Pulse:  **Resonant Fortune on one Warding Resonance per Brief Attunement when within 30 ft of the bonded partner. **Loom Test Conversion:  **A bonded partner within 30 ft converts one Loom Test failure to a success per Pulse. The bond's weight on the Loom. **Knowledge Transfer:  **After 6 months of acknowledged bond: each may attempt any Active Resonance the other is Mastered in (without their own Mastery Bonus, but the attempt is possible). |
| --- |

| Tier II **Triad Bond -- Whisper Bond** Three souls · All within 4 points · All pairs must have individual Kindle Moments · All three must acknowledge together **All Tier I abilities apply  **At maximum extent to all three. **Whisper Bond:  **Full telepathy between all three bonded members -- intent, sensation, language -- across the same plane. No action cost for routine communication. **Vitality Transfer:  **As a Reflex, redirect up to half incoming damage from one bonded member to yourself. You cannot redirect damage that would reduce the original target below 0 Vitality. **Aetheric Channel Sharing:  **A Weave-capable bonded member may expend Channels on behalf of another bonded member within 30 ft (the Working manifests from the recipient, not the source). **The Triad****'****s Weight:  **The Aetheric discharge at Triad acknowledgment is significant -- Aetheric Artifacts in a 60 ft radius activate briefly, Fade-Bleed intensifies locally for 1 minute. |
| --- |

| Tier III **Quad Bond -- The Living Memory** Four souls · All within 2 points · Six individual Kindle Moments required (each pair) · Four-way simultaneous acknowledgment **All Tier I-II abilities apply  **At maximum extent. **Full Wordless Communication:  **Communication between all four is instantaneous and does not require the Whisper Bond's active expression -- information simply arrives. **Death Resistance:  **While any conscious bonded member is within 300 ft, no other bonded member can be reduced to 0 Vitality -- they drop to 1 Vitality instead. This does not apply if ALL conscious members are outside 300 ft. **Bond Breach Warning:  **The Aetheric discharge of a Quad Bond acknowledgment causes structural damage in a 300 ft radius. The Coil treats an emerging Quad Bond as an emergency situation requiring immediate Triad-level intervention. |
| --- |

| Tier IV **Quint Bond -- The Fivefold Convergence** Five souls · ALL within 1 point of each other · Ten individual Kindle Moments required · Never recorded in written history **All prior tiers at maximum  **All abilities at all times, regardless of distance. **Aetheric Sovereignty:  **The five generate a persistent field equivalent to a Legendary Beast's presence within 1 mile -- all lesser Aetheric effects either amplified or suppressed at collective will. **Fate Sight:  **The five collectively perceive the Loom of Fate directly -- probability threads, imminent Number convergences, the shape of events before they occur. **Resonant Survival:  **No member can be reduced to 0 Vitality while any other member is conscious. At Legendary Depth III, unconditional -- no longer requires conscious allies. **The Question of the Quint:  **The Ifá prophecy names them "the Five Who Remember What the Gods Were." The Coil has been ensuring this never happens. Aethar has read the same text. He knows exactly what five souls at the same Number can do to his plan. |
| --- |

### **The Resonant Near-Miss**

People whose Numbers fall within 6 to 12 points of each other -- outside the Paired Bond range but close enough to feel -- experience a pull that feels identical to the early Thread State. It is genuine. The Loom is using them as emotional anchors while the real alignment is still forming elsewhere. The Near-Miss is not nothing. It just isn't the Bond.

| **Near-Miss Aspect** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **What it feels like** | Drawn attention. Unusual clarity. The sense that this person matters in a way others don't. The experience is real. The Loom is not misleading anyone -- these are emotionally significant relationships. They simply aren't the final answer. |
| **What it produces** | A relationship that may be deeply meaningful, long-lasting, and formative. Many people build entire lives around Near-Miss connections. Some are content. Some always feel something is slightly unresolved. |
| **False resolution** | The Coil's Fang of the Whisper deliberately cultivates Near-Miss relationships for identified Quint Bond candidates -- arranging that a candidate finds someone "close enough" and settles, while the true alignment never forms. This is their quietest and most effective prevention method. |
| **Detection** | A Stellar Cartographer can distinguish a Near-Miss from a true Thread or acknowledged Bond. A Near-Miss has no Kindle Moment residue and no Thread-glow. It reads as "proximity without ignition." Many Cartographers choose not to say this aloud to their clients. |
| **The reckoning** | When a person in a Near-Miss relationship later encounters their true bond-partner and experiences a Kindle Moment, both understand simultaneously what the prior relationship was and was not. This is one of the more complicated experiences the Loom produces. There is no easy path through it. |

## **The Coil****'****s Systematic Suppression -- Game Master Reference**

Aethar has read the Ifá prophecy. He was present when Orunmila fell. He understands what five bonded souls in perfect resonance can do to his plan. The Fang of the Whisper's secondary mission is specifically structured around this knowledge.

| **Program** | **Method** |
| --- | --- |
| **The Register** | A continuously updated record of known Fate Numbers, cross-referenced for proximity clusters. Any pair within ±5 that comes to Coil attention gets a file. Any emerging Triad gets a Priority Flag. Any Quad Bond attempt triggers Triad-level personal intervention from Drava Nullsong. |
| **The Cartographer Program** | Systematic intimidation, bribery, and occasional disappearance of independent Stellar Cartographers over fifty years. Coil-affiliated Cartographers provide readings but quietly report to the Register. Finding a trustworthy Cartographer is now a meaningful quest hook. |
| **The Separation Mechanism** | For identified bond pairs: not usually physical murder (Loom disruption is detectable). Fabricated scandal. A compelling job offer in a different city. A message that turns one against the other. A Near-Miss partner introduced at the right moment. Quiet, deniable, and leaves no Aetheric trace. |
| **The Thread Suppression Ritual** | The most targeted tool. A Coil operative within 10 ft of either Thread party for one uninterrupted hour can apply a ritual that quietly quiets the thread until it fades. Most targets never know it happened -- they just find that the pull they felt gradually becomes less urgent over weeks. |
| **The Coil****'****s Blind Spot** | Companion Threads (animal bonds -- see below) are not tracked by the Register. A companion with a compatible Number can carry information about the bond without the Coil noticing. Serath knows this but has not reported it to Aethar. |

### **The Companion Thread -- Animal Bond Mechanics**

Animal companions have Fate Numbers. A Stellar Cartographer reads them differently -- "like a Number written in a different hand" -- but they are real, cosmic, and meaningful. When a companion's Number falls within range of its partner's, a distinct form of bond can develop. This is called the Companion Thread.

| **The Companion Thread is NOT a Fated Bond tier.** It runs alongside the Fated Bond system without replacing or advancing it. A companion cannot be the **"**third soul**"** of a Triad Bond or the **"**fifth soul**"** of a Quint Bond -- higher tiers require sapient souls capable of conscious acknowledgment. However, a Companion Thread amplifies any Fated Bond its partner participates in, and it has its own mechanics, formation process, and Aetheric weight. |
| --- |

### **Companion Number Proximity**

| **Proximity** | **Status** | **What It Means** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Within 8 points** | Companion Thread eligible | The companion and partner are cosmically attuned. The Thread can develop through the formation process below. |
| **9-15 points** | Companion Near-Miss | Strong natural affinity -- the companion chose this person and keeps choosing them. Not a Companion Thread, but the relationship is unusually deep. No special mechanics, but the Game Master should treat this companion as genuinely attached beyond training. |
| **16+ points** | Standard companion bond | Trained loyalty and genuine affection, but no cosmic dimension. The beast companion system's Evolution Feats still apply -- they just develop through relationship rather than resonance. |

### **Companion Thread Formation**

The Companion Thread forms differently from a human Fated Bond. Animals experience the world at a different register of consciousness -- they cannot reflect on what they feel or compare it to alternatives. Their acknowledgment is expressed through action, not language.

### **Stage 1 -- Attunement Recognition**

Passive. From the moment of first contact, a companion within Number range feels the resonance as simple comfort -- an unusual calm around this specific person that does not occur around others. The partner feels a reciprocal sense of being more clearly understood by this animal than they have been by any other. A Stellar Cartographer within 60 ft sees a faint glow around both.

### **Stage 2 -- The Companion Kindle**

A specific shared moment that reveals the depth of the companion's choice. Three types qualify:

| **Kindle Type** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **The Loom Test Witness** | The partner reaches a Loom Test (0 Vitality) and the companion stays at their side rather than fleeing to safety, physically guarding the body. Most animals flee dying creatures instinctively. A companion that stays has chosen something over instinct. |
| **The Fight Beyond Capability** | The companion engages a threat it manifestly cannot defeat in order to protect the partner -- not winning, not helping to win, but buying time. The companion continues fighting until physically incapacitated or the threat is resolved. The partner must witness this. |
| **The Three Returns** | The partner sends the companion away (for its safety, as punishment, to spare it from something) and the companion returns of its own will. Three times. The companion returns despite being sent away three times -- the third return constitutes the Kindle Moment. Cannot be manufactured; the partner cannot repeatedly "send away" the companion with intent to trigger this. |

### **Stage 3 -- The Witnessed Promise**

The partner speaks a promise to the companion in the presence of a witness -- not a formal ceremony, but a specific spoken commitment. The companion must be awake and present. The promise does not need specific wording, but it must be genuine and it must include: acknowledgment of what the companion did or chose, a commitment of reciprocal protection, and permission for the companion to leave if it ever chooses.

## **The permission clause is essential. The Companion Thread cannot form if the companion is bound -- it must be a bond between free creatures.**

### **Companion Thread Abilities**

| **Ability** | **Mechanic** |
| --- | --- |
| **Bond Sense (passive, from Thread formation)** | Both always know the other's general state -- calm, distressed, afraid, injured. Range: 1 mile. The companion cannot communicate language, but it can communicate urgency, direction, and emotional state through the Bond Sense. |
| **Synchronized Instinct (from Witnessed Promise)** | Once per Moment as a free action (does not cost Act or Instinct), the partner can give the companion one simple command that it will prioritize above all else until the partner's next Moment. This command overrides training, overrides threat response, and overrides the companion's own judgment. Use sparingly -- companions remember. |
| **The Loom****'****s Protection (passive, from Witnessed Promise)** | Once per session, when the companion would be reduced to 0 Vitality, it drops to 1 Vitality and falls unconscious instead. The partner, wherever they are, feels the near-death as 1d6 points of psychic damage that cannot be reduced. No action can suppress this. |
| **Bond Amplification (when partner is in a Fated Bond)** | A companion with a Companion Thread amplifies its partner's Fated Bond abilities when within 30 ft. Specifically: the Loom Test conversion (1 failure to success per Pulse) now applies at 60 ft range instead of 30 ft. The companion's proximity extends the Bond's reach. |
| **Resonant Presence (Triad or higher partner)** | A companion with a Companion Thread, when within 30 ft of a Triad-or-higher bonded group, adds its Number's frequency to the group's Aetheric field. This does not count toward tier advancement, but it visibly amplifies the field -- Stellar Cartographers describe it as "a fifth thread that doesn't fit the pattern but belongs." The Coil finds this confusing and has not fully classified it. |
| **Coil Blind Spot (intelligence value)** | The Fang of the Whisper does not track Companion Threads. A companion can carry a message, an object, or information about a bonded cluster across Coil checkpoints without triggering the Register's alert protocols. Serath knows this. She has not told Aethar. |

### **Companion Thread -- Path-Specific Notes**

| **Path / Companion Type** | **Interaction** |
| --- | --- |
| **Wolf-Shifter -- Shogun-Kami** | The Shogun-Kami is not quite an ordinary animal. If the Wolf-Shifter and their Shogun-Kami have a confirmed Companion Thread, and the Wolf-Shifter is part of an emerging Quint Bond cluster, whether the Shogun-Kami counts as the fifth soul is an open question the Loom has not resolved. The Ifá prophecy says "five souls." It does not define soul. This ambiguity is intentional. |
| **Primal Accord -- Beast Accord** | A Primal Accord's Beast Accord is a different relationship from a Companion Thread -- it is an attunement bond, not a soul-proximity bond. If the Accord-Walker also has an animal companion with a compatible Number, the Companion Thread and the Beast Accord coexist as distinct bonds. The companion gains Beast Resonance pool interaction: its presence adds 1 point per week to the Accord-Walker's pool for that companion's zodiac sign. |
| **Void-Hunter -- Beast Companion Calling** | The Void-Hunter's Void Quarry designation extends to a Companion Thread partner naturally -- no additional rule needed. A Companion-Thread companion has already chosen the hunt. |
| **Accord-Maker -- Homunculus** | The Homunculus has no Fate Number and cannot form a Companion Thread. It is a tool. It does not grieve. It does not return. |
| **Stellar Cartographer -- Companion Reading** | A Cartographer reading a companion's Number sees the Number and a second resonance beneath it -- the zodiac sign's frequency expressed through a living form rather than a soul-thread. They can immediately determine Companion Thread eligibility and current Thread state. They are the only ones who can. |

### **When a Companion Thread Is Severed**

| **Cause** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- |
| **Companion death** | The Bond-Severed condition applies as if a Fated Bond member died -- -2 to all Active Resonances for 1d6 months. The world becomes slightly less real. The permission clause in the Witnessed Promise does not mitigate this: the companion chose to stay. |
| **Partner death** | The companion does not become a Void-Husk equivalent. Animals do not conceptualize death the same way. But the companion changes -- Accord-Walkers and Stellar Cartographers note that a Thread-bonded companion after partner death carries the Number's resonance differently, as if holding it in trust. |
| **Deliberate release** | If the partner formally releases the companion (speaking the release aloud, in the companion's presence, explicitly granting freedom and releasing the promise) the Thread dissolves without the Bond-Severed condition. The companion may still choose to stay. The Loom notes the release. The partner's Fate Number shifts very slightly -- less than 1 point, detectable only by a Master Cartographer. |

