### **Combat Quick Reference**

### **Core Resonance Formulas**

| **Formula** | **Calculation** |
| --- | --- |
| **Strike Resonance (Attack)** | d20 + Attribute modifier + Mastery Bonus vs. target Guard Rating |
| **Warding Resonance (Save)** | d20 + Attribute modifier (+ MB if Path grants proficiency) |
| **Active Resonance (Skill Check)** | d20 + Attribute modifier + Mastery Bonus (if Mastered) |
| **Guard Rating -- Light/No Armor** | 10 + Swiftness modifier + armor bonus |
| **Guard Rating -- Unarmored Siddha** | 10 + Attunement modifier + Mastery Bonus (Tapas pool full) |
| **Guard Rating -- Gear-Forged** | 10 + Endurance modifier (constructed frame) |
| **Vitality (Depth 1)** | Roll Vitality Die + Endurance modifier (minimum 1) |
| **Vitality (each new Depth)** | Roll HD + END modifier; add to total. Use higher of Kindred or Path die. |
| **Ambient Attunement (Passive Perception)** | 10 + Attunement modifier + Mastery Bonus (if Perception Mastered) |
| **Working Threshold (Spell Save DC)** | 8 + Mastery Bonus + Weaving Attribute modifier |
| **Working Attack Bonus** | Mastery Bonus + Weaving Attribute modifier |

### **Loom Tests (at 0 Vitality)**

| Called **"**Death Saving Throws**"** in D**&**D. In Sideros the Loom of Fate holds the thread -- the world decides if it is time to cut it. |
| --- |

| **Roll** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- |
| 10 or higher | Success -- record it. Three successes before three failures: stabilise at 0 Vitality. Stop making Loom Tests (remain unconscious). |
| 9 or lower | Failure -- record it. Three failures before three successes: thread ends. Character dies. |
| Natural 20 | Instant success AND regain 1 Vitality, regaining consciousness immediately. |
| Natural 1 | Counts as TWO failures. |
| Taking damage at 0 Vitality | Each damage instance = one failure. A critical hit = two failures. |
| Massive damage (full -> 0, excess > max Vitality) | Thread ends immediately. No Loom Tests. |
| **Fated Bond -- bonded partner within 30 ft** | Converts one Loom Test failure to a success per Pulse. The bond's weight on the Loom. |
| Stabilising a downed creature | Medicine Active Resonance DC 10 as an Act within 5 ft. Stops Loom Tests; creature unconscious. Regains 1 Vitality after 1d4 hours. |

### **Warding Resonances -- Attribute Mapping**

| **Attribute** | **When Used** |
| --- | --- |
| **Forcefulness** | Athletic feats, being knocked back, crushing or physical force effects |
| **Swiftness** | Explosions, breath weapons, area effects -- anything that can be dodged |
| **Endurance** | Poison, disease, exhaustion, death effects, physical constitution |
| **Acuity** | Illusions, mind-affecting effects requiring logical resistance |
| **Attunement** | Charms, scrying, emotional manipulation, Aetheric influence |
| **Resonance** | Fear effects, social coercion, Fated Bond Active Resonances, Void corruption |

### **Weapon Mastery Rules**

| **Status** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- |
| **Mastered** | Full Mastery Bonus on Strike Resonance attack AND damage rolls |
| **Half-Mastered** | Half Mastery Bonus (rounded down) on attack rolls only |
| **Unmastered** | Resonant Discord (2d20 take lower) on all Strike Resonances with this weapon |
| **Armor without Mastery** | Resonant Discord on all FOR + SWI Active Resonances and Warding Resonances |
| **Training to gain Mastery** | 250 gm + 250 days with an instructor willing to teach you (Downtime) |

### **Fighting Styles**

Certain Paths grant a Fighting Style at Depth 1 or 2 — Solar Guard (Fighting Discipline, D1), Oathed Vanguard (D2), Fade-Guardian (D2), and Void-Hunter (D2). When a Path feature says "choose a Fighting Style," choose one from this list. A character may have only one Fighting Style at a time unless a specific Path feature grants a second.

| **Style** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- |
| **Archery** | +2 to Strike Resonance attack rolls with ranged weapons (does not apply to thrown weapons used melee, only ranged). |
| **Defense** | +1 Guard Rating while wearing any armor. |
| **Dueling** | +2 damage when wielding a single one-handed melee weapon and no other weapon in the off hand (shield permitted). |
| **Great Weapon Fighting** | When using a two-handed or Versatile (used two-handed) melee weapon, reroll 1s and 2s on damage dice. Must use the new roll, even if it is also a 1 or 2. |
| **Protection** | When a creature within 5 ft attacks an ally, spend a Reflex to impose Resonant Discord on the attack roll. Requires a shield. |
| **Two-Weapon Fighting** | When making the off-hand attack of a Two-Weapon Fighting Strike, add your Forcefulness or Swiftness modifier to the damage (normally not added). |
| **Aether-Smite Fighting** (Oathed Vanguard / Fade-Guardian only) | Channel Aetheric energy into a melee Strike as a Reflex once per Brief Attunement. Deals +1d8 radiant or Void damage (Oath/Veil determines type) at no Channel cost. Higher tier Smites cost Channels. |
| **Working-Bound Fighting** (Weave-capable Paths only) | When you Strike a target you have affected with a Working in the past Pulse, deal +1d4 damage of the Working's damage type. |

### **Cultural Combat Traditions**

Beyond the universal Fighting Styles, distinct martial traditions exist in specific cultures. These are not Path features — they are training paths a character can acquire through downtime (one Cultural Combat Tradition can be learned via 500 Marks + 6 months of training with a master of the tradition; only one Tradition may be active alongside any chosen Fighting Style).

| **Tradition** | **Origin** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Solar Chivalry** | Duchy Compact / Aurelian Coliseum | When wielding a one-handed weapon and shield, gain Resonant Fortune on Reflex Strikes (opportunity attacks). Once per Brief Attunement, may declare a Single Honour-Combat — chosen opponent makes RES Warding (Threshold 14) to disengage; on failure, both combatants gain +1d6 damage against each other for the next 3 Pulses. |
| **Mori-Ōkami Bushidō** | Mori-Ōkami Wolf-Shifter clans | Drawing the Katana (or any cultural blade) is an Instinct, not an Act. On the first Strike Resonance after drawing, +2 to attack and +1d6 damage. Once per Brief Attunement. |
| **Sagittarian Mounted Archery** | Centaur-Kin Star-Reading clans | When mounted (or self-mounted, for Centaur-Kin), ranged Strikes do not have Resonant Discord on moving targets, and the wielder may fire while their mount Dashes. +1 to Strike Resonance damage when target moved 10+ ft on its last Moment. |
| **Te Kapo Cave-Fighting** | Te Kapo Void-Readers | In dim light or darkness, gain Resonant Fortune on first Strike Resonance against unaware targets. Daggers and Cave-Darts deal +1d4 damage in darkness. May Hide as an Instinct in dim light. |
| **Moana-kin Wave-Stance** | Moana-kin Navigators | While standing in water, on a ship, or on unstable footing, gain Resonant Fortune on SWI Warding Resonances and +1 to Strike Resonance damage. Cannot be knocked Prone by any non-magical force while in water. |
| **Shen-lì Twin-Hook Mastery** | Shen-lì Jade Empire martial schools | While wielding Hook Swords (or any paired Light weapons), gain a Reflex Strike against any creature that ends its movement within 5 ft of you. Additionally: while Hook Swords are locked together (the Sword's signature property), you may make Reach attacks AND retain the locking benefit for the full Pulse rather than one Act. |
| **Dunmar Underground Defense** | Dunmarim Stone Kingdom | While wearing heavy armor and within 30 ft of a stone wall or ceiling, gain +1 Guard Rating and Resonant Fortune on Endurance Warding Resonances against being moved. In Stillness zones: this bonus increases to +2 GR. |
| **Tuathan Cold-Iron Veil-Fighting** | Tuathan Hollow-Smiths and Veil-Walkers | When wielding a Cold-Iron Tipped or Tuathan Bronze weapon, gain Resonant Fortune on Strike Resonances against Fae-Blooded, Otherworld, or Fade-Bleed creatures. Once per Deep Attunement, may strike a target as if their Otherworld-phasing was suppressed for one Pulse (force them to remain on this side of the Veil). |

**Restriction notes:** Cultural Combat Traditions and Fighting Styles do not stack their bonuses on the same Strike unless explicitly noted. A character with Defense Fighting Style and Solar Chivalry Tradition still gets +1 GR from Defense, but the Solar Chivalry Reflex Strike bonus only applies when Defense isn't the relevant trigger. The Game Master adjudicates overlaps.

### **Aether-Dampening Ore -- The Stillness**

| The Dunmarim Stone Kingdom and Republic of Argentum control Ore supply. The Coil deploys it tactically. Any encounter in a Stillness zone fundamentally changes the combat economy for Weave-capable characters. |
| --- |

| **Element** | **Rule** |
| --- | --- |
| **Effect on Weave-capable characters** | Resonance-Locked -- cannot Weave Workings of any tier while within the suppression field |
| **Effect on Aetheric Artifacts** | Temporarily suppressed -- magical weapon bonuses inactive; Aether-enhanced armor loses enhancement |
| **Black Iron weapons** | Retain full effectiveness in the Stillness (non-Aetheric by nature). Treat as normal steel in standard environments, but unaffected by Ore suppression. |
| **Ashé-Medium abilities** | Partially suppressed -- Ashe is biological, not Aetheric. Core Vessel abilities persist; advanced Invocations that require active Aether are suppressed. |
| **Gear-Forged frames** | Partial suppression depending on Geode quality. Tier I Geodes: fully suppressed. Tier III+: 50% capacity. Frame Vitality still functions. |
| **Detecting Ore zones** | Weave-capable characters feel the suppression before entering (Ambient Attunement check DC 12). Te Kapo sense it through Void-adjacent perception. Stellar Cartographers cannot read Fate Numbers inside. |
| **Ore range** | Refined Ore: 30 ft radius per unit. Dunmarim-processed: 60 ft. Argent Spire-grade: 120 ft. Stacks -- do not overlap. |

### **Combat Moment Structure**

| **Element** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Pulse Order** | d20 + Swiftness modifier each Pulse. Higher = act sooner. Resets every Pulse. |
| **Act (1/Moment)** | Strike, Weave, Grapple, Dash, Use Item, Help, Feat ability, and similar actions |
| **Instinct (1/Moment)** | Draw weapon, Path Instinct features, drink potion, unarmed strike, bonus-action equivalents |
| **Movement** | Up to Speed in feet; can split around Act. Not an action. |
| **Reflex (1/Pulse)** | Triggered reaction on another creature's Moment (Opportunity Strike, Dodge, Loom Test conversion) |
| **Resonant Fortune** | Roll 2d20, take higher. From Fated Bonds, Path features, Zodiac Feats, favourable conditions. |
| **Resonant Discord** | Roll 2d20, take lower. From unfavourable conditions, Unmastered weapons, Void exposure, Stillness. |

### **Attunement Recovery**

| **Type** | **Time** | **What It Restores** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Brief Attunement** | 1 hour (no combat) | Spend and roll Vitality Dice (pool = Resonance Depth) + END modifier per die. Restores Brief Attunement resources: some Tapas (if meditative), Resonance Seeker Chord recovery, certain Instinct abilities. +1 Vitality Die if bonded partner within 10 ft. |
| **Deep Attunement** | 8 hours (includes sleep) | All Vitality restored. All Aetheric Channels restored. All Vitality Dice restored. All Tapas Points. Omote-Ura Gauge resets to clan default. Removes 1 Exhaustion level. Clears Aetheric Depletion. Clears 1 stack of Void-Touched Exposure (or use Weep-Stone to clear more). |

### **Brief Attunement — Detail Rules**

| **Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Permitted activities** | Light tasks only — eating, drinking, tending wounds, reading, conversation, light meditation. Standing watch is permitted; the watcher does not gain the rest's benefits during their watch but may rest immediately after. |
| **Disqualifying activities** | Combat, Weaving (other than Ambient Workings), running, hard travel, strenuous physical exertion, or sustained social negotiation under pressure. |
| **Interruption** | Interrupted by combat or strenuous activity = no benefit. The Brief Attunement must begin again from zero. |
| **Vitality Dice** | Spend any number of your Vitality Dice during a Brief Attunement. Roll each, add your Endurance modifier, restore that much Vitality. Vitality Dice spent are not regained until a Deep Attunement. |
| **Frequency** | No daily limit. Multiple Brief Attunements per day are possible, but each requires its own uninterrupted hour. |
| **Bonded partner** | A bonded ally within 10 ft during the Brief Attunement grants +1 Vitality Die roll. The bond stabilizes the Aetheric recovery. |

### **Deep Attunement — Detail Rules**

| **Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Permitted activities** | At least 6 hours of sleep. The remaining 2 hours may include light activity: reading, light conversation, keeping watch, light eating, or quiet study. |
| **Disqualifying activities** | More than 1 hour of strenuous activity during the rest — combat, hard travel, Weaving anything beyond Ambient Workings, or extended Active Resonances under pressure. A single interruption of less than 1 hour does not invalidate the Deep Attunement. |
| **Daily limit** | A character may benefit from only one Deep Attunement per 24-hour period. A second Deep Attunement within 24 hours provides no benefit beyond the sleep itself. |
| **Sleeping in armor** | Sleeping in medium or heavy armor without a Path feature permitting it counts as an interrupted Deep Attunement. The Weaver gains no Aetheric Channel restoration; Vitality is restored only partially (half maximum). |
| **Vitality Dice recovery** | A completed Deep Attunement restores a number of spent Vitality Dice equal to half your Resonance Depth (minimum 1). All other Vitality Dice spent over the campaign return when those return. |
| **The Stillness during rest** | A Weaver attempting Deep Attunement within an Aether-Dampening Ore zone restores Vitality and Vitality Dice normally, but recovers no Aetheric Channels. Channels return only after leaving the Stillness. |

## **Damage System — Resistance, Vulnerability, Immunity**

Sideros uses fourteen damage types. Resistance, Vulnerability, and Immunity follow strict rules; multiple sources do not stack.

### **Damage Types**

| **Type** | **Common Source** |
| --- | --- |
| **Acid** | Caustic substances, certain Geode discharges, some Stygian Scorpion venom. |
| **Bludgeoning** | Maces, clubs, falling damage, crushing weight. |
| **Cold** | Frost giants, ice Workings, Aquarian deep storms. |
| **Fire** | Flames, lava, Ashen Ram lineage, Mesha-domain Workings. |
| **Force** | Pure Aetheric concussion — Magic Missile, Counter-Weaving recoil, certain Comet-Magus formulations. |
| **Lightning** | Storm Workings, Shango Orisha contact, certain Geode-Pilot Frame discharges. |
| **Necrotic** | Void-Husks, Coil-Stalker Lead-Scale strikes, certain Hollow Serpent emanations. |
| **Piercing** | Spears, arrows, daggers, claws, fangs. |
| **Poison** | Toxins, Serpent-Kin venom, alchemical agents, certain Stygian Scorpion strikes. |
| **Psychic** | Mind-affecting Workings, Twin Dream-Fish presence, certain Soul-Swayed effects. |
| **Radiant** | Solar Workings, Sun Workings, Aether Smite, Orisha-Touched Living Ashé, anti-Void energies. |
| **Slashing** | Swords, axes, claws, glaive sweeps. |
| **Thunder** | Sonic concussion, Resonance Seeker amplification at intensity, certain Strike Resonances at impact. |
| **Void** | Hollow Serpent emanations, Ophiuchus resonance, Apex Emanation strikes. Few defences exist against Void damage. Weep-Stone, Kanya Siddha, and certain Bonded effects can resist it. |

### **Resistance / Vulnerability / Immunity Rules**

| **Status** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- |
| **Resistance** | Damage of this type is halved (rounded down) after all other modifiers are applied. Multiple sources of Resistance to the same type do not stack. |
| **Vulnerability** | Damage of this type is doubled after all other modifiers are applied. Multiple sources of Vulnerability do not stack. |
| **Immunity** | The creature takes no damage of this type. Immunity overrides Vulnerability. |
| **Resistance and Vulnerability together** | Cancel out. The creature takes normal damage. |
| **Order of operations** | Apply all damage modifiers first (Strike critical, Resonant Fortune dice). Then halve for Resistance OR double for Vulnerability. Then apply Immunity (which sets damage to 0). |

### **Loom****'****s Favor**

The Loom occasionally acknowledges a moment of authentic play — a character acting in deep accord with their Thread, or against it in a way that matters. The Game Master is the Loom's hand at the table.

| **Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Awarding Favor** | The Game Master awards one Loom's Favor token to a player when they roleplay their character in a way that reveals truth — a hard choice consistent with their Origin, a moment of vulnerability that earns Bond weight, an act of integrity at cost, or a complication willingly embraced. Awarding Favor is at the Game Master's discretion; characters cannot earn it through optimization. |
| **Holding Favor** | A character may hold only one Loom's Favor at a time. If a player already has Favor and is awarded another, they may instead pass the Favor to another player at the table. |
| **Spending Favor** | Spend Loom's Favor as a Free Interaction (no Act, no Instinct, no Reflex) at any point — before or after a roll, before or after a Working takes effect. The Favor grants Resonant Fortune on one roll (Active Resonance, Warding Resonance, or Strike Resonance), or converts one Resonant Discord into a flat roll. |
| **Spending for narrative** | A player may spend Loom's Favor not for a roll but to introduce a small narrative element with Game Master collaboration: a useful contact happens to be in this town, a forgotten detail of geography turns out to be relevant, a Working studied long ago happens to be the right one for this moment. |
| **Loom****'****s Favor and Fated Bonds** | A bonded character may spend their Favor on behalf of their bonded partner — the bond carries the Aetheric weight of the Loom's recognition between souls. |

### **Mounted Combat**

The Sagittarian Steppes train riders the world has not seen the equal of. The Boreal Expanse depends on draft animals to survive winter. The Centaur-Kin do not need mounts — they are mounts. Many adventures depend on what your character rides.

| **Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Mounting / Dismounting** | Costs half your Speed for the Moment. A character with Speed 30 ft spends 15 ft to mount or dismount. A character with Speed 0 cannot mount. |
| **Controlled mount** | A trained, willing mount acts on its rider's Pulse Order. The rider chooses the mount's Acts (Dash, Disengage, Dodge). The rider may still use their own Acts and Instincts. The mount does not take its own Strikes unless the rider grants its Act. |
| **Independent mount** | An untrained or unwilling mount acts on its own Pulse Order. The rider may attempt to direct it with an Animal Handling Active Resonance as their Act (Threshold 12 for trained creatures, 15+ for wild). |
| **Mounted attacks** | Make Strike Resonances normally. Ranged Strikes from a moving mount have Resonant Discord unless the rider has a Path feature, Origin Feature, or Feat that prevents it (Steppe Rider Origin grants this). |
| **Falling from mount** | If a rider is reduced to 0 Vitality, knocked Prone, or the mount is reduced to 0 Vitality, the rider must succeed on a Swiftness Warding Resonance (Threshold 10) or fall Prone in a space within 5 ft of the mount. |
| **Strike against rider** | A creature attacking the rider may instead choose to attack the mount with the same Strike Resonance — at the attacker's choice, before the roll. |
| **Mount Vitality** | Mounts have their own Vitality. Standard mounts: warhorse 30, riding horse 22, draft horse 35, pony 13, mule 18, camel 25, waka (small) 60 hull. |

### **Underwater Combat**

| **Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Holding breath** | A creature can hold its breath for 1 + Endurance modifier minutes (minimum 30 seconds). After that, at the start of each subsequent Moment, drop to 0 Vitality. Moana-kin have no Vitality drop from holding breath. |
| **Movement underwater** | Without a swim speed, all movement underwater is difficult terrain (costs double). Moana-kin and creatures with swim speeds move normally. |
| **Melee Strike Resonances** | Resonant Discord on melee Strikes with weapons that aren't daggers, javelins, shortswords, spears, or tridents (water resistance interferes). Workings that produce magical weapons are unaffected. |
| **Ranged Strike Resonances** | Strikes with non-thrown ranged weapons automatically miss targets beyond their listed close range (no medium or long range underwater). Thrown weapons are at Resonant Discord beyond close range. |
| **Fire damage underwater** | Resistance to fire damage. Hot oil, lava, and certain Aetheric flame Workings ignore this — Workings created by Ifrit-line Orishas burn the water itself. |
| **Vision** | Murky water counts as Heavily Obscured (Darkness). Te Kapo Void-Sense functions normally; Stellar Cartographer Aetheric perception functions normally. |

### **Working Mechanics — How Weaving Actually Works**

Every Working has the same six properties. Knowing how each works is the foundation of competent Weaving.

### **Casting Time**

| **Casting Time** | **What It Means** |
| --- | --- |
| **1 Act** | The standard. Spend your Act on your Moment to Weave the Working. |
| **1 Instinct** | Quickened Workings (Star-Born) and certain Path features. Spend your Instinct instead. |
| **1 Reflex** | Triggered Workings — Counter-Weaving (see below), Feather Fall, Shield. Triggered by something on another creature's Moment. |
| **1 minute** | Ritual Workings cast slowly without expending an Aetheric Channel (see Ritual Weaving below). |
| **10 minutes / 1 hour / longer** | Ceremonial Workings (most healing rituals, Fated Bond formation, Kanya Siddha Purification). Cannot be Woven in combat. |

### **Range**

| **Range** | **What It Means** |
| --- | --- |
| **Self** | The Working affects only the Weaver. |
| **Touch** | The Weaver must touch the target. Use an Act to Weave; if the target is unwilling, you make a melee Working Strike against their Guard Rating to apply it. |
| **X feet** | The target or origination point must be within this distance. Measure from the Weaver. |
| **Sight** | The Weaver must be able to see the target. Aetheric concealment (invisibility, mirror illusion, dense smoke) blocks Sight range Workings. |

### **Components — Voice, Gesture, Focus**

Sideros Workings have three possible components. A Working's description lists which it requires.

| **Component** | **Abbr.** | **What It Means** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Voice** | **V** | The Weaver must speak the Working's spoken pattern — not a magic word, but a precise vocal frequency that participates in the Weave. A Deafened or Soul-Swayed-to-silence Weaver cannot Weave Voice Workings. |
| **Gesture** | **G** | The Weaver must make a specific gesture with at least one free hand. Grappled Weavers may still Weave Gesture Workings if at least one hand is free; Seized or fully bound Weavers cannot. |
| **Focus** | **F** | The Weaver must hold a Working Focus appropriate to their Path — Comet-Magi staff or crystal, Siddha prayer beads, Stellar Cartographer's instruments, Ashé-Medium's ritual bundle. Black Iron weapons can never serve as Focus. A Path's Working Focus is part of its starting equipment. |

A Working that costs material components beyond the Focus (such as the rare powder for Working a Resonant Binding) is noted in the Working description. Most Sideros Workings require only Voice and Gesture; Focus-requiring Workings are typically those drawing from Path-specific traditions.

### **Targets**

| **Target Type** | **What It Means** |
| --- | --- |
| **Single creature / object** | Affects one target. Target may make a Warding Resonance or you make a Working Strike. |
| **Multiple creatures** | Affects a specified number, each independently making any required Warding Resonance. |
| **Area of effect** | All creatures and objects in a defined shape are affected (see Areas of Effect below). |
| **Yourself** | The Weaver alone benefits or suffers from the Working. |

### **Areas of Effect**

Five canonical shapes. Each measures from a point — usually one the Weaver designates within range.

| **Shape** | **Definition** |
| --- | --- |
| **Cone** | A cone extends in a direction the Weaver chooses, with a length equal to the cone's listed size. The cone's width at any point is equal to its length from origination. Originates at a point the Weaver can touch (typically the Weaver's hand). |
| **Cube** | Defined by its side length. Originates at one face the Weaver designates within range; fills the cube. |
| **Cylinder** | A circle (defined by radius) extruded upward to a defined height. The Weaver designates the centre of the base circle within range. |
| **Line** | Defined by length and width. Originates at a point the Weaver can touch (typically the Weaver's hand) and extends in a chosen direction. |
| **Sphere** | A point in space within range becomes the centre. The sphere's radius extends outward in all directions, including up and down. Most "Radius" Workings are Spheres. |

Areas of Effect are blocked by total cover (a solid wall, a closed door), reduced by partial cover (the same cover bonuses apply to Warding Resonances), and pass freely through allies (allies are still affected if they are in the area).

### **Duration**

| **Duration** | **What It Means** |
| --- | --- |
| **Instantaneous** | The Working's effect occurs immediately and is permanent in its outcome (damage dealt, Vitality restored, an object created). The Aetheric current ends; the result remains. |
| **Until end of next Moment** | Roughly 6 seconds — used for quick combat effects (most Strike-augmenting Workings). |
| **1 Pulse / X Pulses** | About 6 seconds per Pulse — combat-scale duration. |
| **1 minute / X minutes** | 10 Pulses per minute — short tactical buffs and conditions. |
| **1 hour / X hours / 24 hours / longer** | Persistent Workings — usually require Sustained Resonance to maintain. |
| **Sustained Resonance** | The Working continues only while the Weaver maintains it (see below). |
| **Until dispelled** | The Working persists indefinitely until ended by Counter-Weaving, a specific trigger, or the Weaver's choice. |

### **Sustained Resonance (Concentration)**

Some Workings require the Weaver to actively hold the Aetheric structure together — this is Sustained Resonance.

| **Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **One at a time** | A Weaver can Sustain only one Working at once. Twin-Serpents Gemini Attunement allows two. |
| **Starting a second Working** | Beginning a new Sustained Resonance Working immediately ends any current one. |
| **Damage while Sustaining** | When the Weaver takes damage, they make an Endurance Warding Resonance (Threshold = 10 or half the damage taken, whichever is higher). On failure, the Working ends. |
| **Loom-Suspended or Loom-Tested** | Sustained Resonance ends immediately. |
| **Aether-Dampening Ore** | Sustained Resonance ends immediately on entering a Stillness zone. |
| **Ending freely** | The Weaver may end Sustained Resonance as a Free Interaction at any time. |

### **Combining Aetheric Effects**

The Aether is consistent — it does not let a single source amplify itself indefinitely.

| **Situation** | **How It Resolves** |
| --- | --- |
| **Same Working from same source applied twice to same target** | The effects do not stack. The longer duration overwrites the shorter, or the latest replaces the previous. |
| **Same Working from two different Weavers on same target** | Choose the more advantageous instance. Do not stack. |
| **Different Workings producing different effects** | All apply. A Bless and a Haste together give both benefits. |
| **Different Workings producing the same kind of effect** | The most beneficial instance applies. Two Workings granting Resonant Fortune on the same roll grant Fortune once, not twice. |
| **Working and a Path feature granting the same effect** | The Path feature governs. The Working contributes nothing beyond what the Path already provides. |

### **Counter-Weaving (Dispel Working)**

The Working "Dispel Working" appears on multiple Path lists. This is the universal Counter-Weaving rule.

A Weaver who perceives a Working being Woven (Voice or visible Gesture or visible Focus) may use their Reflex to attempt Counter-Weaving:

- Spend an Aetheric Channel of any tier from 3rd or higher.

- If the spent Channel's tier is equal to or higher than the tier of the Working being countered, the Working fails immediately.

- If the spent Channel is lower tier, make a Weaving Active Resonance vs. Threshold 10 + (tier of the Working being countered). Success = countered.

- A Working in progress that is countered fails. An ongoing Sustained Resonance Working struck by Counter-Weaving must succeed on the same check or end.

- Counter-Weaving may only be attempted against Workings being actively Woven or actively Sustained — not against the instantaneous results of a Working already completed (you cannot Counter-Weave a Cure Wounds after the Vitality is restored).

- Aether-Dampening Ore is a form of Counter-Weaving expressed through material rather than Working — it cannot itself be Counter-Wove.

### **Ritual Weaving**

Some Workings carry the Ritual tag. A Ritual Working may be Woven without expending an Aetheric Channel, but takes 10 minutes longer than its normal casting time and requires the appropriate Focus. Ritual Weaving is not available in combat. A Path must have access to ritual capacity (Comet-Magus's Formulation Ledger, Siddha Acolyte training, Ashé-Medium Orisha Invocation) to Weave Workings as Rituals; not every Weave-capable character can ritualise.

### **Ambient Workings (Cantrips)**

The smallest Workings — the ones a trained Weaver can produce without expending any Aetheric Channel. Sometimes called "Untiered" because they have no tier in the Channel progression.

| **Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Always available** | Ambient Workings can be Woven at will. No Channel cost, no daily limit. |
| **Number known** | Each Weave-capable Path lists how many Ambient Workings are known at Depth 1. Most know 2-4. Comet-Magus knows the most; Coil-Stalker, Fate-Breaker, and other low-Channel Paths have one or none. |
| **Scaling** | Damaging Ambient Workings scale at Depths 5, 11, and 17 — gaining additional damage dice. Each Ambient Working description specifies its scaling. |
| **Components and rules** | Ambient Workings have the same Casting Time, Range, Components, and Duration rules as tiered Workings. The only difference is the lack of Channel cost. |
| **Suppressed by Stillness** | Like all Workings, Ambient Workings fail in Aether-Dampening Ore zones. |

Common Ambient Workings: Guidance, Mending, Resistance, Prestidigitation, Light, Dancing Lights, Chill Touch, Fire Bolt, Sacred Flame, Spare the Dying, Toll the Dead, Vicious Mockery.

### **Conditions Reference**

All Sideros conditions with D**&**D equivalents, effects, and how they end. Conditions marked with a dagger (+) have no D**&**D equivalent.

| **Condition** | **D****&****D Equiv.** | **Effect** | **Ends When** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Corrupted** | Poisoned | 1d6 damage at start of each Moment; Resonant Discord on attacks and skill checks | Successful END Warding Resonance (DC = source); purification Working or Weep-Stone |
| **Seized** | Restrained | Speed becomes 0 and cannot be increased | Source ends; successful FOR or SWI Active Resonance as Act (contest) |
| **Prone** | Prone | Resonant Fortune vs. melee Strike Resonances; Resonant Discord vs. ranged Strike Resonances | Stand up as part of movement (costs half Speed) |
| **Sight-Severed** | Blinded | Resonant Discord on attacks that require sight; creatures have Resonant Fortune vs. you | Source ends; duration expires |
| **Deafened** | Deafened | Fail hearing checks; immune to sonic effects; Resonance Seeker aura abilities blocked | Source ends; duration expires |
| **Grappled** | Grappled | Speed 0; Resonant Discord on Strike Resonances against targets other than grappler | Act: FOR or SWI Active Resonance contest vs. grappler; grappler releases; grappler incapacitated |
| **Exhausted** | Exhaustion (6 levels) | L1: Discord all Active Resonances / L2: Speed halved / L3: Discord all Strikes & Wardings / L4: Max Vitality halved / L5: Speed 0 / L6: Thread ends | Deep Attunement removes 1 level (requires food and water) |
| **Dread-Struck** | Frightened | Resonant Discord on everything while source is visible; cannot move toward source voluntarily | Source leaves sight; duration expires; successful RES Warding Resonance |
| **Soul-Swayed** | Charmed | Treats source as trusted ally; cannot make Strike Resonances against source | Source deals damage to creature; successful RES Warding Resonance; duration expires |
| **Dazed** | Stunned (minor) | Resonant Discord on all Resonances until start of creature's next Moment | Start of next Moment (automatic) |
| **Loom-Suspended** | Unconscious | Drop prone; lose Act and Instinct; auto-fail FOR + SWI Warding Resonances; attacks have Resonant Fortune; crits within 5 ft automatic | Any healing restoring Vitality; duration (some sources) |
| **Resonance-Locked** | Incapacitated/Silenced | Cannot Weave Workings or use Channel-requiring abilities | Leave Ore zone; source duration expires; Dispel Working |
| **Resonance-Shattered** | None | Resonance-Locked + Resonant Discord on ALL rolls + Fated Bond blocked (thread still exists, cannot flow) | Deep Attunement; 5th-tier Restoration Working |
| **Aetheric Depletion** | None (5 levels) | L1: Discord on Working rolls / L2: Half damage on Workings / L3: No Workings tier 3+ / L4: No Workings any tier / L5: 1d10 psychic damage per Moment | 1 level per Brief Attunement; all levels on Deep Attunement |
| **Void-Touched Exposure** | None | Per stack: Discord on Insight; directional awareness of Hollow Serpent. At 3+ stacks: Core begins reaching character (Game Master delivers intrusive thoughts). | Deep Attunement clears 1 stack; Weep-Stone (1 charge) clears 2 stacks; Kanya Siddha Purification ritual clears all stacks |
| **Loom-Tested** | Dying | 0 Vitality; make Loom Tests each turn (d20, DC 10). See Loom Tests table. Thread ends on 3 failures. | 3 successes = stable; natural 20 = regain 1 Vitality; Medicine DC 10 = stabilised |

Conditions marked with a dagger are Sideros-original with no D**&**D equivalent. Red rows have unique Sideros mechanical significance.

### **Zodiac Attunement Feats**

REQUIREMENTS: (1) Physical encounter with your sign's Beast within 300 ft -- the Beast must actively perceive you. (2) Survive with Fate Number intact -- Void-Touched Exposure during the encounter disqualifies. (3) Reach Resonance Depth 4.

| **Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Banking the prerequisite** | You may encounter your Beast at D1 and bank the encounter. The feat unlocks at D4 as normal. The Bank cannot expire. |
| **Gear-Forged exception** | Receive Zodiac Attunement automatically at D1. The Resonant Geode heart IS the encounter. No Beast proximity required. |
| **Apex Emanation (GM Discretion)** | Each Beast produces one Apex Emanation — a singular creature so saturated with the Beast's frequency that the distinction between them becomes philosophically interesting. Surviving a genuine crisis encounter with your sign's Apex Emanation may qualify as the prerequisite at the Game Master's discretion. The encounter must have been a direct, high-stakes confrontation with the Emanation — not observation from distance. A character who has had deep interaction with a Beast's Resonant Emanations receives Resonant Fortune on their first actual Beast encounter, as the frequency is already somewhat familiar. |
| **Secondary Attunement (non-sign Beast)** | Surviving a non-sign Beast encounter grants ONE ability from that Beast's domain, usable once per Deep Attunement. This is a gift -- not trained toward. Beasts choose what they offer. |
| **Cross-Cultural Feat Variant (D8)** | After deep study of a second zodiac tradition (250 gm + 250 days minimum), a formalized version of Secondary Attunement becomes reliable once per Deep Attunement. Available at D8. |
| **Void-Touched numbers (13, 66, 99)** | Bond abilities operate at one tier higher than bond tier. Zodiac Attunement Feat functions normally but the Hollow Serpent's frequency is detectable by Stellar Cartographers behind the Number. |

