| **♓ Pisces** | **Dream-Fish****'****s Sight** **(Twin Dream-Fish)** | Communicate with sleeping creatures within 1 mile (as Dream Working; 1×/Deep, no Channel) | Once/Deep Attunement: prophetic trance — ask Game Master one yes/no about next 24 hours, answered truthfully |

### **The Three Aspects of the Beasts**

Each Legendary Beast exists in the world as a layered presence. Where you stand in a Beast's territory determines which aspect you encounter. The Beasts themselves are not creatures you fight — they are world-scale events. What adventurers actually engage with are the Beast's three Aspects, scaled to how deep into its territory the party has ventured.

| **Aspect** | **Where Encountered** | **What It Is** | **Mechanical Tier** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Peripheral Emanation** | The borders of the Beast's territory — sometimes hundreds of miles from its sacred core | Lesser creatures shaped by centuries of exposure to the Beast's frequency. Recognisably descended from ordinary biology. The Beast's attention is felt as ambient atmosphere, not direct presence. | Tactical encounter, Depth 3–7 difficulty. Can be defeated; killing them does not provoke the Beast. |
| **Resonant Emanation** | The mid-territory — within a day or two of the sacred core | Creatures saturated enough with the Beast's frequency to be partially distinct from their species of origin. The Beast acts through them as proxies; what they witness, the Beast knows. | Survival encounter, Depth 8–13 difficulty. Combat possible but rarely the win condition. Killing one will draw the Beast's attention. Surviving a Resonant Emanation encounter qualifies as the prerequisite for Zodiac Attunement. |
| **Apex Emanation** | The sacred core itself — the heart of the Beast's territory | A singular creature so saturated with the Beast's frequency that the distinction between the Emanation and the Beast becomes philosophically interesting. Each Beast produces exactly one Apex. The Apex is the Beast's voice in the world. | World-tier encounter, Depth 14+. Cannot be defeated by combat. Surviving a genuine crisis encounter with the Apex grants Zodiac Attunement automatically at the Game Master's discretion and may grant additional one-time boons. |

**Movement through the three zones:** The Aetheric pressure of the Beast's frequency intensifies as the party approaches the sacred core. A Weave-capable character feels it as an oscillation in their Attunement at the periphery, a persistent presence in their Sustained Resonance at the middle, and a force pressing against the seams of their own thinking at the Apex. Workings within the Beast's domain are at Resonant Fortune for the Weaver when the Working aligns with the Beast's nature, Resonant Discord when it opposes — and these effects compound the deeper into territory the party has gone.

**The Apex of each Beast** — with summary of the territory, the named Apex Emanation, and what the Apex grants beyond standard Zodiac Attunement.

| **Sign · Beast · Sacred Core** | **Apex Emanation** | **Apex Boon** (1×/character, surviving crisis encounter) |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **♈ Aries**  ·  Ashen Ram  ·  The Caldera (Aries March volcanic chain) | **The First-Ember Ram** — a single black ram whose fleece is continuous molten flow; calmly walks the magma rim | Fire damage Resistance becomes Immunity for 24 hours; one Working you have lost the Channel for restores |
| **♉ Taurus**  ·  Khalkotauros  ·  The Standing Stones of the Taurian Plains | **The Plain-Tread** — a vast stone-armored bull whose hoofprints become ponds that never dry | Once per Deep Attunement for the next year, drop to 1 Vitality instead of 0; permanent +1 to maximum Vitality |
| **♊ Gemini**  ·  Twin-Serpents  ·  The Ruined Library beneath Aetheria | **The Dual-Speak** — the gold rune-dragon and void-black serpent appearing as one creature switching faces between syllables | Gain a permanent second Sustained Resonance slot (functional once per long encounter beyond your normal limit) |
| **♋ Cancer**  ·  Adamant Crab  ·  The Carapace itself — the largest island IS the Crab | **The Walking Island** — the Crab itself, perceptible only when it stops being mistaken for landscape | Once per Deep Attunement for the next month, absorb a single Strike Resonance against an ally within 30 ft completely; permanent +2 to Loom Tests when ally is bleeding |
| **♌ Leo**  ·  Nemean Lion  ·  The Aurelian Coliseum (built around an existing den) | **The Solar Maned** — a golden lion the size of a townhouse, its mane visibly flowing sunlight | Resonant Fortune on Strike Resonances when outnumbered 3:1 or more; one-time: declare a deed witnessed in this encounter for permanent inclusion in song |
| **♍ Virgo**  ·  Queen Bee  ·  The Golden Hive Mountain Labyrinth | **The Queen Herself** — three feet of amber translucence atop a honeycomb throne; bees calm in a ten-foot radius | Once per week for the next year, produce a single dose of Celestial Honey (4d8 healing + removes 1 Lead-Scale level); ongoing healing Workings cost 1 fewer Channel tier |
| **♎ Libra**  ·  Great Roc  ·  The Heart-Stone above the Aurorans' sky-city | **The Shed** — a single primary feather the size of a longboat that flies on its own, animate; the Roc's chest-light visible in its quill | Once per Deep Attunement for the next month, undo one decision made within the past hour as if it never happened (consequences remain for others; only you remember both timelines) |
| **♏ Scorpio**  ·  Stygian Scorpion  ·  The Cemetery Gates of the Ashélands | **The Crystal-Stinger** — the Stygian Scorpion bearing a green crystal stinger that regrows when shed; the stinger itself is the Resonant Binding component | Past-Life Glimpse 1×/Deep Attunement permanent; permanent Poison Immunity; one secret you carry cannot be extracted by any Working short of cosmic-tier |
| **♐ Sagittarius**  ·  Star-Metal Stag  ·  The Spire of the Higher Truth (Sagittarian Steppes) | **The Waymarker** — the Stag itself, antlers configured as a navigable star-chart; sheds tine fragments that are the Resonant Binding component | Cannot become lost outdoors for the rest of your life; once per Deep Attunement for the next year, ask the Game Master one true yes/no question about the immediate future |
| **♑ Capricorn**  ·  Sea-Goat  ·  The Mountain-Sea Threshold (cave system between Dunmar peaks and the sea) | **The Both-Natured** — the Sea-Goat in full, lower half iridescent fish-tail, upper half ice-crusted mountain goat; impossibly large in the cave | Permanent Resonant Fortune on any Active Resonance involving sustained effort over days or weeks; environmental extremes no longer cause exhaustion |
| **♒ Aquarius**  ·  Kelp-Weaver  ·  The Weaver's Loom itself (kelp forest surrounding the Aquarian Archipelago) | **The Loom-Voice** — the Kelp-Weaver fully visible against the kelp; its bioluminescent nodes producing complex meaning the Resonant Geode Siddha can partially decode | Permanent Network-Sense (feel disturbances in the Weaver's Loom worldwide); permanent ability to communicate complex meaning by ATT colour-patterns to other Weave-capable Aquarius-Attuned characters worldwide |
| **♓ Pisces**  ·  Twin Dream-Fish  ·  The K'uh-la'an Cenote of Dreams | **The Twin-Dream** — both koi visible simultaneously in waking, circling a galaxy spiral in the cenote's water; one silver-and-red, one gold | Dream-Sight permanent (sleep restores even when interrupted; once per Deep Attunement, dream of the current location of one person you've met); once per year, share a dream-vision with another mortal who knows you |
| **⛎ Ophiuchus**  ·  Abyssal Leviathan  ·  The Crystalline Core beneath Argent Spire | **The Hollow Serpent** — the Wound itself, visible only to those whose Numbers carry its frequency (13, 66, 99) or who have accumulated 6+ Lead-Scale levels | None — the Apex of the Wound does not grant boons. Surviving with intact identity is the entire reward, and it is not guaranteed. |

**Hidden cores:** Some Apex sacred cores are matters of public knowledge (the Aurelian Coliseum, the Golden Hive). Others are closely-guarded (the Spire of the Higher Truth requires Sagittarian Steppes guidance; the Aurorans' Heart-Stone is unreachable without their permission). Two Apex cores are functionally unknown to the world: the Carapace itself (the Crab IS the territory; everyone who lives there is already in the sacred core), and the Crystalline Core (Argent Spire's continent is secret, and only Aethar has the approach route memorised).

**Apex encounter conditions:** An Apex Emanation does not engage casually. The Beast permits the encounter when:

- A character of compatible sign approaches with intent the Beast considers worth its attention

- A Quint Bond member arrives to perform their portion of the Resonant Binding

- A Coil action threatens the Beast's territory directly

- The Beast decides, by reasons mortals do not fully understand, that this is the moment

A party that wanders into an Apex sacred core without one of these conditions will find the Apex absent — and the surrounding Resonant Emanations behaving in ways that suggest the party is being escorted out by indirection. The Beasts protect their cores. They are also patient about it.

### **Beast Emanation Materials — Per Beast, Per Aspect**

Each of the thirteen Beasts produces three distinct materials, corresponding to its three Aspects. The Apex Harvest (T4) materials are catalogued in the table above. The Peripheral Trace (T1) and Resonant Fragment (T2) materials are catalogued below. All are domain-aligned — they amplify Workings within the Beast's domain only, and are wasted on any other.

