**Cross-tier substitution:** A T2 material can substitute for a T1 material at the same use, though doing so is wasteful (a T1 effect for T2 cost). A T1 cannot substitute upward.

**Storage rules apply across all tiers** — Hearthwood vessels, Resonant Geode caskets, and Kanya Siddha purification linen preserve the materials. Ordinary pouches permit Aetheric leak; a T2 stored in cloth may degrade to T1 over a season. Lead-Trace and Void-Touched Crystal are specifically dangerous in ordinary storage — they should be sealed in Hearthwood-and-lead lined boxes, and even then their possession is criminal in most jurisdictions.

### **Apex Fragment Reagents — Working Amplifiers**

The harvested fragments of Apex Emanations are the most powerful single-use Working components in the world. A Comet-Magus may spend a career and never see one. A Rāśi-Siddha working at a temple aligned with their sign may handle several across a lifetime. The fragments are not items; they are pieces of the Beast itself, the Aether still resonant in them. Their use is the deepest collaboration mortals have available with the world they live on.

Apex Fragment Reagents are graded across five tiers. The lower tiers are obtainable through Beast territory expeditions and trade; the higher tiers require encounter or major narrative achievement. A reagent is **consumed** when used — it is the Beast's gift to a single Working, not a permanent tool.

| **Tier** | **Source** | **Approximate Cost** | **Effect when consumed in a Working** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **T1 · Peripheral Trace** | Harvested from Peripheral Emanations at the border of Beast territory (Aetheric dust, ember-touched wool, doubled-shadow ink, etc.) | 10–50 Marks (most Beast-trading cultures) | The Working is cast with Resonant Fortune on its Working Threshold. Must be aligned with the Beast's domain. |
| **T2 · Resonant Fragment** | Harvested from Resonant Emanations in mid-territory (Resonant hide, twinned scale, shell-tooth shard, antler-tine fragment) | 75–250 Marks (Beast-aligned cultural smiths and apothecaries) | The Aetheric Channel spent on a Beast-aligned Working is restored at the end of the Pulse. Effectively a free cast. |
| **T3 · Resonant Core** | Sourced from deep-territory expedition with cultural permission (Heart-stone shard, Cenote-glass, Beast-aligned fossil) | 400–800 Marks (rare, often non-monetary trade) | Cast a Working of the Beast's domain at one tier higher than your highest available Channel. The Working is otherwise normal. Once per Deep Attunement maximum, regardless of stock. |
| **T4 · Apex Harvest** | Harvested directly from the Apex Emanation with the Beast's tacit permission (Star-Metal Antler tine, Stygian Crystal shard, Great Roc shed feather, Cenote Water vial, Celestial Honey jar) | Not for sale. Earned through encounter, trial, or Beast service. | Substitutes for the highest-tier Channel you possess. Cast any one Working of the Beast's domain without expending a Channel. Additionally: the Working's effect is at the upper bound of all variable rolls. |
| **T5 · Resonant Binding Component** | The specific fragments required for the Resonant Binding ritual itself. | Not for sale. Plot-critical. | Enables cosmic-tier rituals only. A single T5 component cannot be expended on lesser Workings — the Aether refuses the misuse. |

**Domain alignment is strict.** A Star-Metal Antler tine (Sagittarius) consumed in a Working of navigation, prophecy, or star-reading produces full effect; the same tine consumed in a Working of healing or fire produces nothing, and the fragment is wasted. Apex Fragment Reagents recognize the Beast that made them.

