### **Material Upgrade Pricing**

Beyond the standard steel forge, weapons may be made from rare materials that change their behavior fundamentally. A Longsword crafted in Black Iron is still a Longsword — but it functions in the Stillness and never breaks. The pricing below applies as a multiplier to the base weapon cost, and the work requires a smith of the material's tradition.

| **Material** | **Cost** | **Property Granted** | **Cultural Smith Required** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Black Iron** | ×5 base cost | Unaffected by The Stillness (functions normally inside Aether-Dampening zones); +1 damage; cannot be broken by any non-magical means | Dunmarim Deep-Forge |
| **Star-Metal** | ×8 base cost | Counts as silvered weapon; +1d4 radiant damage to undead and Void-Husks; cannot be misplaced (always findable by its wielder within 24 hours of separation) | Sagittarian Star-Reading clan smith |
| **Sun-Kissed Adamas** | ×10 base cost (limited supply) | Counts as magical weapon for damage resistance; +1d6 vs Void-Husks, undead, and Hollow Serpent emanations; sheds dim light in 5-ft radius in darkness | Khem-Ma'at Solar Forge (export-controlled) |
| **Hearthwood Haft** | +200 Marks (shafted weapons only) | Weapon immune to fire damage; haft never shatters under heat or impact; works on staffs, polearms, axes, hammers | Mori-Ōkami Deep Earth Clan |
| **Stygian-Edged** | ×6 base cost (blades only) | On a successful Strike, target makes RES Warding (Threshold 14) or one of their secrets becomes briefly visible to the wielder (Game Master's discretion as to which); does not affect creatures without secrets to keep | Mongolian Bog-Keeper or Ashélands Storm-Iyanifa smith |
| **Tuathan Bronze** | ×3 base cost | Accepts Aetheric inscriptions and Anointments at twice the normal efficiency (Anointments cost half the listed price when applied to Tuathan Bronze); recognized as sacred by Fae-Blooded | Tuathan Hollow-Smith |
| **Obsidian-Edged** | ×2 base cost (blades only) | Adds Bleeding property (1 damage at start of target's next Moment unless they spend an Act to staunch); blade is fragile (5% chance per encounter to chip — must be re-knapped at +50 Marks) | K'uh-la'an volcanic workshop |

**Material stacking rules:** A weapon can be made of only **one** primary material. Anointments may be applied on top of material upgrades. Some combinations have special interactions:

- **Black Iron + Aether-Quenched Anointment** = +2 damage in Stillness (the Anointment's +1 stacks with Black Iron's +1)

- **Star-Metal + Lead-Suppressed Anointment** = the weapon registers in BOTH Star-Reading and Kallos-Sworn records — politically loaded

- **Sun-Kissed Adamas + Sun-Kissed Anointment** = redundant; the Anointment is not applied

- **Hearthwood + any fire-themed Anointment** = the wielder's hands are also protected from fire while gripping the weapon

- **Stygian-Edged + Cold-Iron Tipped** = these two materials repel each other; neither effect functions while combined

### **Maintenance and Repair**

Mundane weapons and armor in Sideros are durable but not indestructible. A weapon used in dozens of encounters, exposed to seawater, magical damage, or extreme environments, will degrade. The rules below codify what happens.

### **Condition states:**

| **State** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- |
| **Pristine** | Standard. No effect. Default state of a newly-acquired or properly-maintained item. |
| **Damaged** | The item is functional but compromised. Weapon: −1 to Strike Resonance damage. Armor: −1 to Guard Rating. Visible signs of wear (notched blade, dented plate). |
| **Broken** | The item cannot be used until repaired. Weapon: no Strike Resonance possible. Armor: provides only half its GR bonus until repaired. |

**Triggers for condition loss** (Game Master's discretion as to specifics):

- A Critical Miss (natural 1) with a weapon may damage it (Game Master call, more likely if striking armored opponents)

- Failing a Loom Test while wearing armor may damage it

- Sustained exposure to Stillness, Void energy, or magical fire over multiple sessions

- A weapon that strikes an Aetheric Artifact at full force may be Damaged

- A weapon used to parry a high-tier Working's physical projection (e.g., Khalkotauros's hoof, Adamant Crab's claw) is Broken unless made of a material rated to resist it (Black Iron, Sun-Kissed Adamas, etc.)

- Submersion in saltwater for over a day Damages most metals (Moana-kin Woven Flax and Black Iron exempt)

### **Repair:**

| **Service** | **Time** | **Cost** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Pristine → Damaged repair (weapon)** | 1 day at any smith | 10% of weapon's base cost |
| **Pristine → Damaged repair (armor)** | 2 days at any smith | 10% of armor's base cost |
| **Broken → Pristine (weapon)** | 1 week at the original smith's tradition (or any smith with double cost) | 25% of weapon's base cost |
| **Broken → Pristine (armor)** | 1–2 weeks at the original smith's tradition | 25% of armor's base cost |
| **Repair of cultural weapon at non-tradition smith** | Variable | 1.5× listed cost; the work is technically correct but lacks cultural specificity |
| **Repair of material-upgraded weapon (Black Iron, Star-Metal, etc.)** | Same as above | Cost is calculated on the base weapon cost, not the multiplied material cost — the smith is restoring, not re-forging |

**Path-specific maintenance** (referenced from Path progressions):

- **Geode-Pilot Resonant Frame:** Repair costs follow the Frame Maintenance rules in the Geode-Pilot Path features; baseline 100 Marks per 10 Frame Vitality restored at any Jade Empire-aligned facility, plus 1 day of work. Field repair is possible but costs 2× and produces only temporary patches (lasting one Deep Attunement).

- **Accord-Maker Aetheric Infusions:** Maintained automatically; refresh on Deep Attunement or improve gradually with 30+ days continuous maintenance (as per Path features).

- **Comet-Magus implement:** Self-maintaining provided the user has not been Resonance-Locked in the past Deep Attunement cycle; otherwise re-attune at the nearest Comet-Magi Conclave (no cost; access required).

- **Resonance Seeker tuning instrument:** Damaged by Aetheric Depletion or Resonance-Shattered conditions. Repair = re-calibrate at any temple or Conclave; 1 day, no Marks cost.

### **Specialized environmental risks:**

| **Environment / Source** | **Risk** |
| --- | --- |
| **The Stillness** (extended exposure) | Non-Black-Iron weapons may develop "Stillness-fatigue" — a tendency to fail at critical moments. After 30+ days inside Stillness zones cumulative, roll 1d20 on weapon retrieval: 1–3 = Damaged. |
| **Weep-Stone exposure** | Volatile material; weapons stored within 5 ft of an active Weep-Stone for over a day develop Aetheric instability. Reflex Strike rolls have Resonant Discord until the weapon is purified at a Kanya Siddha sanctum. |
| **Void-Husk attacks** | Each successful strike against a Void-Husk has a 5% chance of corroding the weapon's edge — Damaged on a roll of 1 on a d20. Sun-Kissed Adamas and Aether-Quenched weapons are immune. |
| **Saltwater submersion** | Most metals corrode after 24+ hours. Black Iron, Moana-kin Woven Flax, and ritually-treated Tuathan Bronze are exempt. |
| **Resonant Geode leak** | Damaged Resonant Geodes (in Gear-Forged constructs or stored crystals) leak Aetheric energy that warps nearby weapons. A weapon stored adjacent to a damaged Geode for over a week may become a temporary Working focus (Game Master discretion — could be boon or curse). |

