### **Cultural Gear Variants**

Standard gear is available everywhere, but most cultures make their own versions of common items — and the cultural version is often available at any cultural enclave or major city. The differences are mostly cosmetic, but several have minor mechanical effects worth noting.

| **Item** | **Cultural Variant** | **Cost** | **Difference** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Lantern** | Mori-Ōkami **paper-and-bamboo lantern** | 3 gm | Half the weight; +1 to be extinguished by wind; folds flat for travel |
| **Lantern** | Dunmarim **deep-forge glow-lamp** | 20 gm | Heavier (3 lb) but functions in The Stillness; no oil required (uses Resonant Geode dust, lasts 1 year) |
| **Bedroll** | Boreal **wolf-fur roll** | 4 gm | Protects against Extreme Cold; +2 to Endurance Warding against arctic conditions |
| **Bedroll** | Moana-kin **pandanus weave mat** | 2 gm | Waterproof; doesn't degrade in saltwater; rolls small for canoe storage |
| **Waterskin** | Khem-Ma'at **alabaster vessel** | 3 gm | Keeps water cool in desert heat; insulated against Extreme Heat |
| **Waterskin** | Sagittarian **horsehide skin** | 1 gm | Designed for horseback; doesn't leak under jolting; holds 2 days water |
| **Rope (50 ft)** | Tuathan **silk-and-cold-iron weave** | 25 gm | Cold-Iron threaded; cannot be cut by Fae-Blooded or Otherworld entities |
| **Rope (50 ft)** | Sagittarian **horsehair lasso** | 5 gm | +2 to Grapple from horseback; standard length 40 ft |
| **Tinderbox** | Mori-Ōkami **Hearthwood-sliver kit** | 8 gm | Lights even when wet; one sliver lasts a month |
| **Tinderbox** | Te Kapo **void-glass striker** | 4 gm | Strikes silent (no spark sound); produces faint blue flame |
| **Holy water** | Khem-Ma'at **Solar-Blessed water** | 30 gm | +1d4 radiant damage instead of standard; Sun-Throne-consecrated |
| **Holy water** | Tuathan **Moon-Blessed water** | 30 gm | Specifically against Fae-Blooded and Otherworld; standard against undead/Void |
| **Holy water** | Ashélands **Ifá-Blessed water** | 25 gm | Works through patron Orisha — pre-blessed by a Babalawo |
| **Healer****'****s Kit** | Kanya-Siddha **purification kit** | 25 gm | Premium version; +2 to stabilize Loom-Tested; 10 uses |
| **Healer****'****s Kit** | Boreal **field surgeon****'****s roll** | 3 gm | Cheap but basic; 8 uses; common in mercenary outfits |
| **Disguise Kit** | K'uh-la'an **feather-mask kit** | 35 gm | Includes ritual feathers for Aetheric concealment; +1 to disguise checks |
| **Disguise Kit** | Coil-Stalker **operational dossier kit** | 50 gm | Includes false papers, signet impressions, and dye for hair/skin |
| **Mess Kit** | Mori-Ōkami **bento set** | 1 gm | Lacquered; meals stay fresh 24 hours longer |
| **Mess Kit** | Sagittarian **saddle-bowl** | 5 sm | Designed for eating in motion on horseback |
| **Robes** | Comet-Magus **initiate****'****s robe** | 15 gm | Cultural identification; Comet-Magi will recognize the wearer |
| **Robes** | Kanya-Siddha **amber-and-gold robe** | 25 gm | Hexagonal-patterned; counts as Holy Symbol for Bee-Tradition |
| **Spyglass** | Resonant Archive **annotated spyglass** | 1,500 gm | Includes etched Stellar references; +2 to celestial Active Resonances |

