### **The Sideros Calendar**

The world reckons time by the zodiac. The solar year is divided into twelve months, each tied to one canonical zodiac sign (Ophiuchus, the thirteenth, has no month — its sacred days fall between Sagittarius and Capricorn months and are reckoned only by Comet-Magi and Kallos-Sworn). Each month is 30 days; the year is 365 days, with the five extra days observed differently by different cultures.

| **Month** | **Sign** | **Season** | **Cultural Significance** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Month of the Ram** | ♈ Aries | Early spring | The Caldera burns; smithwork begins; Aries March holds its ritual lighting. |
| **Month of the Bull** | ♉ Taurus | Mid spring | Plowing month. Taurian Plains farmer-priests bless the earliest fields. |
| **Month of the Twins** | ♊ Gemini | Late spring | The doubled month. Aetheria Resonant Archive holds its annual debate; paired weddings traditional. |
| **Month of the Crab** | ♋ Cancer | Early summer | The Carapace Archipelago observes refuge week (closing islands to outsiders). |
| **Month of the Lion** | ♌ Leo | High summer | The Aurelian Coliseum's tournament season. The Solar Throne's Coronation festival falls here. |
| **Month of the Maiden** | ♍ Virgo | Harvest | Worldwide harvest. Kanya-Siddha Hive-Feast at the Golden Hive Mountain. |
| **Month of the Scales** | ♎ Libra | Autumn equinox | Judgment month. Duchy Compact courts hear major cases. Equilibrium's truth-field intensifies. |
| **Month of the Scorpion** | ♏ Scorpio | Mid autumn | Threshold Night (the new moon of this month) — mourning the dead worldwide. Bog-Keepers active. |
| **Month of the Archer** | ♐ Sagittarius | Late autumn | The Stag's Walk — Sagittarian Steppes nomads complete their annual migration. |
| **(Days of Ophiuchus)** | ⛎ Ophiuchus | Between months | Six days observed only by Comet-Magi and Kallos-Sworn. The Six Days of Witness; vigil kept at all Conclaves; no other public observance. |
| **Month of the Goat** | ♑ Capricorn | Winter solstice | The Sea-Goat's Climb — Dunmar holds deep-keep festivals; Mori-Ōkami mountain-monasteries hold silent rituals. |
| **Month of the Water-Bearer** | ♒ Aquarius | Late winter | The Kelp-Weaver's tides. Te Moana-nui Navigators chart courses for the coming year. |
| **Month of the Fishes** | ♓ Pisces | Early spring (rains) | The Mist-Coming — K'uh-la'an cenotes overflow; dreams sharpen worldwide. |

### **Major Festivals — The World****'****s Holidays**

| **Festival** | **Month** | **Culture** | **What Happens** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **First-Ember Day** | Aries 1 | Aries March / Boreal forges | Ritual lighting of the Caldera. Forge-Master strikes the first ember; Hearthwood vessels relit. |
| **Twin****'****s Eve** | Gemini 15 | Aetheria / Comet-Magi | Resonant Archive opens to the public for one night; paired-witness weddings traditional. |
| **Refuge Week** | Cancer 1–7 | Carapace Archipelago | Islands closed to outsiders. Shell-Speaker rituals. Sanctuary granted to anyone arriving in this week. |
| **Solar Throne Coronation** | Leo 21 | Khem-Ma'at | Annual reconfirmation of the Solar Throne. Sun-Kissed Adamas weapons publicly displayed. |
| **Hive-Feast** | Virgo 14 | Worldwide (Kanya-Siddha) | The Bee-Priestess presents Celestial Honey for one day. Common people may petition healing. |
| **Equinox of the Roc** | Libra 1 | Chinvat | The Great Roc traditionally seen overhead. Equilibrium's truth-field intensifies; legal priority. |
| **Threshold Night** | Scorpio (new moon) | Worldwide | Day of remembrance for the dead. Bog-Keepers and Storm-Iyanifa conduct rites. Past-life rituals safe. |
| **The Stag****'****s Walk** | Sagittarius 8 | Sagittarian Steppes | Star-Reading clan completes annual migration; Antler-Reader Warden's ritual. |
| **Six Days of Witness** | (Days of Ophiuchus) | Comet-Magi / Kallos-Sworn | Vigil kept at all three Conclaves. The only acknowledged Ophiuchus observance worldwide. Civilians usually unaware. |
| **Sea-Goat****'****s Climb** | Capricorn 1 | Dunmar / Mori-Ōkami | Deep-keep festivals (Dunmar); silent mountain rituals (Mori-Ōkami). Long-term oaths sworn. |
| **The Tide-Reading** | Aquarius 11 | Te Moana-nui | Moana-kin Navigators chart courses for the year; Tide-Reader Warden's public reading. |
| **The Mist-Coming** | Pisces 17 | K'uh-la'an | Cenotes overflow; dreams sharpen. Dream-Walker rituals; major public dream-witness ceremonies. |

**The five extra days at year****'****s end** are reckoned differently by culture:

| **Culture** | **Name for the Days** | **Observance** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Duchy Compact** | The Quiet Days | Civic businesses close; reflection encouraged |
| **Khem-Ma****'****at** | The Sun's Rest | Five days of solar fasting |
| **Mori-Ōkami** | The Den-Days | Clan reunion week |
| **K****'****uh-la****'****an** | The Five Mists | Five sacred dreams kept |
| **Boreal** | The Long Drink | Five days of feasting and storytelling |
| **Sagittarian Steppes** | The Empty Sky | No traveling; horses given full rest |
| **Coil interpretation** | Five Days the Loom Cannot See | Preferred timing for clandestine work — Stellar Cartographers have empirically confirmed that Fate-readings during these days produce unstable results |

