### **Downtime Activities**

### **Campaign Tracking**

### **Aethar****'****s Five Stages**

| The Serpent Bearer's plan is not guesswork -- it is documented in recovered Coil intelligence and Serath's private records. Stage 5 is not written in any Coil document; it exists only in Aethar's knowledge of the Ifa prophecy. Track which stages are active, complete, or disrupted by the party's actions. |
| --- |

| **Stage** | **Description** | **Current Status / Notes** | **Party Impact** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Stage 1** | Accelerate Void-Husk production across Kindred populations to create chaos, fear, and political pressure on zodiac institutions |  |  |
| **Stage 2** | Destabilise the zodiac political blocs. The Leonine succession crisis is Stage 2 already in motion -- Lord Leo's legitimacy fracturing is not coincidence. |  |  |
| **Stage 3** | Seize the Crystalline Core beneath Argent Spire. The Three Conclaves' combined Aetheric pressure is the only thing keeping it sealed. Remove them. |  |  |
| **Stage 4** | Void the Loom itself -- sever the cosmic framework so that Fate stops weaving futures Aethar cannot control. |  |  |
| **Stage 5 (UNWRITTEN)** | Prevent the Quint Bond from forming. The Fang of the Whisper's secondary mission: track bonded lineages, ensure the five never occupy the same location simultaneously. | SERATH KNOWS. Serath has identified 3 of 5 members and has not reported this to Aethar. |  |

### **Fated Bond Tiers**

| **Tier** | **Name** | **# Proximity** | **Key Abilities** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **I** | **Paired Bond** | Within 5 pts | Resonant Awareness (emotional state, unlimited range, same plane); Resonant Fortune on 1 Warding Resonance per Brief Attunement within 30 ft; Knowledge Transfer after 6 months; Synchronized Combat after 3 major encounters |
| **II** | **Triad Bond** | 3 souls, all within 4 pts | All Tier I. Whisper Bond telepathy (intent, sensation, same plane); Vitality transfer (half damage redirected as Reflex); Aetheric Channel Sharing (Weave-capable member loans Channel through bond) |
| **III** | **Quad Bond** | 4 souls, all within 2 pts | All Tier I-II. Full wordless communication; Death Resistance (drop to 1 Vitality instead of 0 while any conscious member in proximity); bond breach causes Aetheric discharge (structural damage in 300 ft radius) |
| **IV** | **Quint Bond** | 5 souls, all within 1 pt | All prior tiers at maximum. Aetheric Sovereignty (persistent Legendary Beast-scale field within 1 mile). Fate Sight (perceive Loom probability threads directly). Resonant Survival (no member reaches 0 Vitality while any other is conscious -- unconditional at Legendary Depth III). |

| **Special Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Void-Touched Numbers (13, 66, 99)** | Bond abilities operate at ONE tier higher than the bond tier. Bond is unstable (Game Master rolls d6 each session for unusual bond effect). Stellar Cartographers see the Hollow Serpent's frequency behind the Number when reading it. |
| **The Denied Bond** | A recognised but deliberately refused bond traps both parties in mounting instability. Alphas: erratic and reckless. Betas: controlling and resentful. Omegas: withdrawn and obsessive. Releasing it requires BOTH parties' willing participation. |
| **Loom Test conversion** | A bonded partner within 30 ft converts one Loom Test failure to a success per Pulse -- the bond's literal weight on the Loom. |
| **Aethar****'****s intelligence on bonds** | The Fang of the Whisper tracks bonded lineages. If any party member's Fate Number is within 3 points of others at the table, Aethar has a file on it. |

### **The Verse of Five — The Quint Bond Prophecy**

Recovered from Pre-Fall fragments in the Resonant Archive substructure beneath Aetheria. Dated before the Pantheonic Fall. Every Comet-Magi initiate learns the verse — most consider it metaphorical. The Kallos-Sworn study it as operational scripture.

> Five voices when the Wound speaks,

> Five threads drawn from the Twelve,

> Five bonds sealed by the Loom,

> Five gifts returning what was scattered.

> And in their gathering, the Serpent sleeps.

**Canonical interpretation** (Kallos-Sworn House Aquarius, current consensus):

| **Line** | **Meaning** |
| --- | --- |
| Five voices when the Wound speaks | Five mortals whose Fate Numbers resonate with Ophiuchus's frequency — Fate Numbers clustered tightly enough (within 4 points) to be heard as one signal. |
| Five threads drawn from the Twelve | Each bonded soul's zodiac sign corresponds to one of the Twelve Beasts. One sign may repeat; one of the five is Ophiuchus-frequency adjacent (often Void-Touched). |
| Five bonds sealed by the Loom | A Quint Bond cannot be manufactured — only recognised by the Loom of Fate. Voluntary association does not create the Bond; the Loom does. |
| Five gifts returning what was scattered | Each member must bring a component from their sign's Apex Emanation. The five components, ritually assembled, become the Resonant Binding. |
| And in their gathering, the Serpent sleeps | The Resonant Binding ritual seals the Hollow Serpent (the Wound's voice through Ophiuchus) — sealed, not destroyed. The Beast remains. The Wound silences. |

### **Competing interpretations:**

| **Faction** | **Reading** |
| --- | --- |
| **Kallos-Sworn** | The Quint Bond is the only known path to averting another Pantheonic Fall. Locate the five. Protect them. Allow the Binding. |
| **The Ashen Coil** | "The Serpent sleeps" is the threat, not the resolution. Aethar believes (or has been made to believe) that the Bond completing prevents a necessary cosmic dissolution. The Coil's Stage 5 plan exists specifically to prevent the Bond from forming. |
| **Comet-Magi mainstream** | The verse is metaphorical commentary on the Pantheonic Fall's resolution. The five threads are the world's five cosmic axes. Not literal mortals. |
| **Stellar Cartographer secret tradition** | The verse is operational scripture. Five Fate Numbers exist that, when bonded, complete a Loom-pattern that the Stellar Cartographers have been watching for centuries. Identities of the five are not publicly known and the tradition keeps them deliberately so. |

**Status of the Quint Bond at campaign start:** The Game Master determines whether the Quint Bond has formed, is forming, or has not yet been recognised. In most campaign setups, three to four members are already alive and unaware; the fifth is the wild card the campaign may revolve around finding. Player characters may or may not be among the five — this is a campaign-specific Game Master decision.

**The Active Quint Bond table** (Game Master Reference — to be filled during campaign play; do not pre-populate with player-known information):

