## **Sideros is 5E Compatible.**

### **✶  CREATIVE COMMONS ATTRIBUTION 4.0  ✶**

Under the CC-BY-4.0 license you may use SRD 5.2.1 content freely, provided the attribution above is included in your work. Section 5 of CC-BY-4.0 includes a Disclaimer of Warranties and Limitation of Liability limiting Wizards of the Coast LLC liability to you.

### **✶  SIDEROS ORIGINAL CONTENT  ✶**

All Sideros-original content, including world setting, canonical terminology (Weaving, Resonance Depth, Aetheric Channels, Fated Bonds, Pulse/Moment/Reflex, Kindred/Path/Calling, the Three Primal Essences, Zodiac Attunement, the Ashen Coil Triad, the Loom, and all associated lore), is original intellectual property and is NOT part of the SRD 5.2.1. The mechanical framework adapted from the SRD has been renamed, redesigned, and integrated in accordance with CC-BY-4.0.

### **✶  DESIGNER NOTES  ✶**

Sideros adapts and substantially transforms the 5E SRD framework. Sideros canonical terminology replaces all D**&**E 5E terms throughout this document. The SRD provides the mechanical scaffolding; Sideros provides the world, the fiction, and the play experience built upon it.

✶  ✶  ✶

### **GAME MASTER TOOLKIT**

The following sections are reference material for running an immersive Sideros campaign. None of it is canon-binding; all of it is meant to give the Game Master in-play texture without requiring improvisation under pressure.

### **Cultural Name Tables**

Quick reference for naming NPCs on the fly. Roll d10 for each list, or pick by feel. Combine first name + clan/family + (occasional) epithet to produce a layered cultural name. Epithets are earned, not inherited — use sparingly and only for figures of standing.

