| **Examiner** | 3 | 26 | 14 | +2 | Aether-Dampening Ore badge — Weave-capable characters within 5 ft cannot cast cantrip-level Workings. Confiscates Aetheric items aggressively. |
| **Inspector** | 8 | 68 | 16 | +3 | Larger Aether-Dampening field (15 ft); legal authority to detain in Duchy Compact; carries warrant documents. |
| **Grand Inspector** | 15 | 130 | 18 | +5 | Full Stillness aura (30 ft); Fallen Star project knowledge; politically untouchable except by Solar Throne intervention. |

### **Kanya-Siddha Healer**

| **Tier** | **Depth** | **Vitality** | **GR** | **Mastery Bonus** | **Key Abilities** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Initiate** | 3 | 28 | 13 | +2 | Basic healing Workings; carries Honeycomb Wax. Refuses no patient. |
| **Adept** | 8 | 65 | 14 | +3 | Multiple healing Workings; can produce limited Royal Jelly; trained in non-violence. |
| **Master** | 15 | 110 | 15 | +5 | Beast-Tender adjacent to the Bee-Priestess; produces Celestial Honey at her direction; bees actively follow them. |

### **Random Encounter Tables — By Region**

Roll d8 to determine the encounter. Half are non-combat (1-4); half are combat-adjacent (5-8). Use these as prompts, not scripts.

### **Duchy Compact / Aurelian region**

1. A merchant's caravan asks for escort to the next town (2 gm/day offered)

2. A street performer's act includes uncanny prophecy fragments (Stellar Cartographer in disguise)

3. A Solar Chivalry squire seeks witnesses to a duel of honour

4. A Coil "philanthropist" offers low-cost Working casting at a charity tent

5. **Bandit ambush** — 2d4 bandits (untrained), one carrying a Lead-Trace dagger

6. **Order of Pure Reason patrol** — Inspector-level, scans party for Aetheric items

7. **Coil cell exposure** — a screaming person rushes past, pursued by 2 Fang agents

8. **Void-Husk incident** — a recent victim, still half-changed, in alley behind a respectable inn

### **Khem-Ma****'****at desert**

1. A desert oasis with caravan hospitality (3 sm/night, water for mounts included)

2. A Sun-Kissed priest blesses the road in exchange for an offering

3. A nomadic family invites the party to share evening tea

4. A trader sells Pre-Fall artifacts of dubious provenance (Aetheria-Glass shards)

5. **Sandstorm with Resonant Ram-Emanations** — 3 fire-touched sheep, defensive not aggressive

6. **Khem-Ma****'****at scout patrol** — assess party intent; hostile if Coil-aligned items detected

7. **Bandit raid on caravan** — party caught in middle; multiple Coil hands

8. **Ashen Ram Peripheral Emanation** — territorial Ram-spawn, fierce but not malevolent

### **Mori-Ōkami forests**

1. A Mori-Ōkami clan member offers shelter in their den-hall

2. A hidden Hearthwood grove tended by a Deep Earth Clan keeper

3. A traveling tea-master sets up shop in a clearing

4. A child of the Wolf-Shifters in transition phase asks for help

5. **Bandit attack at forest edge** (Boreal raiders crossing the border for Hearthwood)

6. **Wolf-Shifter clan dispute** — party witnesses; choice of intervention

7. **Resonant Fire-Wolf** — Aries Resonant Emanation drawn to the Mori-Ōkami forge

8. **Coil Fang infiltrating Mori-Ōkami territory** — hidden purposes revealed

### **K****'****uh-la****'****an jungle**

1. A jungle cenote with welcoming local guides (1 gm offering)

2. A Lotus-keeper offers healing-petal trade

3. A Red Clan ceremony in progress (witnessed only, not interrupted)

4. A scholarly Cartographer studying ancient ruins

5. **Jaguar Clan territorial enforcement** — questions party's purpose firmly

6. **Stygian-corrupted local wildlife** — 1d4 Resonant Scorpion-spawn

7. **Coil expedition seeking Weep-Stone** — recently raided a sacred cenote

8. **Twin Dream-Fish Peripheral Emanation** — Mist-Koi appearing in shallow pool (revealed as sacred encounter, not combat)

### **Moana-kin sea voyage**

1. A welcome ceremony on landing at a Moana-kin island (no Marks; reputation-based)

2. A storm with traditional navigation guidance from a Tide-Reader

3. A Moana-kin Navigator offers passage at favorable terms

4. A floating market of inter-archipelago trade

5. **Pirate attack** — 4-6 sailors, basic weapons

6. **Sea storm with Resonant Emanations** — Aquarius Emanation creates a vision

7. **Ship boarded by Fang of the Whisper** — searching for Quint Bond related goods

8. **Abyssal Leviathan Peripheral encounter** — Lead-Touched fish, signal of Void-disturbance below

### **Boreal Expanse / Northern wilderness**

1. A Jarl-hall welcomes party with full guesting rights

2. A Forge-Master commissions Hearthwood retrieval

3. A skald asks for story-telling exchange

4. A Boreal warrior duels for entertainment

5. **Frostbeast Resonant Emanation** — territorial Beast-Kin defending range

6. **Boreal raid in progress** — party choice of intervention

7. **Coil agent infiltrating Boreal court** — Drava's interest in Jarl Skadi

8. **Skadi****'****s blizzard intensifies** — possible Kelp-Weaver communication attempt

### **Te Kapo caves**

1. A Te Kapo guide offers cave-passage in exchange for outside-world goods

2. A bioluminescent cave-lake with rare materials

3. A Void-Watcher elder shares Pre-Fall prophecy

4. A Te Kapo coming-of-age ritual welcomes outside witnesses

5. **Cave-collapse** with Te Kapo rescue assistance

6. **Coil expedition seeking Void-Glass** — armed and intrusive

7. **Resonant Void-Husk** — a Te Kapo gone wrong, more dangerous than typical

8. **Abyssal Leviathan signal** — Lead-Trace residue concentrating; the Wound is closer here

### **Tuathan Archipelago / Hedge-zones**

1. A Hollow-Smith offers Anointment work at deep tradition rates

2. A Fae-Blooded asks for a riddle game

3. A Veil-Walker invites the party to attend a Hedge-Wedding

4. A merchant of Pre-Fall Tuathan artifacts shows wares

5. **Hedge-Tavern misunderstanding** — party wakes in Otherworld

6. **Cold-Iron raid on Fae** — party choice of intervention

7. **Coil agents masquerading as Hedge-Folk** — recognizable to Tuathan

8. **Otherworld bleed-through** — Fae-Bleed creature crossing during waning moon

### **Sagittarian Steppes**

1. A Star-Reading nomad offers passage and one true Reading

2. A horse-trader with notably skilled mounts

3. A traveling Antler-Reader Warden's apprentice

4. A festival of the open sky with welcomed outsiders

5. **Steppe raiders** — small group, mounted

6. **Coil agent seeking Sagittarius alignment** — Stage 5 work

7. **Wild Resonant Stag-spawn herd** — territorial but not malevolent

8. **Star-Reading clan messenger encountered** — passes a brief, knowing glance to one party member, then continues without engaging. Game Master discretion on identification.

### **Ashélands**

1. An Iyanifa offers Ifá divination for an offering

2. A Babalawo seeks witnesses to a Working

3. A community festival in progress (welcoming guests)

4. A market of Iron-Staff-blessed tools

5. **Storm-Iyanifa called to a Stygian Scorpion territorial encounter**

6. **Slave traders operating illegally** — party choice

7. **Coil cell exposed** — local community responds

8. **Adebowale Null sighting** — distant figure observed, identity unconfirmed

### **Shen-lì (Jade Empire)**

1. A Gear-Forged ambassador requests passage assistance

2. A Resonant Geode mine offers tour for inspection-licensed visitors

3. A Jade Empire scholar seeks foreign perspective on translation

4. A formal tea ceremony with potential political stakes

5. **Gear-Forged uprising in progress** — runaway constructs

6. **Jade Empire intelligence operation** — party caught in middle

7. **Coil infiltration of Shen-lì court** — high-stakes

8. **The Twelfth-Plus-One in the distance** — ceremonial appearance, never engaged

### **Chinvat highlands**

1. An Eagle Clan messenger offers guidance up the path

2. A truth-keeper interviews party at the Asha-field perimeter

3. A high-altitude vista with cultural welcoming

4. A Spentu-marked merchant trades highest-grade goods

5. **Eagle Clan border patrol** — strict but fair

6. **Coil under Vazir Nullwing****'****s direction** — corrupting Equilibrium

7. **Aerial threat** — Resonant Roc-Emanation, territorial

8. **Vazir Nullwing herself** — sighted distantly, never engaged directly until campaign endgame

### **Failure-as-Progress Prompts**

When a player rolls badly on a critical Active Resonance, use a prompt below to convert the failure into plot momentum. Pick one that fits the moment.

1. Your forgery passes inspection but a Khem-Ma'at clerk recognises you specifically and files the name.

2. You miss the Strike but your weapon embeds in a tapestry — pulling it free reveals a hidden passage.

3. Your stealth fails but the guard who sees you is someone your character knew long ago — what now?

4. You fail to disarm the trap; it triggers, but in doing so reveals it was Coil-engineered.

5. Your healing Working fails — the patient lives, but their next dream is yours instead of theirs.

6. You fail to persuade the merchant, but their refusal is so emphatic it draws an unwelcome witness.

7. You fail to navigate; you arrive somewhere else — where you find what you weren't looking for.

8. Your forgery is too perfect — the recipient assumes it's important and acts accordingly.

9. You fail the Loom Test by 1 — you live, but you remember being dead for one Pulse.

10. You fail the Reading — the Stellar Cartographer sees a different Fate Number in you than expected.

11. Your Working backfires — but the secondary effect is exactly what someone else needed.

12. You fail to identify the item — but in handling it, you have triggered a small Working it carries.

13. Your bond-check fails — but the failure reveals the bond was always one-sided in a way you didn't see.

14. You fail to keep the secret — but the listener is one who can be trusted with it, against expectation.

15. Your tracking fails — you find a different trail, far older, leading somewhere worse.

16. You fail to recognise the cultural courtesy — your unintentional offense begins a more honest conversation.

17. You fail the Endurance Warding — you collapse, but in collapsing you are taken somewhere significant.

18. You fail to convince the council — but one councillor speaks up later, privately, with information.

19. You fail to read the inscription — but a passing Comet-Magus does, and asks where you found it.

20. You fail to suppress your reaction — and the emotion you show is exactly what disarms the NPC.

21. Your hidden movement fails — you are seen, but by someone you trusted who pretends not to see.

22. You fail to outrun pursuit — caught, you are taken not where you feared, but somewhere you needed to go.

23. You fail to keep balance on the cliff — you fall, and where you land is the actual destination.

24. You fail to identify the Void-Husk — but in your hesitation, you see what it was before it changed.

25. You fail the Resistance Working — you are influenced, but the influence reveals the influencer's name.

26. You fail to barter the price — but the merchant, intrigued, offers a side-deal you didn't think to ask for.

27. You fail to find the inn — you sleep rough, and in the morning you see what travels by night here.

28. You fail the disguise — your true identity is recognised, but by someone who has reason to keep it secret.

29. You fail the divination — but the false reading turns out, retrospectively, to have been correct all along.

30. You fail to defeat the enemy — you flee, but your retreat takes you past something the campaign needs you to have seen.

### **Player Handout Templates**

Pre-prepared handouts dramatically lift Sideros's immersion. Below are handout types with brief content notes. Game Masters should produce these as physical or visual artifacts the players can hold and read.

| **Handout Type** | **Format** | **Content Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Solar Throne Formal Summons** | Wax-sealed scroll | Ornate language; specific summons date; cultural Khem-Ma'at idiom; carries political weight |
| **Intercepted Coil Dead-Drop** | Scrap of paper, blood-spotted | Cryptic operational code; partial; signature initial of a Triad member |
| **Stellar Cartographer****'****s Fate Reading** | Star-chart annotated by hand | Fate Number written in formal star-script; brief interpretation; signature and date |
| **Babalawo****'****s Ifá Inscription** | Engraved bone or wood plaque | Ifá pattern; one specific divination relevant to a player; cultural language |
| **Comet-Magi Conclave Bulletin** | Formal printed broadsheet | Reports on recent Working activity worldwide; redactions visible; signed by Arch-Oracle |
| **Lost Mori-Ōkami Clan Letter** | Folded paper with calligraphy | Family member's last letter; emotionally weighty; cultural specificity |
| **K****'****uh-la****'****an Dream-Vision Record** | Glyph-marked bark | A dream-vision drawn by a Veil-Walker; ambiguous; player-interpretive |
| **Tuathan Hedge-Tavern Card** | Faded card with old script | Invitation to a Hedge-Tavern that may not exist when sought; address shifts |
| **Sagittarian Star-Reading** | Cloth annotated with charcoal | Trail map plus star-position annotations; cultural language |
| **Order of Pure Reason Notice** | Official poster | Formal denouncement of named Aetheric practitioner; carries legal weight |
| **Ashélands Iyanifa Blessing** | Beaded cord with attached note | Charm against specific threat; spoken-aloud phrase required to activate |
| **Boreal Jarl-Hall Invitation** | Carved wooden token | Guest-right token; recognized by all Boreal Jarls; transferable |
| **Coil ****"****Charity****"**** Pamphlet** | Printed leaflet | Innocent-looking; recruits through compassion; reveals nothing damning on inspection |
| **Quint Bond Verse Fragment** | Pre-Fall paper, partial | Just one line of the Verse of Five; the player who receives it doesn't know what it is |
| **Aethar****'****s Personal Letter** | Hand-signed parchment | Late campaign; charming; reveals more than intended; carries the Wound's faint signature |

### **Regional Soundscape Reference**

Sound is the fastest path to immersion. Each cultural region has a distinctive auditory texture. The references below are starting points; Game Masters should adapt to their group's musical preferences.

| **Region** | **Sonic Elements** | **Musical Reference (any pieces fitting these descriptions work)** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Duchy Compact / Aurelian** | Brass, organ, choral; ceremonial fanfare; coliseum crowds | Late medieval European choral; Renaissance brass ensembles |
| **Khem-Ma****'****at desert** | Wind across stone; reed flute; deep ceremonial drum; throat-singing | Egyptian classical maqam; ancient near-eastern wind instruments |
| **Mori-Ōkami forests** | Wind through pine; bamboo flute (shakuhachi); distant taiko; wolf calls | Japanese traditional shakuhachi; minimalist taiko |
| **K****'****uh-la****'****an jungle** | Cenote water sounds; ocarina; rainforest birdcall; ceremonial conch | Mesoamerican ocarina; jungle ambient; Mayan flute |
| **Moana-kin sea** | Ocean waves; conch trumpets; rhythmic chanting; outrigger water-slap | Polynesian choral; conch and percussion; chant traditions |
| **Boreal Expanse** | Howling wind; deep frame drum; horn calls; ice cracking | Sami yoik; Norse-inspired ambient; old Scandinavian folk |
| **Shen-lì Jade Empire** | Erhu (two-string fiddle); guzheng; bells; mechanical Gear-Forged hum | Chinese classical erhu and guzheng; structural metallic ambient |
| **Chinvat highlands** | High wind; eagle cries; santur (hammered dulcimer); call to truth | Persian classical santur and ney; high-altitude monastic chant |
| **Ashélands** | Talking drums; calabash percussion; brass-bell; community call-and-response | West African talking drum; Yoruba percussion; afrobeat-adjacent |
| **Sagittarian Steppes** | Horse hooves on packed earth; morin khuur (horse-head fiddle); long-song; throat-singing | Mongolian throat singing; morin khuur; steppe folk |
| **Tuathan Archipelago** | Wind through gorse; uilleann pipes; harp; otherworld bell-like silence | Irish traditional uilleann pipes; harp music; Celtic ambient |
| **Te Kapo caves** | Echoing water-drips; bone-flute; silence; bioluminescent hum (low harmonic) | Australian Aboriginal didgeridoo (cave acoustics); minimalist ambient; deep drone |
| **Dunmar deep-keep** | Stone-on-stone resonance; deep horn; chant in low registers; rhythmic forge-strike | Throat singing; Tibetan ritual horns; subterranean ambient |

